(3811, 2, '2013-11-21 22:37:57', '2013-11-21 22:37:57', 'Dear EESTEC-ers,\r\n\r\nWe are proud to invite you to our traditional event JAZZ DO IT!, because its 3<sup>rd</sup> edition! It was great previous times, so we have decided to do it again! That''s why you are welcome to join us at the biggest jazz event in Southern and Eastern Europe "<a href="http://www.nisville.com/" target="_blank">Nivillejazz festival</a>". Together we will enjoy the good jazz sound accompanied with great atmosphere that only EESTEC exchangecan provide. Organized in the medieval<a href="http://img704.imageshack.us/img704/1240/centar.jpg" target="_blank">fortress</a> andvisited by more than <b>100.000 people</b> only last year, Niville hosted some of the biggest stars of jazz music: Hans &amp; Candy Dulfer, Grace Kelly Band, Incognito, Solomon Burke, Benny Golson, De Phazz, Roy Hargrove, Sly&amp;Robbie, Mungo Jerry, Tom Harrell, Rick Margitza and many others. Worlds best jazz musicians and 50other bands will jazz up on 5 different stages for us!\r\n\r\nParticipants will also have unique opportunity to participate at <a href="http://www.nisville.com/index.php/en/workshop" target="_blank">workshops</a> held by the best jazz musicians.\r\n\r\nRegular price for this festival is about 50 Euros, but as our guest you aregetting it for <b>free</b> :)\r\n\r\nBut, thats not all. The City of Ni has great cultural and historical heritage. Serbia is birthplace of 17 Roman emperors, and one of the most important persons in European history, emperor <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Constantine_the_Great" target="_blank">Constantine the Great</a>, was born in Ni (roman name <b>NAISSUS</b>) in 272AD. We are very proud of him, because he was the greatest among all Roman emperors and certainly the person who changed the course of human civilization. And this year is very special because we celebrate 1700 years of issuing the Edict of Milan, which proclaimed religious tolerance in the Empire and stopped numerous persecutions. He had also built a new imperial capital Constantinople, was first Christian emperor in Europe, his mother Saint Helena found True Cross. And by being a birth town of such important person, Ni is also called imperial city. You are going to visit his villa <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mediana" target="_blank">Mediana</a> and many other sights that testify rich history of this place between East and West.\r\n\r\nYou will also visit a <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ni%C5%A1_Fortress" target="_blank">Fortress of Ni</a>, where Niville jazz festival takes place. The fortress exists at this place for more than 2000 years, and has layers from different historical periods. Its in this condition since XVII century, and now its one of the best preserved fortifications of Ottoman style in Europe. In Ni exists one unique monument in the world, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Skull_Tower" target="_blank">Skull Tower</a>, which was built from skulls of the warriors who died in the egar battle. You will also visit a <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_of_%C4%8Cegar" target="_blank">egar monument</a> where this famous battle took place. Well show you one very nice relaxing place, <a href="http://www.nistourism.org.rs/health-oasis.html" target="_blank">Nika Banja</a> spa which has radioactive healing water and well go swimming there with a lot of EESTEC spirit!\r\n\r\nAnd if you think that we only have history, youre wrong, because Ni is known as town where you can have a lot of fun. We have centuries old hedonist legacy! You will enjoy the best Serbian food (world-known barbeque, special burek of Ni and many others), drinks (rakija, wine etc.) and of course a lot of good music. There wont be a single moment that youll be hungry, because Serbs like good food in big quantities. All that you will be able to taste in a traditional ambient at the special night in <b>kafana</b>. You will certainly learn what is traditional southern <b>merak</b>.\r\n\r\nThis event is completely financed with grant given by Serbian Oil Company <b>NIS</b>, the most profitable Serbian company, so you will be treated like emperors in imperial city!\r\n\r\nSo the crazy summer cocktail with... traditional Serbian drinksand food plenty of great music nice town a lot of EESTEC spirit Mix all that in asummer temperature and share it with good orgaNICEers.\r\n\r\nWhat are you waiting for?\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="http://img404.imageshack.us/img404/5156/jazzdoitcopy.jpg" target="_blank">JAZZ DO IT!</a></span>\r\n\r\n<b>Application </b>by sending this <a href="https://www.dropbox.com/s/bhpajuwmfeiqsvc/Appendix%20C%20-%20Application%20Form.odt" target="_blank">form</a> to <a href="mailto:nis@eestec.net" target="_blank">nis@eestec.net</a>; later maybe via <a href="http://eestec.net" target="_blank">eestec.net</a>', 'Jazz do it 2013!', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '3129-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 22:37:57', '2013-11-21 22:37:57', '', 3129, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3811', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3812, 2, '2013-11-21 22:39:40', '2013-11-21 22:39:40', '<div>\r\n\r\n<i>When we define the Photograph as a motionless image, this does not mean only that the figures it represents do not move; it means that they do not emerge, do not leave: they are anesthetized and fastened down, like butterflies.</i>\r\n\r\nRoland Barthes define the photograph with these sentences in Camera Lucida. Im sure that most of you interested in Photography in some way, try to save some memories and feelings in frame, look to huge world from a little viewfinder.\r\n\r\nNow, LC Eskiehir organizing an amazing workshop about Photography for the second time. Were proud to invite you to Photosynthesis 2 Were offering you an amazing week, lots of fun, useful trainings, great parties, delicious Turkish food and chance to recognize other cultures with photography.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\nIn this workshop, you will get basic knowledge and useful tips about photography and then you will practice on historical and cultural places. And at the end, best photos will be displayed in the most popular place in Eskiehir. On the other hand, you will be able to explore Eskiehirs nightlife, historical places around Eskiehir, Turkish cuisine and beauties of a student city.\r\n\r\nOne more thing; as you know we applied to Grant for this workshop. But results hasnt been announced. If it will be accepted, we can pay to you your travels costs %70 as a standardprocedure. We will share the news with you as soon as possible.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSee you in Eskiehir.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Apply :</b>As you know<a href="http://eestec.net/" target="_blank">eestec.net</a>is not reachable. So you can fill this<a href="https://www.dropbox.com/s/bhpajuwmfeiqsvc/Appendix%20C%20-%20Application%20Form.odt" target="_blank">form</a>and send us to apply until<a href="http://eestec.net/" target="_blank">eestec.net</a>is on again.\r\n<div><i>For additional information please contact me.</i></div>', 'Photosynthesis 2', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '3112-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 22:39:40', '2013-11-21 22:39:40', '', 3112, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3812', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3813, 2, '2013-11-21 22:41:33', '2013-11-21 22:41:33', '<p dir="ltr">Ladies and gentlemen,</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">The rumours you heard are true. EESTEC LC Skopje is proud to announce its second summer exchange, EESTECers Gone Wild 2. Motivated from the successful last year exchange, this time we offer you even more rocking summer.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">What is better time for exam get-away then summer? Sunny days, traveling round the country, tones of fun, parties 24/7 and all that with EESTECers from around Europe are just a few of the things included in our EESTEC vacation. Start planning now your wild get-away time!</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Well Eestecers, the only thing that is obligatory to bring is your EESTEC spirit.The rest you can do is pack your swim suits and get your camera, because its time for shooting priceless moments from the wildest trip in the history.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p dir="ltr">Let us present you the unknown cities you will visit...</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">- <a href="http://www.exploringmacedonia.com/skopje.nspx" target="_blank">Skopje</a> (2 days)</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">- Probistip (1 day fun in the <a href="http://www.aquaparkmacedonia.mk/gallery-wts/?lang=en" target="_blank">Aquapark</a>)</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">- <a href="http://travel2macedonia.com.mk/destinations/kavadarci" target="_blank">Kavadarci</a> (2 days tasting Macedonian wine and rakija)</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">- <a href="http://www.exploringmacedonia.com/krusevo.nspx" target="_blank">Krusevo</a> (1 day breathing fresh mountain air with a stop in <a href="http://www.exploringmacedonia.com/prilep.nspx" target="_blank">Prilep</a>)</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">- <a href="http://www.exploringmacedonia.com/ohrid.nspx" target="_blank">Ohrid</a> (4 days - all night, all day, partying with participants from International Motivational Weekend)</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p dir="ltr">For more details, visit this <a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1hkXjhrJ60qKPPN0xXEM_jr-yAbNrfMgtidNCz2AaxLQ/edit?usp=sharing" target="_blank">link</a></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Just to be on clear, during this EESTEC vacation we provide all the logistic and organization, but we can not provide the food and the accommodation. On this <a href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheet/ccc?key=0Ahm5dmgMu2KBdERlMkV5bUtqZ1pDdlhLdjFTWlJ3SWc#gid=0" target="_blank">link</a> you can find price list for average prices for the food, drinks and other expenses.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">If you are brave enough to be part of EesteCers Gone Wild 2, then fill this <a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1nqTmy1YRZf5C6d5IWKHG28x6YgvQs9V6ZqlnonSnPGE/viewform" target="_blank">form</a></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Let your spirit do the walkin'' through the party rockin''!</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">If you have any kind of question or maybe suggestion or wishes what to visit or what to do you can contact us : <a href="mailto:lcskopjecontact@gmail.com" target="_blank">lcskopjecontact@gmail.com</a></p>', 'EESTECers Gone Wild 2 - LC Skopje', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '3108-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 22:41:33', '2013-11-21 22:41:33', '', 3108, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3813', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3814, 2, '2013-11-21 23:28:24', '2013-11-21 23:28:24', '<div id="parent-fieldname-text">\r\n<div>DearEESTECers,</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\nEESTEC Chairpersons'' Meeting is the second biggest event of EESTEC. This year it will be held by<strong>LC Tallinn</strong>from<strong>3-9 November</strong>. Each LC, JLC and Observer has the right for<strong>one place</strong>on ECM. Therefore, we would kindly ask you to discuss with your Local Board and decide on the representative.\r\n\r\nApplications must be submitted via eestec.net and by sending an email to chairwoman[at]eestec[dot]net with the following information:\r\nFull name, LC, Position in your Local Board or LC\r\n\r\nPlease make sure you use the following tags in the subject of your email:\r\n[ECM''13][Representative Application][LC ''NAME OF LC'']\r\n\r\nDeadline for applications is the <strong>7th of September</strong>.\r\n\r\n<strong>Main Goals of ECM 2013</strong>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nThe main focus of ECM 2013 is both Local and International Level. First goal is to strengthen the (J)LCs and Observers by educating Board members via trainings and by sharing knowledge. Second goal is to improve the international awareness and involvement of the members.\r\n\r\n<strong>How to reach those Goals?</strong>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nFollowing sessions/trainings will be held during ECM 2013 :\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n- GMs : 2 GMs will be held this year. Reports on the activities of the association on the past six months as well as RoP change proposals will be presented.\r\n\r\n- International awareness session : This session will be designed in 2 levels. The beginner level session, destined for less experienced representatives, will be an introduction to the structure and international projects in EESTEC. The advanced level, destined for experienced members, will be an introduction to challenges that EESTEC faces and also discussions will be held on how to overcome them.\r\n\r\n- LC Hangout : Evening Hangout with all LCs, where they can discuss with each other.\r\n\r\n- Open Space Technology (OST) : During this session, representatives will suggest topics to be discussed. Afterwards, they will vote on the topics they want to discuss and the most voted ones will be analyzed.\r\n\r\n- Trainings : 3 Soft Skills trainings for less experienced participants. Topics of those trainings will be announced later on.\r\n\r\n- Working sessions : In parallel with the Trainings, the experienced members will be invited to collect best practices of LCs into a document which will be presented and shared with the rest of the members at the end and after ECM. The topics of the working sessions will be announced later on.\r\n\r\n- EDUDay will be held on the 5th of November.\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>Profile of participants of ECM</strong>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\nConsidering the fact that there is only one place per LC and important decisions will be taken during ECM, the chairperson is highly recommended to attend. However, if it is not possible, then an experienced member or a future candidate for your board should attend.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div>For any questions or clarifications, please send an email at board[at]eestec[dot]net.</div>\r\n</div>', 'EESTEC Chairpersons'' Meeting 2013', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '3144-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 23:28:24', '2013-11-21 23:28:24', '', 3144, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3814', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3815, 2, '2013-11-21 23:28:46', '2013-11-21 23:28:46', '<div id="parent-fieldname-text">\r\n<div>\r\n<div>Dear EESTECers,</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>The wait is finally over!</div>\r\n<div>LC Ljubljana is happy to announce its dual workshop "<strong>Facebook CPR</strong>"!</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>That''s right.</div>\r\n<div>This year we''re offering you not one, but TWO ways to improve your skills in EESTEC!</div>\r\n<div>Coding or Public Relations.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>Are you a programmer? Do you want to become one? If you value order, structure and problem-solving, you can choose to enter the fun and innovative world of Facebook apps! Programming is one of the most valuable abilities a person can have today and the market is becoming huge! Imagine! The next Angry Birds might just as well be yours.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>What is the topic?</div>\r\n<div>The goal of this workshop is to teach attendees a basic understanding of facebook app programming and acquaint them with the developmental options that facebook supports. As a participant you will get a chance to develop your own application and implement facebook supported functions as well as work closely with professionals from successful app companies. You will also work on other aspects, such as public speaking and teamwork. Although you can join without any prior knowledge of programming, a basic understanding of HTML and Javascript is appreciated. The workshop itself will consist of lectures and programming sessions, where you will team up with other EESTECers to work on your application.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>But that''s not all! We at LC Ljubljana know that a student''s mind can''t work properly without some kind of release. A head full of knowledge can collapse under its own weight. So we took care of that too! We have prepared a number of fun social activities that take care of your mind and soul. On top of that you will be able to explore the beautiful streets of Ljubljana, enjoy its charming and vibrant nightlife and even attend the legendary City Rally!</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>That has to be it, right?</div>\r\n<div>WRONG!</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>After the workshop, you''ll also get to attend the International Motivational Weekend. It is a huge EESTEC event with people all across Europe. It includes soft-skill training, socializing with EESTECers from numerous LCs, crazy themed parties and best of all: it''s free for all workshop attendees.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>We invite you to join us from 19th (arrival day) to the 27th (departure day) of October 2013 and become part of another unforgettable EESTEC experience here in Ljubljana, Slovenia.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>We''re hearing some rumours (hint: 404) that<a href="http://eestec.net/lc/" target="_blank">eestec.net</a>still doesn''t function as it''s supposed to, so we''ve put up a<a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1J6zrtOzwy89qMmjsQSdU74yGlMYL2oZO6vPkp6xN9as/viewform" target="_blank">form where you can apply</a>.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>See you all in Ljubljana!</div>\r\n</div>', 'Facebook CPR: FB Apps', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '3140-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 23:28:46', '2013-11-21 23:28:46', '', 3140, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3815', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3816, 2, '2013-11-21 23:29:07', '2013-11-21 23:29:07', 'Dear EESTECers,\r\n\r\nAfter the success of LC Hamburg''s last workshop - "The EesteCube", we are presenting our brand new production DiscoTech\r\n\r\nThe curtains haven''t been raised yet, but our short "trailer" will give you some hints of what awaits you.\r\n\r\nIn the main role are starring ten (eventually more) professional Eestecers.\r\n\r\nAgain the story takes place in thegreenest and probably most beautiful city in Europe - Hamburg.\r\n\r\nThe plot consists of unforgettable nights at the famous Reeperbahn street, a trip to one of the biggest airline companies - Lufthansa, as well as, visiting the second biggest harbor in Europe. Moreover, there will be an adventurous city rally and acanoe ride in our favorite lake in the middle of the city - the Alster,all accompanied by "tasting" of German beer. And all these amazing scenes will be enlightened by the unique devices that our smart main characters are going to build.\r\n\r\nRegarding the academical part, this time the actors will have to show how music and lights combine through technology. Their task will be to make frequency analysis of audio files and with the help of digital signal processing and some RGB LEDs make the music shine. Therefore, you can take your talent our of the closet, record yourself singing, playing your favorite instruments, or just making silly noises.. eestec style.. and see what kind of beautiful enlightment would come out.\r\n\r\nThe scenario will be presented by our professors and co-students, however in order to pass the casting the actors should have basic C programming knowledge.\r\n\r\nSo put your costumes and makeup on, get your mp3 players and apply for this fascinating workshop.\r\n\r\n<span style="font-size: medium;">We are waiting for you!</span>', 'DiscoTech', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '3135-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 23:29:07', '2013-11-21 23:29:07', '', 3135, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3816', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3817, 2, '2013-11-21 23:31:35', '2013-11-21 23:31:35', 'Dear Eestecers,\r\n<div>It has come to our knowledge that the period between<strong>July 18th</strong>to<strong>July 21th</strong>is the time you will have the most fun this summer, period full with tourists and a lot of parties. Well, probably because its time for LC Skopje to announce and invite you to its first International Motivational Weekend, held in Ohrid, one of the most beautiful cities in Macedonia.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=meeKffWE_Uc" target="_blank"><strong>Ohrid</strong></a>is known as the pearl of the Balkan and if you want to party until the morning hours it is definitely a place to be with its numerous beach parties. Because of the uniqueness of Ohrid Lake and the city, they are part of UNESCO, as one of the few places on the list World Inheritance.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>This IMW is extremely important for our LC, not only because we are organizing for the first time but also this year we are celebrating our The number of your fingers Birthday :P So we will be very pleased if you come to celebrate it with us on EESTEC commonly known way :)</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>Its not only our birthday associated with the number 10. This year is coming<a href="https://www.facebook.com/events/143474625847806/?context=create" target="_blank"><strong>EESTECers Gone Wild 2</strong></a>, but this time even wilder :P The adventurous crew of LC Skopje is offering you 10 days (including the IMW) of crazy summer vacation and a chance to see the nature beauty of our country.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>The participation fee for the IMW is<strong>50</strong>and it includes both ways ticket from Skopje to Ohrid, accommodation, 3 meals per day and of course drinks. Also it includes a little surprise which we guarantee you will like it.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>So EESTECers, this means all you have to do is apply, bring yourself here in Macedonia and take your EESTEC Spirit with you to have a wild summer break.</div>\r\n<div>We promise you will feel all summer joys</div>\r\n<div></div>', 'IMW: 10 years LC Skopje', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '3106-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 23:31:35', '2013-11-21 23:31:35', '', 3106, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3817', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3818, 2, '2013-11-21 23:32:16', '2013-11-21 23:32:16', '<div>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-family: verdana, sans-serif;">Dear EESTECers,</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-family: verdana, sans-serif;">Have glamorous events and movie spotlights always been out of reach? Have you always dreamt of experiencing the spirit of Hollywood? If so, youre in luck! LC Sarajevo will provide you the ideal opportunity to learn everything you have ever wanted to know about movies: producing, editing, acting and much more.</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-family: verdana, sans-serif;">Europe''s most awesome LC is proud to invite you to the <b>3rd eMovie Academy</b>, which is becoming a tradition appealing to many potential artists and movie fanatics. We are offering you a week of fun, a week of glamour, a week of learning and most of all a week of <b>EESTEC Spirit</b>! Join us from <b>15th to 22nd of August </b>and enjoy the best experience of your life!</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-family: verdana, sans-serif;">The academical aspect will contain lectures and workshops about elements of movie making. You will learn to use professional software tools for movie-making, and at the end you will be able to make your own movie!</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">In the period from 16th to 24th of August Sarajevo will gather movie elite from all over the world in one place, and bring them closer to fans and movie lovers. This is the period of one of the most respected movie festivals in Europe - the<b>Sarajevo Film Festival</b>. During the festival, Sarajevo becomes the center of Europe''s best cinema and entertainment! Movie stars such as Angelina Jolie, Morgan Freeman, Brad Pitt and Kevin Spacey are amongst the lucky people who have experienced Sarajevo at its best - dont miss this opportunity to become one of them!</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-family: verdana, sans-serif;">But thats not all! You will be able to explore Sarajevos nightlife, cultural diversity, our delicious food, and the hospitality of our citizens. If you''re still having second thoughts, <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yLk7jgZUxX0" target="_blank">take a look at the atmosphere during eMovie Academy ''11</a>!</span></p>\r\n<span style="font-family: verdana, sans-serif;">We guarantee you a week of unforgettable experiences, education and excitement!</span>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<p dir="ltr"></p>\r\n<span style="font-family: verdana, sans-serif;">Feel free to ask any questions you might have, and dare to join us in this adventure!</span>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-family: verdana, sans-serif;">We are waiting for you!</span></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'eMovie Academy ''13', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '3104-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 23:32:16', '2013-11-21 23:32:16', '', 3104, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3818', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3819, 2, '2013-11-21 23:32:24', '2013-11-21 23:32:24', '<p dir="ltr">Welcome on board to flight 86 to Chalkidiki (<em><a href="https://maps.google.gr/maps?q=poseidi&amp;gbv=2&amp;ie=UTF-8&amp;hl=el&amp;authuser=0" target="_blank">Possidi</a></em>). This is your captain <strong>LC Athens</strong>. We will be cruising at a crazy student altitude where everybody has fun and unforgettable memories at a halara (hint: relaxed, cool) airspeed of reggae rhythm and not only... The weather is clear and sunny and with the tailwind on our side we are expecting a high temperature which will increase as more and more people apply for this <strong>IMW</strong>. If the parties cooperate we should get a great view of the city as we descend... The cabin crew will be coming around to offer you a snack and a drink, and the experience of your lifetime will begin shortly after that. I''ll talk to you again before we reach our destination.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Translation:\r\nYes, ladies and gentlemen you are already on a plane or on a bus (or who knows where else) and you are heading to Possidi where the <em>IMW of Greece Me Up vol.2</em> is going to be held.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Possidi is the camp of the university of Thessaloniki and as you can imagine, it is full of students who want to take a rest after a tough year and have some fun...like you! You will have the chance to enjoy the greek sunny weather, the beach, crazy activities, awesome parties and of course the Greek hospitality.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">The participation fee is 50 without the tent and transportation from Thessaloniki to Possidi and backwards. Concerning transportation to and from Possidi, it will be announced near the deadline, but arriving with your own means of transport is acceptable.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">If you want to be a part of this awesome experience apply now in <a href="https://gmuv2-unof-form.typeform.com/to/ON9pUS" target="_blank">this form</a> in which you can find all the information and the details you may need.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Until then, sit back, halara (hint: relax) and enjoy the rest of the flight.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><strong>P.S.</strong> You can find more information in our site <a href="http://greecemeup.net/" target="_blank">http://greecemeup.net/</a></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><b>Contact mail:</b> Giannis Sotiropoulos (C.P.): <a>js.lcathens@gmail.com</a>\r\nEleni Santorinaiou (H.O.)  : <a>elsantor8@gmail.com</a></p>', 'IMW in Greece 2013', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '3099-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 23:32:24', '2013-11-21 23:32:24', '', 3099, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3819', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3821, 2, '2013-11-21 23:47:01', '2013-11-21 23:47:01', 'Dear EESTECers,\r\n\r\nAre you ready to Cross the Line with LC Podgorica one more time?\r\n\r\nBe prepared, this year there will be more action, more excitement and even more lines to cross! You will experience 7 days of unforgettable atmosphere, EESTEC spirit and memories for a lifetime.\r\n\r\nLC Podgorica is taking you to <b>Kotor</b>, which is situated in Europe''s southernmost <a title="Fjord" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fjord" target="_blank">fjord</a> called - Boka Kotorska (The Bay of Kotor, or Boka Bay). Kotor is one of the most beautiful cities on Montenegrin coast (UNESCO protected) . You will be able to experience Mediterranean spirit, see one of the most beautiful bays in Europe during the cruise that we will organize, and visit Gospa od krpjela (Our Lady of the Rocks) island.\r\n\r\nYou will see <b>Budva</b>, a pearl of Mediterranean, and a <a title="Luxury yacht" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Luxury_yacht" target="_blank">luxury yacht</a> <a title="Marina" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Marina" target="_blank">marina</a> <b>Porto</b> <b>Montenegro</b>. Beside sightseeing and city rally, you will also have a chance to enjoy your stay in Montenegro on beautiful beaches of Budva, Tivat and Kotor and do summer activities with us.\r\n\r\nBut wait, thats not all... The most important thing is the <b>Kotor Carnival</b>, one of the biggest and craziest carnivals in Europe! We are preparing many more surprises that will remain a secret for now... Sooo APPLY !\r\n\r\nThis event will also have an educational part. Considering that you are probably tired of engineering, we decided to make workshops on photography, journalism and filmmaking where you will be able to release your creativity. Summer and sunny days will surely inspire you! Also two EESTEC trainers will give you some innovative and damn interesting trainings, in order to motivate and relax you more and more...\r\n\r\nSo pack up your swimsuits, good mood, EESTEC Spirit and <b>Cross the Line</b> in Montenegro! We are waiting for you!', 'Cross the Line 2', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '3044-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 23:47:01', '2013-11-21 23:47:01', '', 3044, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3821', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3822, 2, '2013-11-21 23:47:41', '2013-11-21 23:47:41', '<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Dear EESTECers,\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">LC Belgrade is proud to announce its first <a href="http://tinyurl.com/cd2zv47" target="_blank">International Motivational Weekend</a>, which will be held from 17th to 19th May! We are bringing the participants of our workshop <strong>World Beyond Tomorrow",</strong> as a conclusion to a great event! The best way to participate at the IMW is to apply for our workshop!</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Prepare yourself to enjoy in the youth camp erdap, located in the tourist region Karata, just in the period in all of its beautiful colors, through the joy of spring! You will have the chance to enjoy in our beautiful countryside, visit Hydroelectric Power Station erdap 1" - the largest and first producer of hydroelectricity in Southeast Europe, take part in many fun activities like the games without limits, indoor soccer tournaments, beach volleyball, beer pong in the evening, have great fun at the parties and a lot of other funny things!</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">The participation fee is <strong>55</strong>, which includes return journey from Belgrade to Karata, accommodation, 3 meals a day, drinks and free theme parties. At the IMW we will be accompanied by members of association <i>ESTIEM LG Belgrade</i>, so we definitely need all of you to join us and show them our EESTEC spirit! Also, you can ask us to book a room for you at the hostel in Belgrade, if you want to stay few more days.</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Our bus will leave Belgrade at 09:00 am on Friday and back from the location on a Sunday afternoon.</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">We promise you won''t regret it! <a href="http://eestec.net/lc/belgrade/imw-belgrade-2013" target="_blank">See you in Serbia</a>!</span></p>', 'IMW Belgrade 2013', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2910-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 23:47:41', '2013-11-21 23:47:41', '', 2910, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3822', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3823, 2, '2013-11-21 23:47:55', '2013-11-21 23:47:55', '<div id="parent-fieldname-text">\r\n\r\nDear EESTECers,\r\n\r\nWere proud to announce the second edition of a workshop entitled Smart Energy for a Better World, in cooperation with ABB Corporate Research Centre, which will be held in Krakow from 7th till 13th of July 2013.\r\n\r\nThis study tour is dedicated to students, who want to learn about modern solutions in the field of energy, automation and electrical science. The event will be a unique opportunity to visit one of the most advanced ABB Research Centers in the world and to broaden your knowledge on:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Advanced numerical simulations</li>\r\n	<li>Power electronics</li>\r\n	<li>Transients phenomena</li>\r\n	<li>Smart Protection</li>\r\n	<li>Advanced diagnostics</li>\r\n	<li>Ferroresonance phenomena</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nAll students from European Universities are invited to join us in Krakow, one of Poland''s most renown cities. This event will be a great occasion to meet experts on energy, electrical sciences and to visit Poland''s well-known tourist attractions.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWe are waiting for applications from students who have:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>electrical engineering profile</li>\r\n	<li>good academic results</li>\r\n	<li>good command of English</li>\r\n	<li>completed at least 3 years of university education</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nMore information about the lectures and lab excercises can be found on the website of the event<a href="http://smart.eestec.pl/" target="_blank">here</a>.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nFeel the EESTEC Spirit and join us in Krakw. See with your own eyes the beauty one of the biggest city in Poland with its historicial treasures and vivid nightlife. Youve got an unusual opportunity to visit i.a.:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>the Wawel Royal Castle - located at the Vistula River the residence of Polish kings and queens;</li>\r\n	<li>the Underground of the Citys Main Market Square  unusual place created by modern technology with the exhibition of the monuments from the Middle Ages;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nWe will go on a tour to Kryspinw lake, barbecue at the biggest student campus in Poland or have a bowling night. We wont reveal all of the spicy attractions weve prepared. We can say youll certainly experience the amazing nightlife and many other activities so you wont get chance to get bored. Apply now or regret through the lifetime.\r\n\r\nHow to apply:\r\n\r\n1. EESTEC members: via eestec.net, where you should write down your motivational letter and send your CV to<a href="mailto:krakow@eestec.net">krakow@eestec.net</a>\r\n\r\n2. Non-EESTECers: via website:<a href="http://smart.eestec.pl/" target="_blank">smart.eestec.pl</a>\r\n\r\nWere waiting for You in Krakow! ;)\r\n<div></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<a id="parent-fieldname-eventUrl" href="http://smart.eestec.pl/" target="_blank">More information about this event</a>', 'Smart Energy for a Better World 2', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2673-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 23:47:55', '2013-11-21 23:47:55', '', 2673, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3823', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3824, 2, '2013-11-21 23:48:10', '2013-11-21 23:48:10', 'DearEESTECers,\r\n\r\nWe, LC Delft, are proud to announce our next workshop Tie Another Day  A challange from Mars,\r\n\r\nFirst of all, welcome to the<strong>Mars rover project</strong>! In this powerful workshop we give you a directive to design a complex system. We have taken a top-down approach. This way you can understand the operation of the increasingly larger parts within the whole system.\r\n\r\nIn the first part of the workshop you will design a mobile robot (the Mars Rover) in a group of students. This robot has to be able to search for a line and then track the line and take turns. Some<strong>additional intelligence</strong>has to be added as well. The design steps are not only useful for this workshop, but also for complex systems in general. First you focus at the problem as a whole, and then the problem is divided into even smaller parts which are then implemented. This is the so-called top-down approach.\r\n\r\nIn the design you have to deal with operation and readout of input signals (sensors), output actuators the motors) and a controller. The robot is programmed in VHDL. VHDL is a Hardware Description Language (HDL), a language which is used to help design digital circuits.\r\n\r\nIn order to test the Mars Rover,<strong>a complex maze</strong>is available. Your Mars Rover has to find the way out as fast as possible. As an added challenge, the maze contains instructions for the Mars Rover for making sharp turns that allows a faster traversal of the maze.\r\n\r\nThe second part of the workshop focuses on the<strong>power supply of the Mars Rover</strong>. In the first part of the workshop, the robot will use batteries as its power supply. If the batteries run out of power, you can easily replace them. However, on Mars this would pose a problem. In order to be able to use the Mars rover for an extended amount of time, an alternative energy source is needed. On Mars it is possible to use solar energy to power the Mars rover. In the second part of the workshop you will examine a solar cell and design additional circuits in order to use the solar energy as the power supply of the Mars rover.\r\n\r\nObvious this is not everything in the weekend and at every evening there will be time to explore other things like Delft and The Netherlands. So dont hesitate and apply before Friday the 19<sup>th</sup>of april.\r\n\r\nFor Questions dont hesitate to contact<a href="mailto:cp@etv.tudelft.nl">cp@etv.tudelft.nl</a> for further questions.', 'Tie Another Day - A Challenge from Mars', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2670-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 23:48:10', '2013-11-21 23:48:10', '', 2670, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3824', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3825, 2, '2013-11-21 23:48:21', '2013-11-21 23:48:21', '<div>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><b><i>Hello dear friends, students and other members of NGOs!</i></b></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><b><i>LeadershipSummer School is coming!</i></b></span>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><b><i>Do you want to inspire people? Do you have plans to lead a project in your NGO? Do you think that the word leader describes you?</i></b></span>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><b><i>Interested? </i></b></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><b><i>Apply to LSS`13.</i></b></span>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<b><i><span style="color: #000000;">Our project will help you discover your potential!</span></i></b>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><b><i>Together we can change the world!</i></b></span>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<span style="color: #000000;">==============================<wbr />==========================\r\n</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><b>==What is LSS?===</b></span>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;">The Leadership Summer Schoolis an intensive learning event and a networking platform, aimingat increasing skills and readiness of youth NGO leaders, sharing best practices and improving leadership skills among prominent members of each participating organisation.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"></span>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><b>===What are we looking for?===</b></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;">We are looking for<b>70 highly motivated and active students and youth</b>who will participate to a challenging learning event.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><b>===When and Where?===</b></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;">Sofia (Bulgaria)<i>f</i></span>rom<b>21st till 30th of July 2013</b>\r\n\r\n<img alt="Inline images 2" src="https://mail.google.com/mail/u/0/?ui=2&amp;ik=6c33839bd5&amp;view=att&amp;th=13dad4cf0ee7a16d&amp;attid=0.1&amp;disp=emb&amp;realattid=ii_13dad39a8865b14e&amp;zw&amp;atsh=1" width="420" height="310" />\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><b>===What about the fee?===</b></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;">The fee will be<b>190 EUR</b>whichincludes:\r\n</span>- accommodation;\r\n- food (3 meals per day + coffee breaks);\r\n- transport for LSS activities;\r\n- and some social activities.\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;">If selected to participate in the event, it will be requested from you to pay 50% of the fee (95 EUR) as participation confirmation: this amount is<i><b>not refundable</b></i>. The rest can be paid anticipatively or at the event itself. More details will be communicated at that moment.</span>\r\n\r\n<i><span style="color: #000000;">We are not able to provide scholarship or any form of discount.</span></i>\r\n\r\n<i><span style="color: #000000;"></span></i>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<b><span style="color: #000000;">===How to apply?===</span></b>\r\n\r\n<b><span style="color: #000000;"></span></b>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;">Fill the<a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1zqu6fpLsWGk9QtI5Ln72Pzlx2BWv9xWiEF6Ha19Qn2A/viewform" target="_blank">LSS 2013 Application form</a>.</span>\r\n<div><span style="color: #000000;"></span></div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div dir="ltr">\r\n<div><i><b>Deadline to apply: April 14th 23:59 CET</b></i></div>\r\n<b><span style="color: #000000;">===And now ===</span></b>\r\nWe are looking forward to reading your applications and if you have any questions or suggestions, feel free to contact us by mail:<a href="mailto:contact@leadershipsummerschool.org" target="_blank">contact@<wbr />leadershipsummerschool.org</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'Leadership Summer School 2013', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2664-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 23:48:21', '2013-11-21 23:48:21', '', 2664, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3825', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3826, 2, '2013-11-21 23:48:45', '2013-11-21 23:48:45', '<div id="parent-fieldname-text">\r\n\r\nDear EESTECers,\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWe are proud to announce our next workshop. After a long tradition of successful workshops, we are still trying to do better and improve our offer! This time we will amuse you with a workshop related to Green and Eco Friendly Technologies.\r\nFuture Technologies are coming to be more and more green. Our lectures will deal with Green Computing technologies, having a deep practical insight: we will have the honor to host some successful StartUp in this field, that will explain how it works in real life.\r\n\r\nGreen Economy is the new challenge, and we are ready to catch it!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nMoreover this year there will be an exclusive news! Our workshop will be held in collaboration with ESTIEM Association (European Students of Industrial Engineering and Management). Green supply chain will be the other topic that you will have the opportunity do deal with.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nIt means a double opportunity to meet and melt with Students from all Europe!!!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAcademics activity will be just a short (but heaped) bracket in your experience here in Cosenza.\r\nCosenza is the biggest Campus in the South of Italy. A neighborhood made up exclusively of 2000 Students and 200 Erasmus Students, offers one of the most brave and challenging night life! <strong>Get ready for it!!!</strong>\r\n\r\nYou will have also the opportunity to visit the most stunning and breathtaking landscapes of our land! The land of the sun, the sea and the good food! All this delved in a rich cultural background ( don''t forget that Pitagora was born in Calabria ;) ).\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nCalabria is waiting for you, see you there!!! :D\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nPS: We will provide you a detailed programme as soon as possible.\r\n\r\n</div>', 'GECO (Green Engineering COmputing)', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2652-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 23:48:45', '2013-11-21 23:48:45', '', 2652, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3826', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3827, 2, '2013-11-21 23:49:36', '2013-11-21 23:49:36', '<div>Dear EESTECers,</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>All of you probably remember one of the most known Latin phrases: "Historia est Magistra Vitae" :) We sure do and we are proud to announce our workshop which pretty much bases on this phrase. If you apply for Back in Time we can promise you wont regret it.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>Have you ever wondered how stuff worked before almost everything went digital and computer controlled? All those interesting and smart solutions everyone has forgotten about? In Zagreb you will have a chance to get familiar with them. Old principles of automatics, programming, power engineering and wireless technology can always come in handy to todays modern engineers. We will make comparisons between old and new, and make conclusions with pros and cons for each individual technology/solution/approach.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>Now lets get to the more interesting part of the workshop  our beautiful city of Zagreb. You will get in touch with every part of Croatian culture and have an opportunity to taste our delicious cousin and our inspiring drinks. Also, you will get a chance to enjoy our beautiful Adriatic coast and our crystal clear sea ;)</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>Our museums are going to give you a very good insight into our culture and you will spend time exploring Zagreb in a really interesting way. We will make sure you have enough time to enjoy the city and relax.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>And the most important part  youll attend the most awesome parties in Zagreb and we can assure you that you will remember them for your life.</div>\r\n<div>So, dont hesitate to apply to our super duper workshop! We promise you good time :)</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>If you have any questions or need more convincing just contact us.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>With love from LC Zagreb &lt;3</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div><span style="color: #222222; font-family: arial,sans-serif;"><span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #888888;"><br clear="all" /> </span></span></span></div>\r\n<iframe src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/Xsz49mzCVg0" height="315" width="560" allowfullscreen="" frameborder="0"></iframe>', 'Back in Time', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2650-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 23:49:36', '2013-11-21 23:49:36', '', 2650, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3827', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3828, 2, '2013-11-21 23:50:10', '2013-11-21 23:50:10', 'Greetings from The North.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nEverything today is driven by computers, bigger or smaller ones. Almost everything that has any kind of electronics includes a computing unit also. So what are these, why they make so complex things work? We try to find this answer for you as we open the world of digital technology for you.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAND SO! We proudly announce our new workshop"Workshop of 41:73:73:65:6d:62:6c:79". Our fellows at computer techlab are more than welcoming to take you for a tour in the world of computing with ones and zeros.<b></b>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nFor one week our LC is happy to host you to enjoy our beautiful city of Tampere, the northernmost LC in eestec. If you think this is going to be one of those easier workshops where you can sleep between lectures then youre gravely mistaken. We indeed take our education seriously but we take our parties even more seriously. In one week we will introduce you to the whole new world of sauna, singing, Finnish culture, city life of small town and the right Finnish way of doing things wrong.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSo, everyone who has any interest in digital designs, embedded systems, computers or just generally is trying to find something interesting to study, we openly welcome you.\r\n\r\nWed really appreciate those applications that have some information about what you generally study and what you know about digital designs and computer technologies as our professor may want people to have some degree of knowledge about the area.', 'Workshop of 41:73:73:65:6d:62:6c:79', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2488-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 23:50:10', '2013-11-21 23:50:10', '', 2488, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3828', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0);
