(3829, 2, '2013-11-21 23:50:30', '2013-11-21 23:50:30', 'Hey Everyone!\r\n\r\nGreetings from the island where Aphrodite born, where Shakspeares Othello Castle is, where the one of the longest beach of world, where the place that caretta carettas choose to live, and where the place of our workshop that we are inviting you,\r\n\r\nLadies (and maybe Gentlemen!)\r\n\r\nSunnydays by LC Famagusta : )\r\n\r\nAll came from the stars, they said, and we came from our star, the Sun. Now, we have the technology to produce energy that our civilization desperately needs. So, the workshop Sunnydays is all about that. We got seminars and lectures about solar energy and also a visit to recently built photovoltaic power station.\r\n\r\nWhen it comes to entertainment, we got some hot plans for you. The spring festival of our university will take place at same time with this event so the city will never sleep ! We are inviting you over to share the great fun in our tropical campus with more than 15000 students including people from 68 different countries. Yacht Party, City Rally, Windsurfing, Karaoke Parties, Discos, Sea, Sun, Beach Parties, Beaches and Beaches what else do you need?\r\n\r\nSo prepare your swimming suits and apply !\r\n\r\nPlease dont hesitate if you have questions. We will be more than glad to answer them .', 'SunnyDays', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2216-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 23:50:30', '2013-11-21 23:50:30', '', 2216, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3829', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3830, 2, '2013-11-21 23:52:43', '2013-11-21 23:52:43', 'Prepare every single cell in your body, cause you are going to become time traveller in Belgrade, and we will give our best to be great companions in this journey. We''re happy to announce that this May you could be the part of "World Beyond Tomorrow".\r\n\r\nGuiding you through a regular family day, twenty years from now, lecturers will introduce you with new necessary technologies. Familiar with all the details and needed knowledge about 4G, hologram, must-have robots, and all innovations that strive to become a part of our everyday life, the future will seem like the present to you. In cooperation with ESTIEM, the organisation for European Students of Industrial Engineering and Management, we will show you admirable landscapes of our country and the way we define word<a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=--c03roM4nI" target="_blank">party</a>. So, you will also have the opportunity to meet with members of their event which would be held side-by-side with our workshop.\r\n\r\nAfter a long time, we decided to show you the<a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_Zu_tkk9be0" target="_blank">White city</a>in the period when you can see it in all of its beautiful colors, through the joy of spring. Ada Ciganlija, oasis of nature in the busy city life, is waiting for you, as well as Kalemegdan, Skadarlija, Nikola Tesla Museum, Knez Mihailova street... You will have the chance to enjoy traditional<a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wIwNwZwNXuA" target="_blank">Serbian cuisine</a>, gibanica, ajvar, pljeskavica and of course rakija.\r\n\r\nApply now, and enjoy in knowledge and party time warp! :)\r\n\r\nSee you in Serbia,\r\nAnita Jovi.', 'World Beyond Tomorrow', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2562-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 23:52:43', '2013-11-21 23:52:43', '', 2562, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3830', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3831, 2, '2013-11-21 23:57:13', '2013-11-21 23:57:13', 'Dear EESTECers,\r\n\r\nThis May, Madrid will be the place to be. We proudly present our yearly workshop, with a brand new name: <b>Going Green!</b>, based in the challenging field of Green Technology.\r\n<p align="JUSTIFY">We live in a society with a higher demand of energy. This increasing necessity has become a real problem, directly affecting our environment and natural resources. Accordingly, it is not a surprise that companies have started pursuing a maintainable productive model and investing part of their incomes in this new Green Technology. However, what is then Green Technology? Just the application of technology and echo sciences to the preservation of our ecosystem. Green technology is a field of new, innovative ways to make changes in daily life. Currently, this Clean Technology is in the beginning stages of its development, so the future will only bring bigger and better things.</p>\r\nUnder this green theme, lectures will deepen into the subjects of energetic efficiency, sustainable development or echo-friendly buildings. Furthermore, the week will be completed with visits to some of our University laboratories, other companies researching centers and even real examples of sustainable houses. So, <b>from 5th to 12th of May </b>participants will have the chance to enlarge both their theoretical and practical knowledge in the matter.\r\n\r\nBut wait, there is more. We dont forget about our city, Madrid, and its major and minor secrets. During afternoons, history, through monuments and buildings, will be revealed before our eyes, while nights will be dedicated to explore the meaning of fiesta. The capital of Spain is known for its never-sleeping life, and we will invite you to discover it with us (would you be willing to try your own limits? <img class="wp-smiley" alt=";)" src="http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" /> ).\r\n\r\nTo end the event with the best sensation, we prepared a special weekend in the countryside. Two days, lost in the rural area of a near mountain. Time to relax, time to nature and, again, time to party. What else can you ask for ??\r\n\r\nPerhaps we could add some of our Spanish spirit to the mixture  Drinking sangra or eating tortilla and jamn, along with our natural cheerful attitude will bring you closer to our lively culture. Dont hesitate and apply <img class="wp-smiley" alt=":D" src="http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif" /> , you have till <b>24th of March </b>to make up your mind\r\n\r\nFinally, as we always sayWe are so sorry to have to say this, every year we have to make great efforts to find sponsors for our events, and although last years were faultless <img class="wp-smiley" alt=";)" src="http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" /> , we expect an exemplary attitude from all of you and we friendly ask you for cooperation and comprehension. Irresponsible attitudes wont be tolerated and in case it happens, participants will be warned and eventually expelled from the event if warnings are disregarded.\r\n\r\nWhen it is time to party, we party (and trust me, we will! ;D), but when its time to work, we must work (and later we have party! ^^).\r\n\r\nYou dont wanna miss this!!!\r\n\r\nHope to see you all in Madrid!\r\n\r\n<b>Follow us</b><b>:<a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.eestec.es'']);" href="http://www.eestec.es/" target="_blank">Website</a>,<a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.facebook.com'']);" href="http://www.facebook.com/#%21/pages/Eestec-Eurielec/115934218476771" target="_blank">Facebook</a></b>and<b><a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://twitter.com'']);" href="https://twitter.com/#%21/eestecLCMadrid" target="_blank">Twit<wbr />ter</a></b>', 'Going Green! Engineer your future', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2219-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 23:57:13', '2013-11-21 23:57:13', '', 2219, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3831', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3832, 2, '2013-11-21 23:57:51', '2013-11-21 23:57:51', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>After a very successful last year&#8217;s exchange we decided to go further and create an even more memorable event for you. This time we did our best to enable more of you to come &#8211; we hope for 18enthusiastic EESTECers to visit us and spend the<a href="http://youtu.be/opqZAXJ4t0o" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://youtu.be'']);" target="_blank">best week</a>of spring 2013 in the city with a largest student community in Poland  which of course means the greatest students traditions. It is our pleasure to announce that Krakows gates are opening for you again!</p>\n<p>You will experience living in the biggest students campus in Poland -<a href="http://youtu.be/SiMHTK15Pik" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://youtu.be'']);" target="_blank">its over 9000</a>people! Besides, we will present to you the<b>most important parts of Krakow</b>and a bit of<b>Polish history</b>.</p>\n<p>Since there is only a small academic part planned, you will have plenty of time to relax and recharge your batteries for the rest of semester. However, we prefer active leisure time, so prepare for an<b>intensive week</b>. There will be no opportunity to get bored! We have an awesome programme for you, including a bike tour ending with an open-air beer-tasting evening, a legendary lasertag competition and many, many more&#8230;!</p>\n<p>Wait, have we mentioned the parties? Believe us, no two nights are going to be the same. We prepared a variety of night-time activities for you: outdoors, student-only clubs, theme parties  whatever you can think of <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif'' alt='';)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n<p>But more to that! If this is not enough for you, at the end of the week we will<a href="http://youtu.be/432iaBjdgjI" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://youtu.be'']);" target="_blank">travel to Zakopane</a> abeautiful city at the foot of Tatra Mountains,known as &#8220;the winter capital ofPoland&#8221;and also acenter of Gorals culture.There, you will have a chance to enjoy the beauty of the highest Polish mountains and local folklore.</p>\n<p>We promise amazing atmosphere with EESTEC Spirit, great company and many surprises! <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif'' alt='';)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n<p>Curious about how student life should be like? <a href="http://eestec.net/lc/krakow/charge-up-in-krakow-2013-spring-exchange-2013" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://eestec.net'']);" target="_blank">Apply now!</a><br />\n<b>CU in Krakow</b></p>\n<p><i>NOTE: When booking tickets, please keep in mind that we will be back in Krakow (from Zakopane) on Sunday at noon. If you intend to go to EESTEC Congress afterwards, there is a cheap connection (from 50 ) with Munich by variety of transport means. We can help with arranging additional nights and buying tickets.<br />\n</i></p>\n', 'Charge Up in Krakow  Spring Exchange 2013', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2218-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 23:57:51', '2013-11-21 23:57:51', '', 2218, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3832', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3833, 2, '2013-11-21 23:58:06', '2013-11-21 23:58:06', '\n<div></div>\n<p>Dear EESTECers,The wait is over! RoboMAC has been announced&#8230; and this years edition of the annual robotics competition carries the much creative title: RoboMAC 2013.</p>\n<p>RoboMac 2012 was quite&#8230; well&#8230; an absolutely awesome event! Building robots and having good time &#8211; perfect recipe for one of the best weeks of my life. Thank you, dear Organizers! &#8211; Daniel Materowski</p>\n<p>If you&#8217;re brave enough to click &#8220;the button&#8221; and apply, your skills and knowledge will be tested in different categories depending on your interest. If you are ready to enter a week full with hi-tech stuff: flying quadcopters, intelligent vehicles, walking humanoids, and not so mobile participants you know where is the flashy button we&#8217;re talking about.During this awesome week we will gradually introduce you into the world of robotics, up from the basis to the very next frontier of this field. At the end of the week the teams will have the chance to stand against each other and compete with their creations in front of an demanding audience.<br />\nBest week ever. Legendary. &#8211; Ismail Morgenegg</p>\n<p>Ahh and the non-academic part&#8230; The crew at our LC as always, are here well prepared<br />\nfor introducing you to the <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?feature=player_embedded&amp;v=ju0lU9fzEsE" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.youtube.com'']);" target="_blank">beauties of Skopje,</a> introducing to <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?feature=player_embedded&amp;v=CRgLmCQzEAo" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.youtube.com'']);" target="_blank">our cuisine</a> and showing you everything that Skopje has to offer, imagination is yours!<br />\nVisit <a href="http://eestec.net/lc/skopje/robomac-2013-1" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://eestec.net'']);" target="_blank">http://eestec.net/lc/skopje/robomac-2013-1</a> to apply now!</p>\n', 'RoboMAC 2013', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2220-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 23:58:06', '2013-11-21 23:58:06', '', 2220, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3833', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3834, 2, '2013-11-21 23:58:31', '2013-11-21 23:58:31', '<div id="parent-fieldname-text">\r\n\r\nDear EESTECers,\r\n\r\nLC Tuzla proudly presents our newest workshop!\r\n\r\nMicrocontrollers? Sounds familiar, right?\r\nIf not yet, then at some point during your studies you will get a chance to work with one. Later on theres a huge chance you might even get to play with one at your office.\r\n\r\nThe application of microcontrollers in order to improve the efficiency of energy systems is something new. That is why EESTEC LC Tuzla decided to organize a workshop on Rapid Instrumentation for Customized Energy Efficient Systems.\r\nDont worry, you will not spend all of your time listening to lectures. We have provided brand new microcontrollers just for you to play with in the laboratory.\r\nThe knowledge you will gain will, with no doubts, ensure you the ticket to enter the big world of microcontrollers.\r\n\r\nSo are you ready to explore Energy Efficient Systems TEChnology, or as we like to call it EESTEChnology?\r\nNot yet?\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWell good, because we havent told you everything.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nLC Tuzla has prepared a truly unique experience for you. If you want to enjoy the famous Bosnian atmosphere, an elegant blend of traditional and modern, East and West, then the Salt city is the right place to visit. Just imagine, you are sitting on the shores of the Pannonian lake, the only salt lake in Europe, looking at the mosque and church standing next to each other in the background while the nice sound of traditional Bosnian music comes to your ears.\r\nYes, we have so much salt that we made salt lakes. You will learn all about it while visiting the Salt factory and Museum of Salt.\r\nBeing tired from lectures and the city atmosphere you will also have a chance to spend one day in pure nature, at the famous tourist resort near our city, Zlaca.\r\n\r\nLast, but not least and perhaps most important  Bosnian cuisine! All of the evapi, pie and dolma lovers will come to the right place. Those who arent yet will definitely become one after this trip.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nDo you need more reasons to come, learn and have fun with us?\r\n\r\nLC Tuzla is waiting for you.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nHave a look at these videos about Tuzla and Bosnia and Herzegovina:\r\n\r\n<a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.youtube.com'']);" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EPtjxx1ht5Y" target="_blank">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EPtjxx1ht5Y</a>\r\n<a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.youtube.com'']);" href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rinQSOVUvrU" target="_blank">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rinQSOVUvrU</a>\r\n\r\n</div>', 'EESTEChnology', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2221-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 23:58:31', '2013-11-21 23:58:31', '', 2221, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3834', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3835, 2, '2013-11-21 23:59:01', '2013-11-21 23:59:01', '<div id="parent-fieldname-text">\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nDear EESTECers,\r\n\r\nWe are very glad to officially announceCongress2013registration period. From now and till 5th of March all LCs, JLCs and Observers have a chance to register their representative forCongresswhich will take place from 23rd till 30th of April in Munich, Germany.\r\nEach LC,JLCand Observer have a right for at least one place onCongress. If you do not register your representative till the deadline, Int. Board will assign place for your LC toBAs, Trainers, IT members and other international teams.\r\n\r\nPlease do not miss the deadline5th of March for your registration!\r\n<strong>What kind of participants are expected at theCongress?</strong>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\nIts totally up to the LC/JLC/Observer to decide who you want to send onCongressas your official representatives. Representatives should be experienced, familiar with EESTEC structure and ready to participate actively on Congress.\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<strong>What do we expect from participants duringCongress?</strong>\r\n\r\nWe expect thatevery LC has at least one representative during every General Assembly (GA) sessions. It isinexcusable to miss any GA since we are going to have discussion on very important topics for EESTEC such as:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>EESTEC projects</li>\r\n	<li>Board and Bodies report</li>\r\n	<li>Promotion and degradation of LCs and JLCs</li>\r\n	<li>RoPchanging</li>\r\n	<li>Election of the new International Board and Bodies</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>What you should do besides the registration on eestec.net:</strong>\r\n\r\nTo select and manage the applicants we kindly ask you to fill in the following form after you have applied on EESTEC.net. If you do not, your application wont be considered as valid.\r\n\r\n<a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://docs.google.com'']);" href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheet/viewform?formkey=dDhXREFYUW1jWi12RElld2hqMjNaV3c6MA#gid=0" target="_blank">EESTEC Congress Munich  Application Info</a>\r\n\r\nFurthermore, please fill in another form with which we collect information about the universities to be represented on the Open Day. Please do this task as soon as possible, since we need the information for printing them on the Open Day booklet.\r\n\r\n<a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://docs.google.com'']);" href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheet/viewform?formkey=dFJhTkItTFBtMS1CWW5uNGM0VzN1LXc6MQ#gid=0" target="_blank">Open Day  University Facts</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThis year we will also have Open Day as part ofCongress2013.Open Day can be counted as a fair where there are booths for participating companies, universities, EESTEC local committees and international Board, and every representative are free to visit each others booths for information exchange about any idea or opportunity. You can check how OpenDay looked like on previous Congress<a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.youtube.com'']);" href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9Y69aQeeHcg" target="_blank">here</a>.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>What do you need to bring for Open Day?</strong>\r\n\r\nEvery LC representative should bring onCongress:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Informational materials of your University-Faculty (this is most important)</li>\r\n	<li>Informational materials of your LC (also very important)</li>\r\n	<li>Promo materials of your LCactivities (posters, flyers, bookmarks)</li>\r\n	<li>LC flag (only if you have one, dont need to make if you dont have)</li>\r\n	<li>Prepare nformational (at least 1 page) documents or presentation/slides which includes:</li>\r\n	<li>Your recruitment Strategy (how you get new members every year)</li>\r\n	<li>What makes your LC successful?(yoursuccessfulprojects, activities)</li>\r\n	<li>How you keep motivations of your members? (motivation strategies, tips andtricks)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div><em><strong>To sum up and again the most important, dont miss deadline for registration,</strong></em><strong>5th of March,</strong><em><strong>since after that deadline, International Board will give your places to Bodies.</strong></em>Waiting for your registration,</div>\r\nEESTEC International Board and LC Munich\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nFor questions please contact:\r\n\r\nCongress-CP: Wataru Oshima, coc2013munich(at)gmail.com\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nInformation about unofficial participation will be sent in the next days.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<a id="parent-fieldname-eventUrl" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://congress.eestec.net'']);" href="http://congress.eestec.net" target="_blank"> More information about this event</a>', 'EESTEC Congress 2013', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2222-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 23:59:01', '2013-11-21 23:59:01', '', 2222, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3835', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3836, 2, '2013-11-21 23:59:12', '2013-11-21 23:59:12', 'Dear EESTECers,\r\n\r\nLC Munich is honored to present you the sequel of our<em>Women in Engineering </em>workshop from<strong>April 23rd</strong>until<strong>April 30th</strong>. As always, the event goes hand in hand with a second event which will be the EESTEC Congress 2013!\r\n\r\nOur department for Gender Studies will give an interactive four day seminar. Female students will learn how to use their voice, express themselves and prove themselves in a working environment. It is a fact that women earn less money, are treated worse and hold less important positions in a company. Often, these facts lead to prejudice against women and they dont even try to stand up for themselves, seeing that it is just as it is. So all you girls, use your voice and<em>Speak Up!</em>Our seminar will show you how to grasp opportunities and broaden your prospects for your future working life. Besides, together with all the participants you should work out<em>your</em>personal road to success.\r\n\r\nFurthermore, there will be a womens contact forum during where youll have the opportunity to interact and exchange experiences with other women working in engineering jobs. On April 25th, you will get the chance to join the EESTEC OpenDay where you can establish contacts with representatives of companies or other sponsors and foreign universities.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nApart from the lectures, we will introduce you to the lovely Bavarian capital, Munich. We look forward to showing you our Bavarian culture, Munich nightlife and our charming hospitality. The workshop will take place during the weeks of<em>spring festival</em>which is the little sister of our Oktoberfest and, of course, we dont want you to miss this event either!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nDo not hestitate and apply now! LC Awesome is waiting for you!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Note:</strong> <em>Evening activities are together with the Congress participants and you will also get the chance to get a glimpse on the Congress, nevertheless your main focus should be this workshop. This is an Exclusive Workshop and to ensure your motivation, we are taking into account your motivational letter. Following criterias will be assessed: Motivation, Progress of Studies, Level of English. The letter should consist of 500 to 1000 words.</em>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<em>For question regarding WiE please contact andreas.albrecht(at)<a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://fs.ei.tum.de'']);" href="http://fs.ei.tum.de" target="_blank">fs.ei.tum.<wbr />de</a>. </em>', 'Women in Engineering 2013', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2223-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 23:59:12', '2013-11-21 23:59:12', '', 2223, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3836', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3837, 2, '2013-11-21 23:59:50', '2013-11-21 23:59:50', '<ul>\r\n	<li><span><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">2 spoons of creativity,</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">1 cup of teamwork,</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">1 teaspoon of technology,</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">2 bottles of fun,</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">15 spirits of EESTECers</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Preheat your processors to 60-80 degrees C (140-176 degrees F). Lightly bend your screen for perfect sight. Open up some space in your hard disk.</span></span><span><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">\r\n</span></span><span><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Separate EESTECers into teams.</span></span><span><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">\r\n</span></span><span><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Load technology to the memory. Mix creativity, teamwork and fun. Bake in preheated processor for one week. Finally add some cheat.</span></span><span><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">\r\n</span></span><span><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Enjoy your game!</span></span>\r\n\r\n<span><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">You have the recipe, you have the spirit. Just heat up your processors and mix up to the new workshop of LC Eskisehir! Our event, Just Cheat It, will be held between 16th  23th March.</span></span><span><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">\r\n</span></span><span><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Subject of the event is video game development (especially mobile ones). You will be trained to obtain the necessary knowledge to make a mobile game from scratch. Lectures will cover both theoretical and practical parts of video game development. After the basics of game design is introduced theoretically, game programming using Unity3d game engine will be experienced practically.</span></span>\r\n\r\n<span><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">We will group you into teams to build your games, some art students from Anadolu University will also join to the teams in this phase. Then you will have time to develop your games in a relaxed development environment.</span></span>\r\n\r\n<span><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">While you are building your games in days, evenings are going to have awesome parties and activities to refresh you! Traditional EESTEC events like multi-culture night and city rally are planned for you to feel the spirit. As you will taste well-known Turkish tastes (rak, baklava, kebab, Turkish delight) from its source, you will also reveal some more tastes which may still be secret to you like tantuni, simit, knefe</span></span>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<span><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">If you want to have an highly productive week full of fun and EESTEC spirit, you are invited to Eskiehir!</span></span>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<span><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Oh and please dont forget to mention about your programming background in your application, its not strict but a basic knowledge in programming is preferable.</span></span>', 'Just Cheat It', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2224-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 23:59:50', '2013-11-21 23:59:50', '', 2224, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3837', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3838, 2, '2013-11-22 00:02:09', '2013-11-22 00:02:09', '\n<div id="parent-fieldname-text">\n<p>Dear EESTECers<br />\nHave you ever wondered what Switzerland looks like? Have you ever wanted to experience the fascinating contrast between a busy banking hot spot and the calmness of the mountains not even an hour away from Zurich but don&#8217;t have the time to come here for the whole week? Or just looking for an amazing place to spend some time before the congress and get some good chocolate? EESTEC LC Zrich hereby invites you to its first international motivational weekend in the Swiss mountains!<br />\nArrivals will be on Thursday, so you will experience our legendary<strong> tramparty</strong> with the participants of our simultaneously happening workshop. On Friday, we will move to the mountains and have some <strong>fun activities</strong> and a <strong>Swiss night </strong>just to break the mountain night&#8217;s silence with a<strong> LC Zurich style surprise party</strong>. The next day you will also spend with lots of fun program, good food and finish the weekend with the <strong>amazing farewell party! </strong>Unforgettable moments are guaranteed!<br />\nAfter featuring the motivational weekend in our workshop last year for the first time, we decided to open it up to all of EESTEC. Why? Because you guys are just amazing and we want you to party with us! As travelling in Switzerland is pretty expensive, the participation fee will be relatively high. So this year, we have a strongly limited number of participation spots to evaluate the interest in an international motivational weekend in Zurich. In case of success (which we are convinced of) we will organize the weekend next year in a much bigger scale. So, use this unique chance and apply, apply, APPLY! With your participation you will be part of the kick start to a whole new amazing EESTEC tradition!<br />\n<strong>The costs for the weekend will be published soon!</strong> We figure on around 120-150 Euros all incl.<br />\nSee ya soon in Zurich!<br />\n<em>PS: If needed, we will be able to accommodate you until the start of congress and organize your travel there (Munich is just about a 3 hour trip from Zurich).</em></p>\n</div>\n', 'IMW Zurich 2013', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2226-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:02:09', '2013-11-22 00:02:09', '', 2226, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3838', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3839, 2, '2013-11-22 00:02:29', '2013-11-22 00:02:29', 'Dear EESTECers\r\n\r\nNot too long ago, LC Zrich hosted an amazing pack of EESTECers to rebuild the famous smartphone game Angry Birds in real life. This made us put ourselves under a lot of pressure to make this years workshop even more memorable. After an intense decision making process, we are proud to announce the topic of our next workshop:\r\nIn<strong>Slot Engines Xtreme</strong>you will take a close look at the small but fascinating world of slot cars. In this workshop you will compete in small teams to<strong>build the fastest slot car</strong>. Slot cars? Well, were sure you were as fascinated by those mini racing cars  built by companies like Carrera  that went from 0 to infinite speed on a push of a button as we were  and still are!\r\n\r\nOf course, this comes with a nice package of<strong>racing performance and electrical engine theory</strong>. So you will not only have the chance to show off your creativity but also your engineering talent. How? You will spend most of your time building your own small electrical engine  the centerpiece of your mini racing car.\r\nIn the end, we will<strong>test your cars at their limit on a big public racing track</strong>. May the best engineers win!\r\n\r\nOf course, thats not it  by far! As much as we appreciate a great academical part in our workshop were also known for some of the<strong>finest cultural activities in EESTEC</strong>. We dont want to reveal the whole program already but here are some of the higlights:\r\n\r\nFor the first time ever, we will attend the<strong>Schsilte</strong>in Zurich. Its a spring tradition that, in todays form, dates back to 1902. After a beautiful parade of the guilds of Zrich, the Bgg, a huge snowman spiked with firecrackers, will be burned on a huge bonfire. It is said that the time that passes from the start of the fire until the explosion of the Bggs head determines the weather of the summer\r\n\r\nOther cultural activities include clubbing, our amazing city rally and of course the legendary<strong>tramparty</strong>. If this still isnt enough EESTEC spirit for you, keep on reading!\r\n\r\nBecause were Swiss, were trying to plan your stay in Zurich as efficient and fun as possible. So, after a week of excitement and high level performance at both day and night, you will get the chance to relax and enjoy some fun activities on our motivational weekend in the Swiss mountains.\r\n\r\nThis and even more amazing experiences are waiting for you in Zurich! No previous knowledge is required but we do require you to be ready to<strong>have some serious fun</strong>and  what probably goes without saying at an EESTEC event  to be able go without much sleep for a week. If this sounds like you,<strong>welcome to Zurich</strong>! Were excited to get your motivational letter!\r\n\r\n<em>PS: If you wish, we can organize the transportation to Munich for the congress after our workshop. Accommodation until congress will also be organized.\r\nAlso, we will happily<strong>accept unofficial participants</strong>. Please wait for the respective call after the application deadline.</em>\r\n\r\n<strong><em>Arrival Notes:</em></strong>For planning purposes, we want to inform you already about the following arrival/departure guidelines. The event is designed such as you should arrive before 12 oclock on April 14th in Zurich and depart after 2 pm on April 21st from Zurich. Of course, we will be happy to host you some days before and/or after the event!', 'Slot Engines Xtreme', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2227-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:02:29', '2013-11-22 00:02:29', '', 2227, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3839', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3840, 2, '2013-11-22 00:02:50', '2013-11-22 00:02:50', '<span style="color: #1a1a1a;">Dear EESTECers,</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWe are proud to announce you a new workshop organised by <strong>LC Athens</strong>!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nNowadays, that Internet has become part of our daily routine, more and more services are available through it. The governmental services cannot be an exception to this!\r\n\r\nTherefore, the topic of this workshop is<strong>e-governance</strong> and during the week the participants will get to know the use of e-governance services through lectures by experienced professors, visits to some Public Services and discussions with experts.\r\n\r\nBy the end of the workshop, participants will use all the acquired knowledge to analyze and present the needs and specifications of an <strong>e-voting system!</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nDid you believe thats all? Well of course not! The participants will have the chance to meet the beautiful city of Athens!\r\n\r\nThey will walk around the historical center, visit Acropolis and its magnificent museum! They will taste our delicious traditional Greek cuisine, drink ouzo and of course meet the never-ending nightlife of Athens! We assure you that Athens nightlife will more than satisfy you! <img class="wp-smiley" alt=";)" src="http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" />\r\n\r\nThere will also be a Motivational Weekend from 15-17 March, in the beautiful and picturesque city of Trikala, which has the best e-governance system in Greece! For our participants, the expenses of this trip are covered by LC Athens.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAnd last but not least, since our Youth in Action application was accepted, we are really pleased to announce you that about <strong>70% of the travelling expenses for each participant will be refunded</strong>! But the refund is only available for the following (J)LCs and Observers that sent us the Part3 documents:\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Ankara, Banja Luka, Belgrade, Bucharest, Budapest, Eskisehir, Hamburg, Helsinki, Istanbul, Izmir, Krakow, Lille, Ljubljana, Madrid, Munich, Nis, Novi Sad, Riga, Sarajevo, Sheffield, Tallinn, Tampere, Trieste</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSo what are you waiting for?\r\n\r\nApply and get ready to have the best travelling experience with us!\r\n\r\nSee you in Athens! :)', 'Govern the Way of Youth', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2228-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:02:50', '2013-11-22 00:02:50', '', 2228, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3840', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3841, 2, '2013-11-22 00:03:09', '2013-11-22 00:03:09', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers;</p>\n<p>In cooperation with our WiE (Women in Engineering) affinity group, we are proud to announce the second &#8220;WiE &#8211; Girls @Business Class-2&#8243; Workshop as LC Istanbul which will be held on 3 &#8211; 10 March 2013, in Istanbul, Turkey.</p>\n<p>In the light of mission of WiE, we will start the discussion the position of women in society and business life and their problems in working places, and, enterprising women in business. In addition to all these issues there are many special trainings that contribute our participants the development of their personal and career.</p>\n<p>Wait! We havent finished yet. Do you think that weve forgotten the best part of our event? We have to confess; making extraordinary parties, knocking around and make people crazy is more and more easy for us when you compare with the academic part : )) You should know that one week is not enough to see all beauties of Istanbul which is a metropolitan with 17 million population ; however, you ll have an unforgettable 7 days without doubt. Istanbul is full of beauties, cultural activities, historical places and nightlife of course <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':-)'' class=''wp-smiley'' />  This city has become the capital of 3 biggest empires of the history (Roman, Byzantium and Ottoman). So just guess how old the city is and how much diversity and richness it includes. We are going to take you to Topkapi and Dolmabahce Palaces where the Ottoman Sultans resided, the Hagia Sophia Museum from the 6th century, the Blue Mosque, Basilica Cistern and some more surprise places. Participants will also have the chance to watch both Asian and European Part from the middle of the Bosphorus. And the awesome parties will be held in Istiklal Avenue which is the most crowded and crazy street you can ever see.</p>\n<p>In addition; to help you to know at least a little about;</p>\n<p>Istanbul,<a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=m-lh6zH74nQ" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.youtube.com'']);" target="_blank">Istanbul &#8211; 2010 European Capital of Culture</a>,<a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iglYVm01RHU" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.youtube.com'']);" target="_blank">Istanbul Timeless City</a>and<a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7CBllQ3Uchk" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.youtube.com'']);" target="_blank">Turkey</a></p>\n<p>For more feel free to contact us via <a href="mailto:Istanbul@eestec.net" target="_blank">Istanbul@eestec.net</a>. Dont think too much, apply it!</p>\n', 'WiE &#8211; Girls @Business Class &#8211; 2', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2229-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:03:09', '2013-11-22 00:03:09', '', 2229, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3841', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3842, 2, '2013-11-22 00:03:27', '2013-11-22 00:03:27', 'Dear Eestecers,\r\n\r\nAfter a long silent period, LC Istanbul is proud to announce the upcoming workshop .COM (point of Creativity, Originality and Magnificence) which will be held on 3<sup>th</sup>- 10<sup>th</sup> of March in Istanbul.\r\n\r\nAfter writing has been invented in Mesopotamia by Sumerians, Internet has become the most important invention which will perhaps change the fate of world as writing has done. At that time those who had knowledge to use writing held much more power in society compared to others. Now everyone has knowledge about writing, all of us know how to write, dont we? What about the Internet which stands at same position once writing had stood? Now those who know of language of Internet will have the same advantages like those who would have knowledge of writing. So we are ready to help you through this way. During the theoretical and practical lectures youll learn the twin brothers HTML and CSS (the things that make internet prettier) and also PHP by expert academicians and programmers. Of course we could not do it without the designing part of web programming.\r\n\r\nWait! We havent finished yet. Do you think that weve forgotten the best part of our event? We have to confess; making extraordinary parties, knocking around and making people crazy are much easier for us when it is compared to the academic part : )) You should know that one week is not enough to see all beauties of Istanbul which is a metropolitan with 17 million population ( in fact no one knows how many people live in Istanbul <img class="wp-smiley" alt=":D" src="http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif" /> ) ; however, you ll have unforgettable seven days without being bored. Istanbul is full of beauties, cultural activities, historical places, night life and, of course crazy people <img class="wp-smiley" alt=":-)" src="http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" /> This city had once been the capital of the three biggest empires of the history. (Roman, Byzantium and Ottoman). So just guess how old the city is and how much diversity and richness it includes. We are going to take you to Topkapi and Dolmabahce Palaces where the Ottoman Sultans used to reside, the Hagia Sophia Museum which was constructed in 6th century, the Blue Mosque, Basilica Cistern and some other surprising places. Participants will also have the chance of watching both Asian and European continents from the middle of Bosphorus. And the awesome parties will be held on Istiklal Avenue which is the most crowded and crazy street you can ever see. Can you imagine that three millions people walk on it just in one day?\r\n\r\nFor more information feel free to contact <a href="mailto:Istanbul@eestec.net" target="_blank">Istanbul@eestec.net</a>. Dont think too much, apply it!', '.COM (point of Creativity, Originality and Magnificence)', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2230-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:03:27', '2013-11-22 00:03:27', '', 2230, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3842', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3843, 2, '2013-11-22 00:03:52', '2013-11-22 00:03:52', 'After a long journey, you just arrived in Ankara. You try to call one of the organizers, but you noticed that battery is dead. Thanks to nanotechnology, you used extra efficient solar cells to charge your phone. Rushing for the party, you noticed that you dont have the most important protection tool with you <img class="wp-smiley" alt=":)" src="http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" /> No no, I am talking about super hydrophobic spray. With its magical hydrophobic material property, if someone spills a beer or even vomits on your dress, it is no big deal  it will clean itself Does it sound like Science-Fiction? The recent advancements in nanotechnology made it real: See the<a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''download'',''http://www.nanoteknoloji.tv/?File=MjAxMjAzMDctMDE1MC1raXJ0dXRtYXlhbmF5YWtrYWJpbGFyLmZsdg==&amp;id=109.'']);" href="http://www.nanoteknoloji.tv/?File=MjAxMjAzMDctMDE1MC1raXJ0dXRtYXlhbmF5YWtrYWJpbGFyLmZsdg==&amp;id=109." target="_blank">video</a>!\r\n\r\nLadies and gentlemen, we are proud to invite you to this small (10^-9 small) and amazing nanotechnology world. In this workshop, you will experience the world of nanotechnology including smart materials, nano bio-sensors and nano electro-mechanical systems not only bylectures but also field trips and tech talks.\r\n\r\nOf course this is not all!We all know that an event without the EESTEC traditions is unthinkable. Sightseeing, international night and parties are waiting for you!You will also experience the Turkish life; delicious Turkish cuisine, nargile (waterpipe), rak, traditional Turkish night and many more <img class="wp-smiley" alt=";)" src="http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" /> To sum up, LC Ankara is ready to host you once again!\r\n\r\nWe are also working really hard to arrange a country house in a mountain near Ankara, where you can enjoy the beautiful scene, and even ski. But we dont promise this, yet!\r\n\r\nWe are waiting for your applications, what are you waiting for ? <img class="wp-smiley" alt=";)" src="http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" />\r\n\r\nSee you soon in the halay\r\n\r\no/o/o/o/o/o/o/o/\r\nI   I  I   I   I   I   I   I\r\n/ / /  /  /  /  //', 'Shrink the World!', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2231-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:03:52', '2013-11-22 00:03:52', '', 2231, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3843', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3844, 2, '2013-11-22 00:04:35', '2013-11-22 00:04:35', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>As engineers, we like games. We actually love the challenges they demand us for winning them. Just recall the last time you discovered that so catchy one that almost drove you nuts because of the tangled rules you had to comprehend in order to focus on the strategies for conquering another level. Wasnt it simpler if you could rather center your attention at the creative side of things than on the frustrating part of reinventing the wheel ?</p>\n<p>Like so in our engineering field. Technology evolves and so do we. New issues need new approaches, particularly straightforward ones. Here, at EESTEC LC Craiova, we use to mock our so frequently low on RAM laptops by advising their owners to water the faint hamster endlessly rolling the wheel J . Would you buy it if we threw on the market a snake that, as it does with living food, makes you readily eat the principles at once leaving your attention open on the so important side of quickly solving your tasks without worrying about those aforementioned tangled rules ?</p>\n<p>Then let the PYTHON byte you ! Youll never have to worry about type declarations, semicolons or brackets. Just plain indentation. Getting rid of all that annoying clutter makes code clean and understandable for you and others. Easy life, on the short hand. Its name comes, as you might not think, from a movie, Guido van Rossum, who invented it in 1991, being inspired from &#8220;Monty Python&#8217;s Flying Circus&#8221;, a BBC comedy series from the 1970s.</p>\n<p>Become a PYTHONian ! Learn the basics and prepare for Twisted, Pyjamas, SQLAlchemy and many other toolkits and frameworks available for any of your platform independent scripting or programing needs, may it be web, databases or operating systems related. These might have funny names, but Python is so powerful that even Google and Facebook use it !</p>\n<p>Join our early spring trainings starting on 24th of March, lasting till 30th, reborn together with nature with all new programming skills, have fun with us coding the days and partying the nights along with our all around the world famous music and Romanian hospitality and wonder yourself why didnt you come to this earlier.</p>\n<p>Discover PYTHONIA ! And your imagination gets code wings. *The only boring part is the Hello, world! one.</p>\n', 'Pythonia', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2232-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:04:35', '2013-11-22 00:04:35', '', 2232, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3844', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0);
