(3886, 2, '2013-11-22 00:26:44', '2013-11-22 00:26:44', 'Shiny EESTECers,\r\n\r\nAs EESTECers, which are the best students in their faculties, we are all trying to be good engineers in our fields, but do you think only technical lectures we have had is enough to be a good one? If you say No way!, <strong>you need the correct TOOL!</strong>LC Ankara is proud to announce a brand-new international event, in cooperation with EESTEC Training Team: <strong>TOOL, a.k.a. Topic Oriented Optimized Learning.</strong>\r\n\r\nTOOL is a week-long soft-skills training and academic lecture series on various themes. The idea was born among EESTEC Training Team, after the first soft-skills training event of EESTEC, Tools For Action, also organized by LC Ankara on 2009. The main motivation behind TOOL is <strong>to spread the knowledge within EESTEC and create the future leaders of it!</strong>\r\n\r\nInterested already? Wait for the details\r\n\r\n<img class="aligncenter" title="TOOL" alt="" src="http://eestec.net/lc/ankara/tool-engineering-management-economics/tool3_2cokkucuk.jpg/image_preview" width="400" height="267" />\r\n\r\nTheme of this first EESTEC TOOL is Engineering Economics &amp; Management. From 10th to 17th of March 2012, EESTECers will attend trainings and lectures on various topics in this frame. The academic part of the event will be divided into two parts:\r\n\r\nFirst part is various soft-skill trainings that will be <strong>delivered by EESTEC Trainers</strong>. If you are interested in this kind of an event, you should have heard about EESTEC Training Team and how well qualified trainers take part of it. So, participants will receive trainings on topics like:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Project Management and Scheduling</li>\r\n	<li>Risk Management</li>\r\n	<li>Strategical Planning</li>\r\n	<li>Organizational Continuity</li>\r\n	<li>Budget Planning</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nSecond part will be academic lectures, again on the same theme. Lectures will be <strong>delivered by professors who have worldwide prestige on their fields</strong>. The topics will be:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Introduction to Engineering Management</li>\r\n	<li>Engineering Economic Analysis</li>\r\n	<li>Decision Analysis</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIs it only about to improvement as prospective engineers? Please\r\n\r\nIf you havent met yet, let us introduce you <a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://en.wikipedia.org'']);" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Turkish_cuisine" target="_blank">Turkish cuisine</a>, <a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://en.wikipedia.org'']);" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hookah" target="_blank">Turkish nargile</a>, <a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://en.wikipedia.org'']);" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rak" target="_blank">Rak</a>, <a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://en.wikipedia.org'']);" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Belly_dance" target="_blank">belly dance</a>, <a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://en.wikipedia.org'']);" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Turkish_bath" target="_blank">Turkish bath</a> and most importantly, Turkish hospitality!.. The accommodation will be in city center and participants will enjoy parties with a lot of different themes! We wont forget to have some EESTEC event traditions like sightseeing in historical capital of Turkey and international night as well.\r\n\r\nOne more important detail: <strong>TOOL is supported by EU Youth in Action Programme, which means 70% of travel costs from your city to Ankara will be covered for EU citizens</strong> as well as 100% of accommodation and food expenses as always. However, we will be able to refund<strong>70% of travel expenses for non-EU citizens, only if they choose to use Balkan FlexiPass</strong>. Besides, applicants from LCs which sent Partnership forms to us will have priority in selection process.\r\n\r\n<img class="aligncenter" title="YIA" alt="" src="http://eestec.net/lc/ankara/tool-engineering-management-economics/youthkopya.png/image_mini" width="200" height="125" /><img class="aligncenter" title="YIA" alt="" src="http://eestec.net/lc/ankara/tool-engineering-management-economics/youthen.png/image_mini" width="200" height="80" />\r\n\r\nAn amazing, brand-new event is waiting for you! Apply via <a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://eestec.net'']);" href="http://eestec.net" target="_blank">eestec.net</a> with your <strong>motivation letter in English</strong> before <strong>4th of February</strong>.\r\n\r\nIf you have any questions, dont hesitate to contact us via cp@eestectr.org\r\n\r\nGreetings from snowy Ankara!', 'TOOL: Engineering Economics & Management', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2272-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:26:44', '2013-11-22 00:26:44', '', 2272, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3886', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3887, 2, '2013-11-22 00:27:25', '2013-11-22 00:27:25', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>After years of silence LC Hamburg is finally back on track and proudly presents its new production:</p>\n<p>The EesteCube</p>\n<p>The curtains haven&#8217;t been raised yet, but our short &#8220;trailer&#8221; will give you some hints of what awaits you.</p>\n<p>In the main role are starring ten (eventually up to 20) professional Eestecers.</p>\n<p>The story takes place in the greenest and probably most beautiful city in Europe &#8211; Hamburg.</p>\n<p>The plot consists of unforgettable nights at the famous Reeperbahn street, visiting the second biggest harbor in Europe, an adventurous city rally, and &#8220;tasting&#8221; of German beer. And all these amazing scenes will be enlightened by the unique LED Cubes all of our smart main characters are going to build.</p>\n<p>They are going to be 5x5x5 single colored LED Cubes controlled by an ATmega32 microcontroller. Each of the 5 LED layers is driven by a D-Flip Flop. The controlling of this 3D LED matrix will be managed by time multiplexing.</p>\n<p>The scenario will be presented by our professors, however in order to pass the casting the actors should have basic C programming knowledge.</p>\n<p>So put your costumes and makeup on and apply for this fascinating workshop.</p>\n<p>The premier will start on 27th February and end on 5th March 2012.</p>\n<p><strong>Deadline to apply is January 26th!</strong></p>\n<p>LEDs on: 3, 2, 1, action!</p>\n', 'EesteCube', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2273-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:27:25', '2013-11-22 00:27:25', '', 2273, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3887', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3888, 2, '2013-11-22 00:27:32', '2013-11-22 00:27:32', '\n<p>Hello dear EESTECers!</p>\n<p>The time has come for LC Athens to announce its next workshop called &#8216;<strong>&#8216;Think Smart, Act Green</strong>&#8221;, which will be held from <strong>January 29th until February 5th</strong>!</p>\n<p><img class="alignnone" title="Think Smart, Act Green" src="http://eestec.net/lc/athens/think-smart-act-green/think_smart4.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="140" /></p>\n<p>The subject of this workshop is (you guessed it right)<strong> renewable forms of energy</strong>, a topic that concerns all of us. So the participants are going to spend the week learning -from our best professors in our faculty-, about how they work, what forms of renewable energy exist, and their importance to today&#8217;s world. But that&#8217;s not all! We&#8217;ll also visit the first energy autonomous village in Greece!!</p>\n<p>Moreover, concerning the practical part, participants will be divided into groups and they will make solar-panel models, where the most effective one&#8217;s team will be awarded! <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif'' alt='';)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n<p>There will be also trainings held by our famous trainers Thanos and Grigoris!!</p>\n<p>But really, have you ever met Athens by night??? This is another very important reason to apply for this event! LC Athens will take care of you every night and take you to the best places in Athens! (I&#8217;m not saying anything more, there will be surprises! <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif'' alt='';)'' class=''wp-smiley'' />  )</p>\n<p>You will also taste traditional Greek food , our famous ouzo and delicious desserts <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif'' alt='':D'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n<p>At the end of the workshop, we will have the chance to visit our beautiful countryside and have almost an entire hotel to ourselves! Crazy partying, anyone??!</p>\n<p>Last but really not least, we&#8217;re really pleased that our application for the &#8221;<strong>Youth in Action</strong>&#8221; programme was accepted, so about <strong>70% of the travelling expenses will be refunded</strong>!!</p>\n<p>So what are you waiting for??</p>\n<p>Just apply and take care of your board! <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif'' alt='':D'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n', 'Think Smart, Act Green', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2274-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:27:32', '2013-11-22 00:27:32', '', 2274, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3888', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3889, 2, '2013-11-22 00:27:58', '2013-11-22 00:27:58', '\n<p>We are excited to announce that this winter all roads will lead to <a href="http://www.tob.rs/en/index.php" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.tob.rs'']);" target="_blank">the capital of Serbia</a>. This December, <strong>LC Belgrade</strong> is organizing our eagerly awaited winter exchange <strong>Freeze the Time!</strong>. The spotlight is on showing our fellow EESTECers why Begrade is known as the city that never sleeps.</p>\n<p>No matter when, if it is during the night or day, our participants will get the chance to see how hedonism is present in all aspects of life in Belgrade. Walking through the New Years decorations of Knez Mihajlova street and visiting numerous restaurants, bars and clubs are excellent ways to enjoy Belgrade, especially when the end of the year is approaching. Dressed in white, our city will show you that there is no such place in the whole world where passion and European elegance is so naturally connected. But dont forget that you are coming to <a href="http://www.tesla-museum.org/meni_en.htm" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.tesla-museum.org'']);" target="_blank">the land of Nikola Tesla</a> and thats why you will also have the chance to enter the brilliant mind of this scientist. But that is not all! As the end of the year approaches, all students in Belgrade, which of course includes you, prepare for the well known <a href="http://kst.etf.rs/?p=14&amp;idv=2812" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://kst.etf.rs'']);" target="_blank">costume ball</a> in our favourite students club KST. So be ready to put some crazy costumes in your suitcase. And in case youve missed the Suit up Day, dont worry, LC Belgrade is taking you to the traditional ball on our faculty where youll get to show your moves on the dance floor.</p>\n<p>Apart from world wide famous nightlife, you will have the chance to spend a few days out of Belgrade, try out our delicious cuisine and of course discover the spirit of <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eASk9akIpvg&amp;feature=related" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.youtube.com'']);" target="_blank">Serbia</a> that lies in a bottle of our national drink rakija.</p>\n<p>Dont think youve heard it all! We have plenty of surprises left for you. Just remember, when you come to the White City, the clock stops, time freezes and the party begins. Be ready for the <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jAtf5obN3cc" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.youtube.com'']);" target="_blank">Belgrade state of mind</a>!</p>\n<p>Best regards,</p>\n<p>Olja Majstorovi</p>\n', 'Freeze the Time', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2275-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:27:58', '2013-11-22 00:27:58', '', 2275, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3889', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3890, 2, '2013-11-22 00:28:18', '2013-11-22 00:28:18', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>Would you like to get out of your daily routine and try something new?</p>\n<p>Do you lure to get a sneak peak in the spectacular cutting edge robots?</p>\n<p>Well, fasten your seat-belts because you are about to have the journey of your lifetime in the Future Robot Republic of Macedonia or abbreviated RoboMAC!</p>\n<p>LC Skopje is proud to announce that in collaboration with IEEE for the third time we are organizing the RoboMAC! It will take place from 19-th to 26-th of February in Skopje, with 30 international participants (EESTEC people) and over 70 students from our faculty&#8230;<br />\nYes you read that right!!! 30 EESTECers means this is the third biggest EESTEC event after EESTEC Congress and ECM.</p>\n<p>Now let us tell you a little bit about RoboMAC<br />\nRoboMAC means students creating scientific robots using off-the-shelf materials. What that means? That means that you will learn to build a robot that will do a specific job, with only the materials that you can buy in the local hardware store. Cool right !!! <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif'' alt='':D'' class=''wp-smiley'' />  And at the end of the week in the biggest closed sport venture in Macedonia &#8211; our national arena you can start the thrilling competition and check out how good is your robot <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif'' alt='':D'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> . Racing, sumo wrestling, programming an AI task oriented algorithms, or simply play hide and seek with your robots in a maze, and all that in front of lot of audience and the media. It means you will be a TV star that day in Macedonia. But thats not creative enough ??? No problem !!! Use your creative mind and take the challenge to program a Humanoid that will be capable of doing some crazy stuff, like Macarena dance <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif'' alt='':D'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> .</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Aq1bkaMBp3w&amp;feature=player_profilepage#t=156s" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.youtube.com'']);" target="_blank">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Aq1bkaMBp3w&amp;feature=player_profilepage#t=156s</a></p>\n<p>You dont know how to do this, but you want to learn? Thats why we have asked our professors from the robotics and AI (artificial intelligence) departments to teach you, and show you everything.</p>\n<p>Not ready to apply?<br />\nBut wait !!! We havent told you about the fun part !!!<br />\nIn Skopje we party only on New Years Eve and the days that end on day, like MonDAY, TuesDAY,., SunDAY. And bear to forget to visit the local Kafanas. Also we promise to keep the tradition of organizing the glamorous wine night where you will be enjoying best wines in Macedonia! We also want to know more about your country, thats why on the international party you will have the chance to introduce us to some of your local drinks and delicacies.</p>\n<p>Dont worry we didnt forget about giving you a tour throughout Skopje. You will be visiting:<br />\nThe Old Bazar <a href="http://tinyurl.com/6cfmyy6" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://tinyurl.com'']);" target="_blank">http://tinyurl.com/6cfmyy6</a><br />\nThe Biggest Cross in the world on the top of mount Vodno, where you will have a cup of coffee with the best view on Skopje<br />\n<a href="http://tinyurl.com/66gyndu" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://tinyurl.com'']);" target="_blank">http://tinyurl.com/66gyndu</a><br />\n<a href="http://www.panoramio.com/photo/14942097" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.panoramio.com'']);" target="_blank">http://www.panoramio.com/photo/14942097</a><br />\n<a href="http://www.panoramio.com/photo/14942204" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.panoramio.com'']);">http://www.panoramio.com/photo/14942204</a><br />\nThe biggest statue of Alexander the Great in the world and its fountain below (believe me the animation does not give it justice)<br />\n<a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=87DJ-LqYmHw" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.youtube.com'']);" target="_blank">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=87DJ-LqYmHw</a></p>\n<p>As you get it, we like big stuff so become part of the big fat RoboMAC<br />\napply don&#8217;t wait!</p>\n', 'RoboMAC', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2276-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:28:18', '2013-11-22 00:28:18', '', 2276, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3890', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3891, 2, '2013-11-22 00:28:26', '2013-11-22 00:28:26', '\n<p>Dear shiny EESTECers,</p>\n<p>After quite a long brake, we are back with new ideas, energy and surprises for you <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_razz.gif'' alt='':P'' class=''wp-smiley'' />  We, LC Wrocaw, are proud and very happy to announce our workshop: Microsystems around us. This event will give you fat and juicy pill of microsystems, an all-around super-developing branch of electrical engineering. Its a great opportunity for all of you to get to know whats inside</p>\n<p>Our experts from the University will show you the world. From their geeky perspective of course;) This means getting into it hard (ware) &#8211; how to fabricate the microsystems from silicon wafer to finished product (including photolithography, chemical etching and packaging process) and soft  latest achievements in the field and the opportunity to visit a cleanroom (if you thought of your toilet, check <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cleanroom" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://en.wikipedia.org'']);" target="_blank">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cleanroom</a>). Already interested? Here you have some videos about this subject:</p>\n<p> about microsystems: <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CNmk-SeM0ZI&amp;feature=related" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.youtube.com'']);" target="_blank">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CNmk-SeM0ZI&amp;feature=related</a></p>\n<p><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=j8VFvlDySHU&amp;feature=related" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.youtube.com'']);" target="_blank">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=j8VFvlDySHU&amp;feature=related</a></p>\n<p> website of Wrocaw University of Technology: <a href="http://www.pwr.wroc.pl/index.dhtml" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.pwr.wroc.pl'']);" target="_blank">http://www.pwr.wroc.pl/index.dhtml</a></p>\n<p> website of our MEMS laboratory: <a href="http://www.memslab.pl/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.memslab.pl'']);" target="_blank">http://www.memslab.pl/</a></p>\n<p> laboratories live  the Faculty of Microsystem Electronics and Photonics: <a href="http://www.wpanoramie.pl/wemifpwrwroc/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.wpanoramie.pl'']);" target="_blank">http://www.wpanoramie.pl/wemifpwrwroc/</a></p>\n<p> a video made in our laboratories: <a href="http://www-old.wemif.pwr.wroc.pl/m3/data/aktywnosc_kola.php" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www-old.wemif.pwr.wroc.pl'']);" target="_blank">http://www-old.wemif.pwr.wroc.pl/m3/data/aktywnosc_kola.php</a></p>\n<p> dessert link: <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bp00IuVAheQ" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.youtube.com'']);" target="_blank">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bp00IuVAheQ</a></p>\n<p>If youve read this far or skipped right to it, what you want the most, here it is: hedonism, tourism and partyism all the way! ;D During this weekly event you will have a lot of fun visiting our city and partying till dawn. To list some of the places we have scheduled for you (excluding party joints to keep the trump card  good luck for inquisitive souls at googling polish sites;):</p>\n<p>Ogrd Japoski,</p>\n<p>Ostrw Tumski (<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ostr%C3%B3w_Tumski,_Wroc%C5%82aw" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://en.wikipedia.org'']);" target="_blank">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ostr%C3%B3w_Tumski,_Wroc%C5%82aw</a>),</p>\n<p>Panorama Racawicka (<a href="http://www.panoramaraclawicka.pl/en/what_to_see.html" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.panoramaraclawicka.pl'']);" target="_blank">http://www.panoramaraclawicka.pl/en/what_to_see.html</a>),</p>\n<p>ZOO (<a href="http://www.zoo.wroclaw.pl/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.zoo.wroclaw.pl'']);" target="_blank">http://www.zoo.wroclaw.pl/</a>),</p>\n<p>Aquapark (<a href="http://www.parkwodny.wroc.pl/en/recreational-pools-gallery" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.parkwodny.wroc.pl'']);" target="_blank">http://www.parkwodny.wroc.pl/en/recreational-pools-gallery</a>),</p>\n<p>Wyspa Sodowa and others (<a href="http://www.facebook.com/wroclaw.wroclove" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.facebook.com'']);" target="_blank">http://www.facebook.com/wroclaw.wroclove</a>).</p>\n<p>Also you will able to do some shopping on the polish Christmas fair (<a href="http://www.jarmarkbozonarodzeniowy.com/?lang=en" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.jarmarkbozonarodzeniowy.com'']);" target="_blank">http://www.jarmarkbozonarodzeniowy.com/?lang=en</a>).</p>\n<p>For any questions don&#8217;t hesitate to ask! <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' />  <span style="text-decoration: underline;">Applications should be sent to <a href="http://eestec.net" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://eestec.net'']);" target="_blank">eestec.net</a></span>.</p>\n<p>Apply now! Don&#8217;t miss the chance to take part in a truly amazing adventure with LC Wrocaw.</p>\n', 'Microsystems around us', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2277-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:28:26', '2013-11-22 00:28:26', '', 2277, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3891', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3892, 2, '2013-11-22 00:28:33', '2013-11-22 00:28:33', '\n<p>Hey EESTECers,</p>\n<p>You don&#8217;t want to miss this! LC Aachen is going to show you the Christmas time of your life  the Niko-event is here! Apply till 01.11.2011 and experience from 03.12. (arrival) to 10.12. (departure) 2011.</p>\n<p>This is not a workshop, so prepare for the best! In our great exchange atmosphere, without learning or smart clothes (people from Delft are still allowed to bring their tie <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif'' alt='';)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> ), we promise you an amazing meeting in a romantic Christmas fair atmosphere with lots of hot mulled wine, gingerbread and EESTEC-spirit! Furthermore we will have a trip to Cologne, Maastricht and a lot of places you WILL enjoy!<br />\nAnd of course there is this great event: the Unicup, the annual ice-hockey tournament at our University. Your job will be to cheer our teams to victory and you&#8217;ll see that in Aachen nothing is usual!</p>\n<p>Should you have any questions, feel free to contact me at any time!</p>\n<p>I&#8217;m just about to finish my third beer for today, so I really hope you will join me <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif'' alt='';)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n<p>Martin<br />\nCP LC Aachen</p>\n<p>PS: beercounter++</p>\n', 'Niko Exchange', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2278-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:28:33', '2013-11-22 00:28:33', '', 2278, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3892', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3893, 2, '2013-11-22 00:28:46', '2013-11-22 00:28:46', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers out there,</p>\n<p>Youve been nagging and complaining so much that you miss the <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vh2HQYVYR64&amp;feature=player_embedded#%21" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.youtube.com'']);" target="_blank">Happy Shiny People</a> that we are and now heres yourresult: EESTEC LC Bucharest is happy to announce itsworkshop Business Engineering School.</p>\n<p>&#8220;To be or not to be anentrepreneur ? That is the question!&#8221;<br />\nThe event offers a week ofstudent conferences that will provide guidance in theentrepreneurship and business environment powered byexperts in the field. The workshop addresses a largenumber of young engineers that are eager toprofessionally develop their entrepreneurial skills.What will you practically learn throughout the week? Howto do your own Start Up, as an engineer. Its yetanother chance for us as EESTECers to prove the worldthat we do mean serious stuff and that we are all suitup and ready to take on theworld.You will have the chance to meetpeople having experience in working with organizationsworldwide, sharing their insights gained from researchand practice of business in industry.</p>\n<p>Our mission is&#8230;..tomake a difference</p>\n<p>We want to encourage engineeringstudents to implement their technical ideas gained inthe college years, and to provide you with skills,knowledge and networks in order to assist in realizingtheir potential.</p>\n<p>So, do not hesitate to apply.Even if this is an academicevent, we promise you will have a great time. VisitingBucharest and parties are on the schedule.And of course, you will have thechance to dance the Happy Shiny People dance again. Weknow its been a long time and maybe many of you haveforgotten about it or maybe didnt get the chance tolearn it, but all is not lost!And for the lucky 15 of you thatwill take part in our eventwe have an extra-spoil: you will be attending, at theend of the Workshop, an amazing just for you weekendin the mountains! Beautiful scenery, maybe even a littlesnow if were lucky, and late night BBQs, LC Buchareststyle <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif'' alt='';)'' class=''wp-smiley'' />  And with no curfew!! <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif'' alt='':D'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n<p>Apply now!<br />\nSee you in Romania!</p>\n', 'Business Engineering School', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2279-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:28:46', '2013-11-22 00:28:46', '', 2279, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3893', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3894, 2, '2013-11-22 00:28:54', '2013-11-22 00:28:54', '\n<p>How many times have you watched what robot can do and asked yourself how all that works? Have you ever tried to program anything like that? Would you like to peek deeper into the robotic world?</p>\n<p>LC Novi Sad is more than happy to announce that our workshop, called &#8220;We are all cyborgs now&#8221; will be held from 23 &#8211; 30. 10. 2011. In that period our experts will teach you as much as possible about programming and robot itself. We will try to do various interesting things such as writing, drawing, montage etc. Understandingly, we would learn all of that through fun and game.</p>\n<p>So far, I can tell you that we&#8217;re planning a weekend in the nature and traditional cooking and making barbecue, City Rally, sightseeing, clubbing and much, much more. And I have to mention that this event is for the people who love to learn (we will implant a lot of knowledge in your brain), for the ones who love noise ( &#8217;cause in the hustle and bustle of the city, nothing is ever silent) and for the ones who have a lot of energy (cause you will definitely need it <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> ).</p>\n<p>We are sure you will bring home a lot of great memories because Novi Sad will definitely make you feel awesome.</p>\n<p>Deadline for applying is: 23. 09. 2011.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SOESSCXGhFo" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.youtube.com'']);" target="_blank">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SOESSCXGhFo </a></p>\n', 'We are all cyborgs now', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2280-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:28:54', '2013-11-22 00:28:54', '', 2280, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3894', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3895, 2, '2013-11-22 00:29:01', '2013-11-22 00:29:01', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>LC Munich/Awesome is proud to announce the 2011 Oktoberfest Exchange from<br />\nSeptember 20th until September 26th.<br />\nYou will have the honor of drinking the world&#8217;s finest beer in the world&#8217;s<br />\nfinest city with the most sophisticated soon-to-be engineers in Europe.</p>\n<p>Besides all these tempting facts we are also planning a cultural program, a<br />\nCity-Rally, sightseeing, and clubbing. There won&#8217;t be any lectures, however<br />\nplenty of entertainment during your stay in Munich is guaranteed.</p>\n<p>Since hostel prices are ridiculous during Oktoberfest, we will be<br />\naccommodating you privately. Unfortunately we have to ask for a participation<br />\nfee of 60. This includes meals and local transportation. We have to warn you<br />\nthough, Munich is generally an expensive place during Oktoberfest. A liter of<br />\nbeer is 8.70! But as usual, everything except for drinks is included for our<br />\nparticipants. No need to worry, we will not be spending the entire week at<br />\nOktoberfest itself, and you will have a lot of chances to get cheaper beer! <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /><br />\nThis is a once in a lifetime chance to experience Oktoberfest at such<br />\naffordable prices!</p>\n<p>This year we will be able to host 11-13 participants.</p>\n<p>Again, this is the opportunity of your life to enjoy the world&#8217;s biggest beer<br />\nfestival (and party) with your fellow EESTECers! We strongly encourage you to<br />\napply! <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n<p>The deadline to apply for this awesome event is Saturday August 20th.</p>\n<p>P.S. Loving beer is a must <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif'' alt='';)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n<p>Cheers,</p>\n', 'Oktoberfest Exchange 2011', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2281-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:29:01', '2013-11-22 00:29:01', '', 2281, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3895', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3896, 2, '2013-11-22 00:29:08', '2013-11-22 00:29:08', '\n<p>Dear EESTEC-ers,</p>\n<p>On behalf of the Grant Team and LC Belgrade we are glad to inform you that the <strong>1st Grant Team Operational Conference &#8211; GToc</strong> is coming to life this <strong>August 16th-22rd 2011 in Belgrade</strong>.</p>\n<p>This International Event is the <strong>first official event of EESTEC Grant Team (GT)</strong> that became an official EESTEC Body during last EESTEC Congress in Craiova.</p>\n<p>In the past year, which was the first pilot year of action for the GT, a lot of progress was made and the results were very promising. Now, it is time for the Grant Team to expand and get more members from various LCs to continue the work of the previous year and open up to road to its future. In short, the Grant Team needs motivated people that want to get involved with the rather tricky, but highly rewarding area of grants. In short, the Grant Team needs YOU! <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n<p>During this event, participants will be introduced to the actions of the Grant Team, the various grants EESTEC can benefit from and the more technical details of these grants. In addition, the participants will be given the opportunity to become junior members of the Grant Team, since GToc is the only official method of becoming part of the Grant Team.</p>\n<p>As can be understood, there will be some serious work done during the event to ensure the work quality of GT for the years to come and to assist all of EESTEC in  getting funding for its events.</p>\n<p>BUT let&#8217;s not forget the fun part! It IS going to be in beautiful Belgrade after all <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /><br />\nLC Belgrade will host the event and show everyone the crazy EESTEC spirit that makes every event in Belgrade an amazing experience!</p>\n<p>A morning of sightseeing and many crazy evening parties in the never-sleeping capital of Serbia will make up for all your hard work!<br />\nAnd of course, the Belgrade Beerfest (August 17th-21st) is no coincidence! It will fuel our inspiration and creativity to its MAX <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif'' alt='';)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n<p>So all of you interested in getting involved with the Grant Team and experiencing the incredible team spirit within make sure to <strong>apply before July 24th 2011 23.59</strong>.<br />\nA <strong>Motivational Letter</strong> with any past experience you may have with grants and the reasons for your interest in the Grant Team will also be needed to let us know why you would like to join the awesome Grant Team <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /><br />\nThe selection of participants will be made jointly by the Grant Team and the International Board to ensure the proper continuation of the Grant Team.</p>\n<p>Don&#8217;t forget, the Grant Team has as one of its primary goals to educate EESTEC members, so do not hesitate to apply even if your former grant experience is minimal. <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n<p>On behalf of the Grant Team,<br />\nBest Regards,<br />\nSotiris Stasinopoulos</p>\n', 'Grant Team operational conference &#8211; GToc', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2282-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:29:08', '2013-11-22 00:29:08', '', 2282, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3896', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3897, 2, '2013-11-22 00:29:16', '2013-11-22 00:29:16', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>There is over a year now since the last Training for Trainers was organized and the time is coming for the 4th Training for Trainers  &#8220;T4T&#8221;.</p>\n<p>As you could see, this year LC Maribor will be the organizing LC and together with the Training Team everything will be done in order to prepare the best T4T till now!</p>\n<p><strong>What is the EESTEC Training Team? What are Trainings?</strong></p>\n<p>EESTEC Training Team is an official EESTEC body which is providing different services for EESTEC and through those services, based on trainings, constantly improving the work of EESTEC on international and local levels!</p>\n<p>Main goal of trainings is transfer of knowledge in an advanced way through different activities, techniques and methodologies.</p>\n<p>More information about the Training Team, Training System and Trainings you can find in the Official Training Team Document here.</p>\n<p><strong>What is T4T? Why is T4T being organized?</strong></p>\n<p>T4T  Training for Trainers is an international training event whose purpose is gaining new EESTEC trainers and it is the starting point for EESTECers to become a trainer.</p>\n<p>EESTECers which participate in T4T will go through intensive trainings, working sessions and practical parts and learn how to transfer knowledge, which methodologies to use and, very important, how to deliver trainings!</p>\n<p>As the transfer of knowledge is crucial for EESTEC, T4T is an event which assures new generations to continue with developing and providing Training Team services to EESTEC members. It is a stage through all Training team members have to go in order to gain different  soft skills like: leadership skills, presentation skills, communication skills and much more!</p>\n<p>Using these skills for transferring knowledge in EESTEC provides greater quality of different activities which are being organized in International and local levels.</p>\n<p>During T4T, 9 days of a lot of work is waiting for you so you will need to bring <strong>a lot of positive energy</strong> and <strong>enthusiasm</strong> in order to be effective all the time and to be able to endure the T4T.</p>\n<p><strong>Why become a Trainer? Why should you apply?</strong></p>\n<p>There are definitely a lot of reasons to apply. Becoming a trainer gives you an opportunity to contribute to EESTEC International, to contribute to LCs and to contribute to yourselves!</p>\n<p>As a trainer candidate (and optionally trainer) you will work in and create a positive atmosphere during T4T and after. If you become a trainer (for what you need to fulfill certain tasks) you will work on the transfer of knowledge to other EESTECers and you will have an opportunity to improve on personal level in different aspects.</p>\n<p>The skills you gain while being a trainer are needed in all aspects of life today and so in EESTEC. Because of that, members who participate in T4T have a big opportunity to develop themselves and to give a great contribution to the development of EESTEC!</p>\n<p><strong>Fun part <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </strong></p>\n<p>T4T is a hardworking event but there is no event in EESTEC which doesn&#8217;t provide a lot of great atmosphere and fun!</p>\n<p>Organizers from LC Maribor, together with trainers, will do their best to prepare great mood and different social activities for participants <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif'' alt='';)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n<p>As always you will meet great people from all around the world, enjoy great parties and enjoy in a beautiful city &#8211; Maribor!</p>\n<p>All this combined with effective work and personal development is surely an event which you will never forget!</p>\n<p>If you are an experienced EESTECer, if you participated in trainings, if you want to become a trainer, if you want to develop yourself and EESTEC or if you think that you could become a trainer &#8211; apply!</p>\n<p>All now is left is to fill the application form which you can find on the next <a href="http://goo.gl/VzMiw" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://goo.gl'']);" target="_blank">link</a> and to send it to</p>\n<p><a href="mailto:trainings-coordinator@eestec.net" target="_blank">trainings-coordinator@eestec.net</a> !</p>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>The deadline for applications is 4th of August 2011.</strong></span></p>\n<p>I will be glad to answer any questions and you feel free to ask anything you have on your mind <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif'' alt='';)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n<p>We hope to see a lot of applications! <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n<p>Best regards and enjoy!</p>\n<p>On behalf of LC Maribor and Training Team,</p>\n<p>Nermin Smaji</p>\n<p>EESTEC International Training Team Coordinator</p>\n', 'T4T 2011', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2283-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:29:16', '2013-11-22 00:29:16', '', 2283, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3897', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3898, 2, '2013-11-22 00:29:22', '2013-11-22 00:29:22', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>Do you want to spend the end of summer time at the best possible way? Do you want to have fun 24/7? Do you want to experience wild beauty and enjoy in it?</p>\n<p>Then, don&#8217;t wait! LC Podgorica is happy to present you Montenegro Summer Exchange. We promise you a lot of great food and parties, as well as beach parties. There will be 7 days of an unforgettable atmosphere , 7 days of EESTEC spirit and of course 7 nights of crazy fun at our parties we are preparing for you!</p>\n<p>Fun will start in our capital city &#8211; Podgorica. Than you&#8217;ll visit re-desovered paradise of our country. Don&#8217;t forget to pack your sunglasses, bikini, shorts and skirts because Mediterranean spirit is waitng for you. For nature lovers we&#8217;ll organize visit to the <a href="http://www.discover-montenegro.com/Lovcen%20and%20Mausoleum%20Slideshow/index.html" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.discover-montenegro.com'']);" target="_blank">National park Loven and Njego mausoleum</a> on top of the mounatin Loven (1657 meters above the sea level). After that, EESTEC spirit will shake one of the most beautiful cities on Montenegrin coast  <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RlbgebQtCgk&amp;feature=related" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.youtube.com'']);" target="_blank">Kotor</a>. You will have opportunity to experience last night of <a href="http://www.kotorkarneval.me/eng/eng.htm" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.kotorkarneval.me'']);" target="_blank">Kotor Carnival</a>. We will organize cruise around Boka bay, and organize many day and night parties <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' />  Also, you will see the pearl of Mediterranean  city of Budva.</p>\n<p>This event will also have an educational part, as we all know the importance of Soft Skills. We will organize trainings on some of most important topics of Soft Skills.</p>\n<p>We are sure you&#8217;ll leave here with memories you&#8217;ll never forget! You only have to bring all of your EESTEC spirit with you!</p>\n<p>Montenegro is calling, holiday is rolling!</p>\n', 'Montenegro Summer Exchange &#8217;11', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2284-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:29:22', '2013-11-22 00:29:22', '', 2284, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3898', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3899, 2, '2013-11-22 00:29:55', '2013-11-22 00:29:55', '\n<p>We are proud to say that our event JAZZ DO IT! is becoming tradition.<br />\nSince it was great last year, we have decided to do it again! That&#8217;s why<br />\nwe are inviting you to join us at the biggest jazz event in Southern and<br />\nEastern Europe &#8220;<a href="http://www.nisville.com/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.nisville.com'']);" target="_blank">Niville jazz festival</a>&#8220;. Together we will enjoy the good<br />\njazz sound accompanied with great atmosphere that only EESTEC exchange<br />\ncan provide. Organized in the <a href="http://img704.imageshack.us/img704/1240/centar.jpg" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://img704.imageshack.us'']);" target="_blank">medieval fortress</a> and visited by more than<br />\n100.000 people only last year, Niville hosted some of the biggest stars<br />\nof jazz music: Candy Dulfer, Grace Kelly Band, Incognito, Solomon Burke,<br />\nBenny Golson, De Phazz, Roy Hargrove&#8230; This year there is no exception<br />\nbecause Steve Hans Dulfer, Sly&amp;Robbie, Mungo Jerry, Tom Harrell, Rick<br />\nMargitza and 50 other bands on 5 different stages will jazz it up for us!</p>\n<p>Regular price for this festival is about 50 Euros, but as our guest you<br />\nare getting it for free <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n<p>And you will also learn some things about acoustics and making music.</p>\n<p>But, thats not all. The City of Ni has great cultural and historical<br />\nheritage. Serbia is birthplace of 17 Roman emperors, and one of the most<br />\nimportant persons in European history, emperor <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Constantine_the_Great" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://en.wikipedia.org'']);" target="_blank">Constantine the Great</a>,<br />\nwas born in Ni (roman name NAISSUS) in 272 AD.</p>\n<p>You will also visit a <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ni_Fortress" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://en.wikipedia.org'']);" target="_blank">Fortress of Ni</a>, where Niville jazz festival<br />\ntakes place. The fortress exists at this place for more than 2000 years,<br />\nand has layers from different historical periods. Thats because Ni is<br />\non the road that connects Europe with Middle East (in roman times this<br />\nroad was called VIA MILITARIS), so many civilizations passed here and<br />\nthey left some trace in the fortress. Its in this condition since XVII<br />\ncentury, and now its one of the best preserved fortifications of<br />\nOttoman style in Europe.</p>\n<p>In Ni exists one unique monument in the world, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Skull_Tower" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://en.wikipedia.org'']);" target="_blank">Skull Tower</a>, which was<br />\nbuilt from skulls of the warriors who died in the egar battle in the<br />\n1809. You will also visit a <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_of_egar" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://en.wikipedia.org'']);" target="_blank">egar monument</a> where this battle took place.</p>\n<p>Well show you one relaxing place, <a href="http://www.nistourism.org.rs/health-oasis.html" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.nistourism.org.rs'']);" target="_blank">Nika Banja</a> spa which has radioactive<br />\nhealing water and well go swimming there with a lot of EESTEC spirit!</p>\n<p>And if you think that we only have history, youre wrong, because Ni is<br />\nknown as town where you can have a lot of fun. We have centuries old<br />\nhedonist legacy! Are you brave enough to try our traditional drink<br />\nrakija? And the best BBQ in the world including pljeskavica will help<br />\nyour body to work well with all that alcohol. There wont be a single<br />\nmoment that youll be hungry, because Serbians like good food in big<br />\nquantities. All that you will be able to taste in a traditional ambient<br />\nat the special night in kafana. If you dont know what merak is (that<br />\nword has no translation to other languages), you will learn here!</p>\n<p>So the crazy summer cocktail with&#8230; traditional Serbian drinks and<br />\nfood plenty of great music nice town a lot of EESTEC spirit Mix all<br />\nthat in a summer temperature and share it with good orgaNICEers.</p>\n<p>What are you waiting for?</p>\n<p><a href="http://img404.imageshack.us/img404/5156/jazzdoitcopy.jpg" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://img404.imageshack.us'']);" target="_blank">Jazz do it! 2011. </a></p>\n', 'JAZZ DO IT!', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2285-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:29:55', '2013-11-22 00:29:55', '', 2285, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3899', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0);
