(3919, 2, '2013-11-22 00:35:33', '2013-11-22 00:35:33', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>LC Madrid is proud to present our new and first event for the 2011!<br />\nDue to the generational change at our local committee and the great change which our society is living, this year we decided to change our minds and focus on something that is closer to us: the SOCIETY. But nowadays everything is global, we all are interconnected with everything, so our society lives and works in NETWORKs.<br />\nFor all these reasons, we have created NETWORK SOCIETY, a new kind of event for us during which, through conferences, seminars and visits to laboratories and research centers, we will try to offer you a wide overview of what is being done in this fields and how our global society is growing up through the network.</p>\n<p>This amazing project will be held in Madrid from  3th April 2011 to 10th April 2011.</p>\n<p>Okay, okay, that all sounds very nice and interesting, but what about the party? WE WANT PARTY!</p>\n<p>Don&#8217;t worry, as we always say: Madrid NEVER sleeps.<br />\nSo, during the whole week you&#8217;ll have a lot of chances to feel Madrid&#8217;s party and lifestyle, visit some of the landmarks of our city and participate in the traditional CityRally. And if that were not enough, during the weekend you will have the opportunity to enjoy some time out the city, practicing some sports and having crazy parties in the countryside!</p>\n<p>Besides, this year we have talked to a psychic who has confirmed that no other Eyjafjallajkull will wake up during our event. Now, what are you waiting for? Apply for the event ASAP, the deadline is 6th February 2011! =&#8217;D</p>\n<p>By the way, there&#8217;s another important point&#8230;<br />\nWe&#8217;re so sorry to have to say this, but as we don&#8217;t apply for EU grant, every year we have to make great efforts to find sponsors for our events, and although we are delighted with the result obtained in this area the last year, in previous events some years back, we had problems with some people showing a total lack of consideration for our work, sleeping during conferences with the sponsors and university professors, which made us lose all our credibility among them&#8230;</p>\n<p>Therefore, this time we expect a similar attitude to the last year and we won&#8217;t tolerate an irresponsible one. And in case of it happens, participants will be warned and eventually expelled from the event if warnings are disregarded.</p>\n<p>When there is time to party, we party (and trust me, there will be! ;D), but when it&#8217;s time to work, we work (and later we have party! ^^).</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.eestec.es/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.eestec.es'']);" target="_blank">More information about this event</a></p>\n<p>We hope to see you all in Madrid!</p>\n<p>Greetings from LC Madrid&#8230;</p>\n', 'Network Society', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2304-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:35:33', '2013-11-22 00:35:33', '', 2304, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3919', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3920, 2, '2013-11-22 00:35:41', '2013-11-22 00:35:41', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>Let&#8217;s all prepare for magnificent and breathtaking mountain of Durmitor and enjoy an unexpected beautiful and picturesque winter wonderland!</p>\n<p>LC Podgorica is happy to invite eight of you to join 3 days long snowy party in tourist center of National Park Durmitor and winter sports of Montenegro &#8211; the town of abljak,  which is situated in the north-west of Montenegro, 1450 meters above sea level.</p>\n<p>Beside extremely good parties, visitation of National Park and other interesting activities, LC Podgorica will hold training on the topic of Team Building and Project Management. Accordingly, you will have a chance to meet a lot of your colleagues from Electrical Engineering Faculty Podgorica.</p>\n<p>If you have any questions, feel free to ask me <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n<p>Deadline for applying is <strong>7. February 2011</strong>.</p>\n<p>More information about abljak you can discover on: <a href="http://www.durmitorcg.com/opstina_eng.php" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.durmitorcg.com'']);" target="_blank">http://www.durmitorcg.com/opstina_eng.php</a></p>\n<p><strong>It is no wonder that visiting Montenegro during the winter can be full of pleasant surprises.</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Come to discover, experience and enjoy &#8221;Wild Beauty&#8221;!</strong> <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n', 'Durmitor Motivational Weekend', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2305-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:35:41', '2013-11-22 00:35:41', '', 2305, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3920', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3921, 2, '2013-11-22 00:36:03', '2013-11-22 00:36:03', '\n<p>Dear CPs,</p>\n<p>We&#8217;re happy to announce that LC Belgrade won EU grant and therefore is making preparations for a workshop called &#8221;<strong>Lead the way!</strong>&#8221;.<br />\nThe prime aim of this event is to prepare young people (meaning participants <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> ) with necessary skills and knowledge in order to improve themselves (more), to create successful business plans and start up their own businesses, find financing opportunities and become future leaders in their communities.<br />\nAll of these skills you&#8217;ll get by taking part in different activities, such as: lectures, presentations, working sessions, funny games&#8230;</p>\n<p>Apart from this academic activities, we&#8217;ll do our best to present you the beauties of <a href="http://www.tob.rs/en/index.php" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.tob.rs'']);" target="_blank">our capital</a> (is there anyone who haven&#8217;t heard about Kalish Challenge?!) and its world wide famous nightlife. You&#8217;ll have enough time to enjoy delights of Serbian cuisine and to find out why people fall in love with rakija with the first sip. <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /><br />\nOh, and&#8230;Prepare yourselves for a lot of winter magic, since we&#8217;re taking you to weekend trip to Kopaonik, one of our most attractive mountains.</p>\n<p>We&#8217;d like to thank to all LCs who signed part3 form and made this event possible by giving us their support.<br />\nPlease note that only LCs listed below can send their members to this event, paying respect to referred gender distribution.</p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;" rowspan="2"><strong>LC<br />\n</strong></td>\n<td style="text-align: center;" rowspan="2"><strong>Number of participants<br />\n</strong></td>\n<td style="text-align: center;" colspan="2"><strong>Distribution by gender<br />\n</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><strong>M</strong></td>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><strong>F</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: left;">Ankara</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: left;">Munich</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: left;">Ljubljana</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: left;">Maribor</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: left;">Zagreb</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: left;">Sarajevo</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: left;">East Sarajevo</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: left;">Belgrade</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: left;">Madrid</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: left;">Bucharest</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: left;">Tallinn</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: left;">Athens</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: left;">Podgorica</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: left;">Skopje</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>0</td>\n<td>2</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: left;">Budapest</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>0</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: left;">Delft</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td style="text-align: left;">1</td>\n<td>0</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n', 'Lead the way!', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2306-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:36:03', '2013-11-22 00:36:03', '', 2306, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3921', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3922, 2, '2013-11-22 00:36:23', '2013-11-22 00:36:23', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>After our third edition of Conquer the markets LC Zrich is proud to announce our new workshop Zrich interactive!</p>\n<p>Despite of the new subject many of the well-tried parts like our famous tram-party and the city rally will take place. In small groups you will design or program games and light animations on our self-made interactive dance floor, which detects movements on it and can be enlightened in all possible colors. Groups will be made according to your preferences and knowledge, so if you do not like to program, you can think about the next party game hit! And it will be played on a 4&#215;2.5m &#8220;Touchscreen&#8221;!</p>\n<p>Check out this video of Snake being played on a smaller version of the dance-floor: <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=um1bMXSOXw8" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.youtube.com'']);" target="_blank">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=um1bMXSOXw8</a></p>\n<p>Besides playing with the dance floor we will visit a <strong>chocolate factory</strong> and go one <strong>whole day skiing</strong>! Like every year there will be <strong>many parties</strong> with much free alcohol <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif'' alt='';-)'' class=''wp-smiley'' />  We are proud to announce that we got the Youth in Action-grant, which means a big part of the travel costs will be paid back to you. Additionally it enables us to organize some special activities you will not forget, ever!</p>\n<p>A temporary schedule can be found here: <a href="http://eestec.net/lc/zurich/zurich-interactive" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://eestec.net'']);" target="_blank">http://eestec.net/lc/zurich/zurich-interactive</a></p>\n<p>If you don&#8217;t have skiing equipment and want to go on the ski-slopes it&#8217;s possible to rent everything. For us it is important that everybody who wants to ski gets the possibility- for this we will pay a part of the renting and ticket costs! And for those not wanting to try skiing, a beautiful day in the snow-covered alps with some sledging and some Glhwein is waiting!</p>\n<p>Best regards and see you in Zrich!!</p>\n<p>Your LC Zrich</p>\n', 'Zrich interactive', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2307-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:36:23', '2013-11-22 00:36:23', '', 2307, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3922', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3923, 2, '2013-11-22 00:36:56', '2013-11-22 00:36:56', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>Dig out your earmuffs, gloves and other winter clothes and get ready for some mind-blowing fun in the snow!</p>\n<p>LC Sarajevo is proud to announce that our EESTEC Winter Olympic Games Sarajevo are becoming a tradition! We are now even more focused on and excited about offering you more fun and entertainment!!</p>\n<p>Everyone knows that when it comes to EESTEC having fun is obligatory so let us prove once again that the EESTEC spirit is alive and kicking!</p>\n<p>It is time to hang up your thinking caps and get ready to party EESTEC STYLE! The parties are going to be crazier, the games more intense than anything you have EVER experienced. This is truly an exchange you will not want to miss out on! (I should also mention that there is no academical part <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> )</p>\n<p>Every night from 22.02.2011 to 27.02.2011 you will be able to experience the Great Spirit of Sarajevo. We will present you cultural beauties of Sarajevo, the place where West and East meet.</p>\n<p>Not only will you experience a cultural mix unlike anywhere in the world and have a chance to meet the friendliest people, but you will also enjoy a weekend on one of our beautiful mountains.</p>\n<p>A true winter wonderland.</p>\n<p>If you have any questions, feel free to contact CP of event Dana Kujan on dzana.kujan@gmail.com.</p>\n<p>Deadline for applying is 25th January 2011.</p>\n<p>More information about Sarajevo and last years EWOGS you can find on:</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.ewogs.com.ba" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.ewogs.com.ba'']);" target="_blank">http://www.ewogs.com.ba</a></p>\n<p><a href="http://www.sarajevo.ba" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.sarajevo.ba'']);" target="_blank">http://www.sarajevo.ba</a></p>\n<p><a href="http://www.sarajevo-tourism.com" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.sarajevo-tourism.com'']);" target="_blank">http://www.sarajevo-tourism.com</a></p>\n<p><strong>Enjoy NATURE. Enjoy FRIENDSHIP. Enjoy CRAZY. Enjoy LAZY. Enjoy EAST. Enjoy WEST. Enjoy LIFE. Enjoy BOSNIA AND HERZEGOVINA.</strong></p>\n', 'Winter Olympic Games Sarajevo', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2308-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:36:56', '2013-11-22 00:36:56', '', 2308, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3923', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3924, 2, '2013-11-22 00:37:05', '2013-11-22 00:37:05', '\n<p>Did you ever want to stop the moment? Sometimes the words do not have any meaning,in at that moment an image becomes physical with photographing. If you are one of that people who wants to stop the moment, if your fever is not balanced and if you want to photograph intersection of European and Asian culter together. Then we will give a chance to you to fell more energetic and refreshing yourself with humanistic photosynthesis.</p>\n<p>The main topic of the event is &#8216;photograph&#8217; and &#8216;photoshop&#8217;. Event will be 2 parts; first part will be theoretical, we will give some sessions about how to produce a professional photograph, usage of a professional  camera, details of taking pictures and using photoshop professionally. Sessions will not be only informative but also funny. Second part will be practice, we will go to the area of Anadolu University, to the beautiful nature and historical places of Eskisehir and into the city, to take some good pictures together.</p>\n<p>Sessions will be really funny but also crazy nights of the Eskiehir will be waiting for you. Also we will give you a chance to see the best Turkish Bath in the Turkey, traditional Turkish drink Rak, delicious Turkish foods, Turkish Nargile,and so on&#8230;We will not forget traditional EESTEC nights for sure, multi culture night&#8230;</p>\n<p>LC ESKEHR will host 15 participants, if there will be more applications, we will try to accept best number of the applications which we can do. <strong>If you have your own camera, recommended to take it with you, but if you do not have any camera we will give you one until the end of the event.</strong></p>\n<p>So <strong>we are waiting for you</strong> ,and <strong>what are you waiting for</strong>?</p>\n<p>If you have any question do not hesitate to ask us.</p>\n<p>SEE YOU!</p>\n', 'PhotosynthESis', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2309-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:37:05', '2013-11-22 00:37:05', '', 2309, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3924', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3925, 2, '2013-11-22 00:37:26', '2013-11-22 00:37:26', '\n<p>Are you interested in space? Do you like Star Wars movies? Would you like to experience Finland&#8217;s beautiful winter? Eestec LC Helsinki proudly presents the first workshop of the year 2011: StarWorks! We have prepared you an awesome workshop about space technology and provided an opportunity to learn cool stuff from famous and crazy scientist guys like Esko Valtaoja!</p>\n<p>We will have super interesting lectures about space, remote sensing, northern lights and satellites. We will also have some fun sessions where you will learn how to study earth from space. Our Department of Radio Science and Engineering will provide you one ECTS (European Credit Transfer and Accumulation System) if you return a diary of the stuff you have learned during the week.</p>\n<p>And no.. we have not forgotten to spoil you with some parties as we are going to throw you to sauna, show you some naked people and teach you how to drink &amp; sing in Finnish academic student party called sitsit. And furthermore, you&#8217;ll experience parties in Helsinki center, movie making with local TV-channel and weekend at a countryside where you can do ice swimming!</p>\n<p>So grab your lightsaber and make sure that you&#8217;ll be in Helsinki at 23rd of January 2011!</p>\n', 'StarWorks', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2310-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:37:26', '2013-11-22 00:37:26', '', 2310, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3925', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3926, 2, '2013-11-22 00:37:53', '2013-11-22 00:37:53', '\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Hello dear EESTECers,</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">LC Aachen is happy to invite you to this year&#8217;s edition of our traditional Niko-Event.</span> <span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">It takes place from 5.12. (arrival) to 11.12. (departure) 2010. The deadline to apply is the 19.11.2010.</span><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">We have to apologize for announcing the event so late and for the short deadline!</span> <span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">However, we will try to present you some nice days: Instead of workshop-atmosphere with lots of learning and company-visiting, we promise you a small nice meeting in a Christmas fair atmosphere with lots of hot mulled wine, gingerbread and EESTEC-spirit! Furthermore we will have a trip to Cologne and tours around our nice little town.</span> <span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">And of course there is the main event: the Unicup, the annual icehockey-tournament at our University. Your job will be to cheer our teams to victory!</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Should you have any questions, feel free to contact us at any time!</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Hopefully see you soon!</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Andreea Siller (CP Aachen)</span></p>\n', 'Niko-Meeting', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2311-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:37:53', '2013-11-22 00:37:53', '', 2311, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3926', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3927, 2, '2013-11-22 00:38:28', '2013-11-22 00:38:28', '\n<p>Dear lovely EESTECers;</p>\n<p>Were sure that all of you wonder how to fly a plane? How can a pilot keep all of the aeronautical units in the cockpit under control? As we EESTECers, planes are very important for us and you have a chance to know everything about them thanks to our great(will be) workshop <strong>Above us only sky!</strong> which will take place in Ankara between <strong>4.12.2010 </strong>and <strong>12.12.2010</strong>.</p>\n<p>The main topic of workshop is &#8220;Avionics&#8221; which is a combination of the words &#8220;aviation&#8221; and &#8220;electronics&#8221;. As you may know, especially with the development of unmanned aerial vehicle, avionics has become a very popular topic nowadays.<br />\nDuring the workshop, you&#8217;ll have comprehensive knowledge about avionics by taking lectures regarding subtopics which are navigation, unmanned aerial vehicle, control, avionics history and development, and every other detail you need to know. Trainings will be given by professors and their assistants in Aerospace Engineering Department of Middle East Technical University which is one of the best technical university in Turkey and trainers of TAI(Turkish Aerospace Industries) which is the biggest company in Turkey in aerospace industry. You&#8217;ll not only have lectures, but also visit production line in the factory of TAI, laboratories of Aerospace Engineering Department of Middle East Technical University, and aeronautic museums. In addition, you&#8217;ll have an opportunity to see a simulation of how unmanned aerial vehicle works.</p>\n<p>Now lets move on to the fun part! We guarantee the enjoying part will be awesome as much as the academic part. You will have a great chance to get know &#8220;T<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kebab" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://en.wikipedia.org'']);">urkish Kebab</a>&#8220;, &#8220;<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nargile" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://en.wikipedia.org'']);">Turkish Nargile</a>&#8220;, &#8220;<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Belly_dance" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://en.wikipedia.org'']);">Turkish Belly Dance</a>&#8220;, &#8220;<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rak" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://en.wikipedia.org'']);">Turkish Raki</a>&#8221; and the most important one Turkish Hospitality. Accommodation will be in the guest house of Turkish Aeronautics Association; that is, you&#8217;re gonna stay with quite many planes. Every night well enjoy with the non-stop and crazy parties with different themes such as masquerade party, aeronautics party where guys can be pilot and girls can be hostess for one night! But it&#8217;s for sure; we&#8217;ll not forget to have some EESTEC event traditions like sightseeing, international night as well.</p>\n<p>LC Ankara will host <strong>15 participants</strong>; however, we&#8217;ll do our best to accept more participants. <strong>Deadline to apply is the 1st of November</strong>.</p>\n<p>As you see, such a wonderful event in different continent, Asia is ready for you. So what you are supposed to do now is just to enter <a href="http://eestec.net" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://eestec.net'']);">eestec.net</a> and submit your application form!!</p>\n<p>If you have any question, feel free to ask via <strong>mervebilgic90@gmail.com</strong>.</p>\n<p>Looking forward to seeing you here!!</p>\n<p>Greetings from Turkey!</p>\n', 'Above us only Sky!', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2312-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:38:28', '2013-11-22 00:38:28', '', 2312, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3927', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3928, 2, '2013-11-22 00:38:46', '2013-11-22 00:38:46', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>Have you ever wondered what it would be like to build some robots? Or maybe you are curious about how amazing Riga and its nightlife is? JLC Riga has prepared for you our very first workshop Plop, Plop, Fizz, Fizz, Oh, What a Robot it is? and it will take place in Latvia, Riga from 5th till 12th December .</p>\n<p>With the help of experienced trainers you will be able to gain practical skills to operate electronical components and learn basic programming that will let the Robot you build become a real fighter! All the built robots will take part Baltic states robot contest Robotika.</p>\n<p>Besides that, we are planning to show you our best places in Riga and not only. You should know that Riga is famous with its architecture and skyline of 3 Church steeples, which has become a true visiting card. Well, of course when the sun goes down, the nightlife can begin and Old Riga is full of places to have fun  plenty of pubs and clubs. But you will have to see it all for yourselves.</p>\n<p>For the weekend we have prepared to you little trip to Sigulda (also called The Switzerland of Latvia) which is famous for its Castles and adorable landscapes.</p>\n<p>Well, we cannot tell you all the details, but we can assure you that you will love it here. Don&#8217;t miss this <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EO_9_Zd8pqk" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.youtube.com'']);">beautiful city</a> !</p>\n<p>See you in Riga! <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n', 'Plop, Plop, Fizz, Fizz, Oh, What a Robot it is?', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2313-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:38:46', '2013-11-22 00:38:46', '', 2313, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3928', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3929, 2, '2013-11-22 00:38:51', '2013-11-22 00:38:51', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>LC Munich is proud to announce that we will organize an event never done<br />\nbefore: The soon-to-be-legendary Oktoberfest Exchange!<br />\nIt will take place between Wednesday the 29th September and Tuesday the<br />\n4th October.</p>\n<p>A few words regarding the concept of this exchange: There will be no<br />\nlectures, however, entertainment during your stay in Munich will be cared<br />\nfor. We will accommodate you privately, since there is no way to get a<br />\nhotel spot in Munich during Oktoberfest without paying ridiculous prices.<br />\nUnfortunately we have to ask a participation fee of 90. This includes<br />\nbeer and food at the Oktoberfest worth 27. Be advised, however, that you<br />\nwill very likely spend a lot more money on beer &#8212; one beer is 8.50.<br />\nMunich is generally an expensive place during the Oktoberfest, but as<br />\nusual, everything except for drinks is included for our participants.<br />\nThe exchange will include two visits to the famous &#8220;Wiesn&#8221; along with<br />\nsightseeing to famous places such as Neuschwanstein, a nearby castle built<br />\nby Bavarian King Ludwig II.</p>\n<p>For various organisational reasons we unfortunately cannot accept more<br />\nthan 10-12 participants, the exact number is yet to be announced. We<br />\nencourage you very much to apply, after all this is a once in a lifetime<br />\nopportunity (unless we do it again next year) to visit the famous<br />\nOkotberfest with few fellow EESTECers!! Don&#8217;t miss out and send your<br />\napplication today <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':-)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /><br />\nDeadline to apply is Saturday, August 14th, 12 PM (noon).</p>\n<p><strong>Disclaimer:</strong> Due to the nature of the event and the extraordinary<br />\ncircumstances, we reserve the right not to respect your priority list. We<br />\nencourage you, however, to send one anyway and apologize for the<br />\ninconvenience. We&#8217;ll try to fulfill your request as good as possible.</p>\n', 'Oktoberfest Exchange', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2314-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:38:51', '2013-11-22 00:38:51', '', 2314, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3929', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
(3930, 2, '2013-11-22 00:39:28', '2013-11-22 00:39:28', '\n<p><strong><br />\n</strong></p>\n<h2>Green Week in Novi Sad  Act Now &#8211; Change the Future</h2>\n<p>eYouwins &#8211; The European Youth Week in Novi Sad is the one of the first and the largest youth festival with a thematic focus in Serbia. eYouwins is dedicated to youth in Serbia, Europe and worldwide, and its mission is to promote the spirit of cooperation, to link cultures, ideas and, above all, people. Festival has started in 2006 and in short time has gained popularity among young people all over Europe. During the last four years more than 5000 young people were involved in the Festival events and almost 400 guests from 25 countries visited Novi Sad and Serbia.</p>\n<p>In 2010 eYouwins celebrates 5th birthday and invites 150 participants to come to Novi Sad, between 17th and 24th August; to focus on green ways of life and sustainable development of our society. Therefore, this year eYouwins is greenWins.<br />\nProgram of the greenWins is structured as a combination of three elements: education, action and fun.<br />\nEducational part of greenWins will be composed of lectures and workshops. The main part of the thematic work of greenWins will be the group work on different topics organized in six different workshops which highlight the Festival theme from various aspects. The second segment of greenWins is Action. In this segment, participants will be directly involved in actions related to Festival topic, practicing ecological habits and raising awareness in Novi Sad and its surrounding. Finally, third segment of the Festival, Fun, covers activities relating to art, music and sport. Traditional Youth Carnival during Festival weekend will bring interesting concerts and dance performances organized for participants, citizens and other visitors of Novi Sad.</p>\n<p>Planned workshops<br />\nWS1  reCycle it! (what, how &amp; where to recycle)<br />\nWS2  Art of Waste (creative reuse of waste)<br />\nWS3  Blue Gold (Water Scarcity )<br />\nWS4  Ecology Hotspots (mapping ecology problems)<br />\nWS5Energy (R)evolution (managing energy resources)<br />\nWS6  Changing Clime (climate change)</p>\n<p>Participation fee for greenWins is 60 EURO for international participants and 3000 Dinars for the participants from Serbia.<br />\nThe participation fee covers accommodation, and meals during the Festival (light breakfast, lunch and dinner per day), organised excursions, sightseeing, entrance fees, and free participation in trips, conference programme, cultural and sport events of the Festival.<br />\nIn participants fee is not included travel costs and personal expenses!!!<br />\nAccepted participants will pay the participants fee on arrival, at the registration. If you want to take a part in the Festival fill the registration form as earlier as you can!!!</p>\n<p>Application deadline is 15th July 20010!!</p>\n<p>For more information on the festival please visit our website at: <a href="http://eyouwins.com/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://eyouwins.com'']);">http://eyouwins.com</a></p>\n<p>Should you have any questions, please do not hesitate to contact me at any time!</p>\n<p>We hope to see you in Novi Sad!!!</p>\n', 'greenWins 2010', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '2315-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 00:39:28', '2013-11-22 00:39:28', '', 2315, 'http://localhost/GITinternational/eestec.portal-2/?p=3930', 0, 'revision', '', 0, 0),
