(2232, 1, '2012-12-24 16:23:55', '2012-12-24 15:23:55', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>As engineers, we like games. We actually love the challenges they demand us for winning them. Just recall the last time you discovered that so catchy one that almost drove you nuts because of the tangled rules you had to comprehend in order to focus on the strategies for conquering another level. Wasnt it simpler if you could rather center your attention at the creative side of things than on the frustrating part of reinventing the wheel ?</p>\n<p>Like so in our engineering field. Technology evolves and so do we. New issues need new approaches, particularly straightforward ones. Here, at EESTEC LC Craiova, we use to mock our so frequently low on RAM laptops by advising their owners to water the faint hamster endlessly rolling the wheel J . Would you buy it if we threw on the market a snake that, as it does with living food, makes you readily eat the principles at once leaving your attention open on the so important side of quickly solving your tasks without worrying about those aforementioned tangled rules ?</p>\n<p>Then let the PYTHON byte you ! Youll never have to worry about type declarations, semicolons or brackets. Just plain indentation. Getting rid of all that annoying clutter makes code clean and understandable for you and others. Easy life, on the short hand. Its name comes, as you might not think, from a movie, Guido van Rossum, who invented it in 1991, being inspired from &#8220;Monty Python&#8217;s Flying Circus&#8221;, a BBC comedy series from the 1970s.</p>\n<p>Become a PYTHONian ! Learn the basics and prepare for Twisted, Pyjamas, SQLAlchemy and many other toolkits and frameworks available for any of your platform independent scripting or programing needs, may it be web, databases or operating systems related. These might have funny names, but Python is so powerful that even Google and Facebook use it !</p>\n<p>Join our early spring trainings starting on 24th of March, lasting till 30th, reborn together with nature with all new programming skills, have fun with us coding the days and partying the nights along with our all around the world famous music and Romanian hospitality and wonder yourself why didnt you come to this earlier.</p>\n<p>Discover PYTHONIA ! And your imagination gets code wings. *The only boring part is the Hello, world! one.</p>\n', 'Pythonia', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'pythonia', '', '', '2012-12-24 16:23:55', '2012-12-24 15:23:55', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/pythonia/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2233, 1, '2012-12-24 16:09:55', '2012-12-24 15:09:55', '<span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Hello dear EESTEC-ers, LC East Sarajevo is back! We are proud to present you Jahorina Spring Break 2013, unforgettable event that will take place from 19th to 26th of March 2013.\r\nAcademic part will be held on Jahorina (our Olympic mountain), where International Scientific Symposium  Infoteh 2013 will take place. You will have opportunity to listen lectures from the experts, scientists, engineers, researchers and students that deal with information technologies. We provided hotel accommodation for our participants, transport to Infoteh and back.</span>\r\n\r\nNon academic part will be quite hedonistic and relaxed, but full of various activities, such as swimming, bowlingor just lazy sitting in pub and drinking beer/coffee/juice/rakija/whatever\r\nWe will also visit Orlovaca cave and beautiful well of Bosna river. Sightseeing and visiting city landmarks are also part of the program. During these 7 days you will taste our traditional food and drinks. We will organize traditional Serbian night with our live music, and people dressed in traditional Serbian clothes.\r\n\r\nAnd at the end, thing that you are waiting the most.YES! Parties will be every night on various places!\r\n\r\nAs you could see, this is a life time opportunity. Millions of people would kill for it, so dont hesitate to apply! <img class="wp-smiley" alt=":)" src="http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" />\r\n\r\nSee you in East Sarajevo!<span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #888888;"><br clear="all" /> </span></span>', 'Jahorina Spring Break 2013', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'jahorina-spring-break-2013', '', '', '2013-04-01 19:40:03', '2013-04-01 18:40:03', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/jahorina-spring-break-2013/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2234, 1, '2012-10-20 19:52:11', '2012-10-20 18:52:11', 'Dear EESTECers,\r\n\r\nLets fast forward a little bit through the time, not very far in the future, but some where in the middle of December 2012.\r\n\r\nSuddenly you find yourself in a hotel room, with an open suitcase right in front of you. As youre packing your bags and apparently getting ready to head home, you wonder yourself: Why am I constantly smiling and feeling happy? And even though I am trying, I still cant remove this distinct happy expression off my face Oh, it is simple, almost two months ago by joining the event Code App, level up by LC Skopje you made your best decision this year.\r\nOK, press the Stop button, lets go back to the beginning, why did you click that APPly button!?\r\n\r\nThe almost radical growth of the world-wide smartphone community consequently affects the growth of need for mobile applications. These factors are opening new windows of possibilities for exploiting that market by the programmers from all around the world. Thats why LC Skopje is hosting a week of quality trainings and place where you will be able to implement your gained knowledge and creativity into practical work. Code App, level up is a workshop that through courses will bring you close to this programming field and will create a chance to code real applications for real clients. Level UP yourself!\r\n\r\nBut its not all about coding!(<a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.youtube.com'']);" href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ltjT25GyXTM" target="_blank">?</a>) All of you PARTYcipants just prepare to get to know with the famous Macedonian hospitality. By rallying our capital, the city of Skopje, you will experience the unique fusion of the West with the Orient. You will have taste of our <a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.youtube.com'']);" href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CRgLmCQzEAo" target="_blank">extraordinary cuisine</a> and for sure you will enjoy the Lozova Rakija that will keep you warm in the long nights of December. But wait until you experience the rich nightlife Skopje is offering and you wont be asking for anything else\r\n\r\nSo all of you programmers on the EESTEC network, dont hesitate, make your future you smiling like crazy on the 15<sup>th</sup> of December. <a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://eestec.net'']);" href="http://eestec.net/lc/skopje/code-app-level-up" target="_blank">Join a hell of a coding party</a>', 'Code App, level Up!', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'code-app-level-up', '', '', '2013-03-01 22:40:27', '2013-03-01 21:40:27', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/code-app-level-up/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2235, 1, '2012-10-12 18:12:44', '2012-10-12 17:12:44', '\n<p><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><strong>Explo<span style="color: #ff0000;">RED</span>Planet</strong></span></p>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Mission of workshop</span>: Finding out about space exploration with a spotlight on &#8220;Mars Science Laboratory&#8221;&#8230;</p>\n<div><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><br />\n</span></div>\n<div><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="color: #222222;">Dear </span><strong><span style="color: #cc0000;">RED</span></strong><span style="color: #222222;"> people,</span></span></span><span style="color: #222222;">We are thrilled to announce that this workshop will be one giant leap for an eestec-kind in space exploration. The focus will be on the Red Planet and the latest mission related to it, which is called <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BudlaGh1A0o&amp;feature=plcp" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.youtube.com'']);" target="_blank">&#8220;Mars Science Laboratory&#8221;</a>.</span></p>\n<p><span style="color: #222222;">The idea is to give you a closer look to the technological aspects of Curiosity rover which<a href="http://mars.jpl.nasa.gov/msl/mission/overview/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://mars.jpl.nasa.gov'']);" target="_blank"> landed on Mars in August 2012</a>. Part of the lectures and practical part will be devoted to the study of this <a href="http://mars.jpl.nasa.gov/msl/mission/rover/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://mars.jpl.nasa.gov'']);" target="_blank">rover</a> as a robot that operates in specific conditions. The main fields are the power and energy efficiency of the robot, the materials from which is made, how it is communicating with the base on the Earth and other telecommunications devices which is equipped with. You will also find out about history of space research and technology that made this possible. Therefore, this will be an exciting week for astronomy lovers and inquisitive engineers.</span></p>\n<p><span style="color: #222222;">As we never forget about eestec spirit, you will have enough time to discover all the beauties of <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QJsvxsViG_k&amp;feature=related" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.youtube.com'']);" target="_blank">our capital</a> and to get to know with its nightlife. Over here, every day is treated as Friday, in regard of fun. When you add theme parties which we are planing for you, then Belgrade is definitely <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OtQywygjdfc" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.youtube.com'']);" target="_blank">&#8220;the-place-to-be&#8221;</a> this winter. You will also have the chance to spend a few days out of the city and experience admirable landscapes and attractive nature in the country with reach legacy in history and art, among <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wIwNwZwNXuA" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.youtube.com'']);" target="_blank">abundant kitchen and warm hospitality</a>.</span></p>\n<p><span style="color: #222222;">Having so many things left for your amazement, we invite you to follow your curiosity and participate in this excellent workshop we are preparing for you.</span></p>\n<p><span style="color: #222222;">Sincerely,</span></p>\n</div>\n', 'ExploRED Planet', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'explored-planet', '', '', '2012-10-12 18:12:44', '2012-10-12 17:12:44', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/explored-planet/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2236, 1, '2012-09-21 19:57:59', '2012-09-21 18:57:59', 'Dear EESTECers,\r\n\r\nwe are announcing our 4th International Motivational Weekend, happening between the 9th and 11th of November 2012.\r\n\r\nWere bringing the participants of our workshop Bad cars gone electric 2 there as a conclusion to a great event and were going to have soft-skills trainings during the day, followed by even more awesome theme parties to keep us up till early morning.\r\n\r\nThe event includes accommodation, transport from Ljubljana, 3 meals a day and free theme parties. At the IMW we will be accompanied by members of other associations, so we definitely need all of you to join us and show them them our EESTEC spirit.\r\n\r\nThe venue is the same as last year and year before that, Kranjska Gora, where you can enjoy our beautiful countryside.\r\n\r\nAnd remember, the best way to participate at the IMW is to apply for our workshop!\r\n\r\nIf you are still in doubt about whether to come or not, ask anyone that has ever participated in an IMW to tell you about it.\r\n\r\nWe promise you wont regret it for a second!\r\n\r\nSee you there!\r\n\r\nP.S. For more information regarding the event please contact <a href="mailto:demjan.vester@eestec-lj.org" target="_blank">demjan.vester@eestec-lj.org</a>', 'International Motivational Weekend 2012', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'international-motivational-weekend-2012', '', '', '2013-03-01 02:48:14', '2013-03-01 01:48:14', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/international-motivational-weekend-2012/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2237, 1, '2012-09-05 09:14:49', '2012-09-05 08:14:49', '<a href="http://bcge2.eestec-lj.org"><img class="alignleft  wp-image-1742" title="Bad Cars Gone Electric 2" alt="" src="http://eestec-lj.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/logo1.png" width="570" height="70" /></a>\r\n\r\nDear EESTECers,\r\n\r\nyou may stop worrying now!\r\n\r\nLC Ljubljana is proud to announce this years workshop, a continuation of last years amazing electrically powered adventure. Yes, weve upgraded the concept and invite you to a more awesome, more sophisticated <a href="http://bcge2.eestec-lj.org/" target="_blank">Bad Cars Gone Electric 2</a>!\r\n\r\nWe invite you to join us from the 3rd (arrival day) to the 11th (departure day) of November 2012 for another unforgettable EESTEC experience brought to you by LC Ljubljana.\r\n\r\n<strong>What is the topic?</strong>\r\n\r\nThe topic of the workshop will once more be electric cars, so were going to spend the week learning about how they work, general implementation into the current infrastructure, obstacles industries are facing for instance recycling, efficient energy usage, the batteries etc\r\nWell also talk about clean energy, specifically solar power, where some experts from both fields will explain the areas that the media sometimes doesnt want to talk about. Is the field of clean energy a black/white or yes/no topic? Is there a best clean energy? Can any of them replace fossil fuel permanently and sustainably?\r\n\r\nBut lectures arent the only thing on the schedule. If the topic are electric cars, why not just make some of our own? Well we will!\r\nAbout half of the academic part will be spent building electric cars from scratch (But in a fun, relaxed and amusing way).\r\n\r\n<strong>What else is in it?</strong>\r\n\r\nDo you know what EESTEC Spirit is? What makes a true EESTECer?\r\n\r\nWell we do!\r\n\r\nAnd you get a wonderful opportunity to visit the very place we breed true EESTECers: <a href="http://bcge2.eestec-lj.org/city/" target="_blank">Ljubljana, our beautiful city</a>, where you will see what makes an EESTECer full of energy, tireless and awesome at all times!\r\n\r\nThere will also be a surprise trip in the middle of the workshop, where you will be able to relax and breathe in some fresh air.\r\n\r\n<strong>Is that all?</strong>\r\n\r\nIts still not over\r\n\r\nWe dont just end our events like that, we end them in style!\r\n\r\nSo you arent just coming to participate in our workshop, you are coming to participate at our International Motivational Weekend as well.\r\nTaking place the final weekend of the event, this is one of the largest EESTEC events organized each year, where we gather in the countryside to network, socialize and participate in soft-skills trainings.\r\n\r\nAll of this, free of charge for our participants!\r\n\r\nThere is really nothing more to add, except that places will fill up fast, and we have a limited amount\r\n\r\nApply now!', 'Bad Cars Gone Electric 2', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'bad-cars-gone-electric-2', '', '', '2013-03-01 22:45:50', '2013-03-01 21:45:50', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/bad-cars-gone-electric-2/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2238, 1, '2012-08-29 16:54:36', '2012-08-29 15:54:36', '\n<p>Hello dear EESTECers!</p>\n<p>Have you ever wondered how green energy is made? Or especially bright and green solar energy? How does it work ? And why its the best alternative energy? How is it implemented in our nearby environment? If the answer is yes, yes and YES! Then its solar time in LC NOVI SAD!</p>\n<p>We will take you through the best journey of your green life.</p>\n<p>On the lectures, we are going to learn more about alternative energy and especially solar energy: how it is implemented, what technology is behind it and see it in use &#8211; generating clean Watts right on the spot, at our Faculty of Technical Sciences. The same group of people who created our small photovoltaic power plant CRESPQ, are the ones who will be holding the lectures for you.</p>\n<p>With all this in mind there&#8217;s nothing other left for you to do but to apply, hopefully start packing and get ready to soak up the Sun!</p>\n<p>Once you arrive, you will be welcomed to Novi Sad, a city that merges the north and the south, that unites the east with the west. Novi Sad (also known as:  , Neoplanta, Neusatz, jvidk, Nov Sad) has a rich history that dwells around our beautiful and world wide known Petrovaradin fortress overlooking the Danube.</p>\n<p>Check out these galleries to get to know YOUR future home city better:</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DG7T1cQsJrI" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.youtube.com'']);" target="_blank">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DG7T1cQsJrI</a></p>\n<p><a href="http://www.novisad.rs/eng/petrovaradin-fortress-7" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.novisad.rs'']);" target="_blank">http://www.novisad.rs/eng/petrovaradin-fortress-7</a></p>\n<p><a href="http://www.novisad.rs/eng/novi-sad-2" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.novisad.rs'']);" target="_blank">http://www.novisad.rs/eng/novi-sad-2</a></p>\n<p><a href="http://www.novisad.rs/eng/streets-novi-sad" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.novisad.rs'']);" target="_blank">http://www.novisad.rs/eng/streets-novi-sad</a></p>\n<p>But dont think that&#8217;s all there is. Not only do we have a great history and picturesque streets, but also a rich and vibrant night scene, which you will discover along with fellow EESTECers, and patry hard until the sunrise!</p>\n<p>See you with the sunrise!</p>\n', 'It&#8217;s solar time!', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'its-solar-time', '', '', '2012-08-29 16:54:36', '2012-08-29 15:54:36', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/its-solar-time/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2239, 1, '2012-08-29 14:42:15', '2012-08-29 13:42:15', '<strong>What is the EESTEC Training Team? What are Trainings?</strong>\r\n\r\nEESTEC Training Team is an official EESTEC body which is providing different services for EESTEC and through those services, based on trainings, constantly improving the work of EESTEC on international and local levels!\r\n\r\nMain goal of trainings is transfer of knowledge in an advanced way through different activities, techniques and methodologies.\r\n\r\nMore information about the Training Team, Training System and Trainings you can find in the Official Training Team Document <a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://eestec.net'']);" href="http://eestec.net/lc/workspaces/training-team/training-material/Training%20Team%20Official%20documents/1st%20Official%20Training%20Team%20Document.pdf/view?searchterm=training%20document" target="_blank">here</a>.\r\n\r\n<strong>What is T4T? Why is T4T being organized?</strong>\r\n\r\nT4T  Training for Trainers is an international training event whose purpose is gaining new EESTEC trainers and it is the starting point for EESTECers to become a trainer.\r\n\r\nEESTECers which participate in T4T will go through intensive trainings, working sessions and practical parts and learn how to transfer knowledge, which methodologies to use and, very important, how to deliver trainings!\r\n\r\nAs the transfer of knowledge is crucial for EESTEC, T4T is an event which assures new generations to continue with developing and providing Training Team services to EESTEC members. It is a stage through all Training team members have to go in order to gain different soft skills like: leadership skills, presentation skills, communication skills and much more!\r\n\r\nUsing these skills for transferring knowledge in EESTEC provides greater quality of different activities which are being organized in International and local levels.\r\n\r\nDuring T4T, 9 days of a lot of work is waiting for you so you will need to bring <strong>a lot of positive energy</strong> and <strong>enthusiasm</strong> in order to be effective all the time and to be able to endure the T4T.\r\n\r\n<strong>Why become a Trainer? Why should you apply?</strong>\r\n\r\nThere are definitely a lot of reasons to apply. Becoming a trainer gives you an opportunity to contribute to EESTEC International, to contribute to LCs and to contribute to yourselves!\r\n\r\nAs a trainer candidate (and optionally trainer) you will work in and create a positive atmosphere during T4T and after. If you become a trainer (for what you need to fulfill certain tasks) you will work on the transfer of knowledge to other EESTECers and you will have an opportunity to improve on personal level in different aspects.\r\n\r\nThe skills you gain while being a trainer are needed in all aspects of life today and so in EESTEC. Because of that, members who participate in T4Thave a big opportunity to develop themselves and to give a great contribution to the development of EESTEC!\r\n\r\n<strong>Organizing Committee LC Istanbul</strong>\r\n\r\nLC Istanbul is very proud to organize such an important EESTEC international event  the 5th Training for Trainers!\r\n\r\nThis will be the first event of many for us in this academic year. So we are eagerly looking forward to offer the famous Turkish hospitality to our motivated participants and preparations are nearly complete to entertain you in this historical, amazing and spectacular city of stanbul. Please dont hesitate to apply!\r\n\r\nSee you in Istanbul, very soon <img class="wp-smiley" alt=":)" src="http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" />\r\n\r\nA Short Movie about city : <a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://goo.gl'']);" href="http://goo.gl/Sl4RZ" target="_blank">http://goo.gl/Sl4RZ</a>\r\nApplication form: *** <a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://eestec.net'']);" href="http://eestec.net/publications/cp-area/forms/t4t-application-form" target="_blank">here</a> ***\r\nSend motivational letter to: <a href="mailto:trainings-coordinator@eestec.net" target="_blank">trainings-coordinator@eestec.net</a>', 'The 5th Training for Trainers  T4T', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'the-5th-training-for-trainers-t4t', '', '', '2013-03-01 22:49:49', '2013-03-01 21:49:49', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/the-5th-training-for-trainers-t4t/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2240, 1, '2012-08-29 14:24:47', '2012-08-29 13:24:47', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>We are proud to announce the 7th EESTEC Chairperson Meeting which will be held in <strong>Lisbon, Portugal from November 18th 2012 until 25th</strong>. The registration period is now open and so until the <strong>September 30th</strong>.<br />\nEach LC, JLC and Observer have a right for <strong>1 (one)</strong> place on ECM!</p>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>What is the main goal of this years ECM?</strong></span><br />\nInternational Board is focused on raising academic level in EESTEC, as well as improving communication between LCs. Based on this, main part of ECM will be educating members about International projects and the possibility for their contribution in these projects. Participants will have the chance to attend one or more sessions, where they can learn about projects and contribute to them. Sessions outcomes will be presented at the end of the ECM.</p>\n<p>Besides sessions, we will have soft skills trainings, where participants will have chance to improve their communication, project management and knowledge transfer in LCs.</p>\n<p>Based on the success of the General Meeting last ECM, International Board decided to have General Meeting this year. We will discuss about current Rules of Procedure, Board report and the progress of projects.</p>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>What will be done in ECM?</strong></span><br />\nWe will have the following sessions:<br />\n- FR session<br />\n- External cooperations<br />\n- Observer guidance session<br />\n- PR guide session<br />\n- Rules of Procedure session<br />\n- IT session<br />\n- Conference project session<br />\n- Design session<br />\n- Trainings</p>\n<p>Trainings that will be delivered on ECM are following:<br />\n- Project management<br />\n- Handover training<br />\n- Board training<br />\n- International awareness<br />\n- International FR training</p>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>What will be the profile of participants in ECM?</strong></span><br />\nConsidering the aim of this ECM and the fact that there should be one participant per LC, the chairperson should attend the ECM, however if its not possible for the chairperson to attend, one of the experienced member should take the delegation.<br />\nLC representation is of the highest importance as focus will be on the working sessions. JLC and Observer representations are also important, and for them focus will be on the training sessions.</p>\n<p>Important!!! Dont miss the deadline for registration: <strong>30th of September! Link for registration</strong>: <a href="http://eestec.net/lc/lisbon/7th-eestec-chairpersons-meeting-lisbon" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://eestec.net'']);" target="_blank">http://eestec.net/lc/lisbon/7th-eestec-chairpersons-meeting-lisbon</a></p>\n<p>We cannot wait for your registration and we are eager to welcome you all in the beautiful city of Lisbon!</p>\n<p>Best regards on behalf of International Board and LC Lisbon!</p>\n', '7th EESTEC Chairperson Meeting', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', '7th-eestec-chairperson-meeting', '', '', '2012-08-29 14:24:47', '2012-08-29 13:24:47', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/7th-eestec-chairperson-meeting/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2241, 1, '2012-08-29 13:36:20', '2012-08-29 12:36:20', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>We were penguins last year and what about this one?</p>\n<p>Isnt the time to expand our horizons and look in the sky? We think it is.:)</p>\n<p>So, after the last year exciting and successful workshop it is both our honor and a privilege to announce this years on topic of Inertial Navigation Systems or as we like to call it &#8211; <strong>INSoBLia</strong> (<strong>I</strong>nertial <strong>N</strong>avigation <strong>S</strong>ystems <strong>O</strong>ctober 2012<strong>B</strong>anja <strong>L</strong>uka <strong>I</strong>n <strong>A</strong>ir) <span style="color: #ff0000;"><strong>from 21st until 27th October</strong></span>.</p>\n<p>First two days of lectures will cover the basics of flying from historical, technical and licensing point of view. Later on, we will get into serious technical details of the navigation systems that aircrafts are using. In the afternoons, we will be paying visits to the nearby airport, aero club and the helicopter service. By visiting these places, you will be able to see how theory is applied in practice.</p>\n<p>As always, one day in our beautiful city is reserved for exciting rafting on our beauty Vrbas where the European Championship 2005, Euro Cup 2007 and World Championship 2009 had been hosted.</p>\n<p>Already sounds interesting? Well, we are not done!</p>\n<p>The highlight of the week is your practical work in our laboratory for electronics. After attending lectures and hearing about inertial navigation systems, you will be able to make one! You&#8217;ll get to play around with accelerometers and microcontrollers, the actual components of an inertial navigation system. Of course, since the workshop focuses on the INS, it is required that you are already familiar with the basic concepts of a microcontroller and here is a site that could help: <a href="http://mucrofe.blogspot.com/2011/03/basic-concept.html" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://mucrofe.blogspot.com'']);" target="_blank">http://mucrofe.blogspot.com/2011/03/basic-concept.html</a>.</p>\n<p>Apart of the lectures, visits, and playing in laboratory, youll get to know our city, delicious and traditional meals and of course Banja Lukas well known night life.</p>\n<p>Do not hesitate, apply now! <strong>LC Banja Luka is waiting for YOU!</strong></p>\n', 'INSoBLia', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'insoblia', '', '', '2012-08-29 13:36:20', '2012-08-29 12:36:20', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/insoblia/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2242, 1, '2012-08-25 17:54:23', '2012-08-25 16:54:23', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>We are proud to announce a long waited and great Summer School organized by EESTEC, Medical Engineering Association and European Medical Students Association!</p>\n<p>Apart from the topic of the event, it is the very first time EESTEC is co-organizing an event like this, and if it succeeds it can become a new trend that adds even more diversity and quality to our already wide event ecosystem. So we encourage you to consider it, not only for the event itself, but for the opportunity it means for all.</p>\n<p>In TIME, you will have the opportunity to take part in scientific lectures and workshops, both medical and engineering. The topics are diversified, from biomaterials, medical imaging to robotic surgery and pharmacogenomics. You may share your knowledge and experience and find the new discoveries and challenges in medical engineering field.</p>\n<p>Let&#8217;s not forget, you will meet students from all over the Europe interested in the interdisciplinary field of medicine and engineering, in an unique Romanian cultural environment.</p>\n<p>The participation fees are the following:<br />\n50  for participants who want accommodation and meals<br />\n5  for participants who are from Timisoara, and for those who don&#8217;t want accomodation and meals<br />\nWe are sure you don&#8217;t want to miss this last summer event and unique chance to make history in EESTEC. Submit your CV and a motivation letter at <a href="mailto:summeschool@mea-edu.ro" target="_blank">summeschool@mea-edu.ro</a>, until 10th of September 2012.</p>\n<p>For more information:</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.summerschool.mea-edu.ro" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.summerschool.mea-edu.ro'']);" target="_blank">http://www.summerschool.mea-edu.ro</a></p>\n', 'TIME &#8211; Timisoara International Medical Engineering Summer School', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'time-timisoara-international-medical-engineering-summer-school', '', '', '2012-08-25 17:54:23', '2012-08-25 16:54:23', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/time-timisoara-international-medical-engineering-summer-school/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2243, 1, '2012-07-31 11:35:15', '2012-07-31 10:35:15', 'Dear EESTECers,\r\n\r\nLC Munich/Awesome is proud to announce the <strong>Oktoberfest Exchange</strong> 2012 from <strong>October 1st</strong> until <strong>October 7th</strong>.\r\nYou will have the honor of drinking the worlds finest beer in the worlds finest city with the most sophisticated soon-to-be engineers in Europe.\r\n\r\nBesides all these tempting facts we are also planning a cultural program, a City-Rally, sightseeing, and clubbing. There wont be any lectures, however plenty of entertainment during your stay in Munich is guaranteed.\r\n\r\nSince hostel prices are ridiculous during Oktoberfest, we will be accommodating you privately. Unfortunately we have to ask for a <strong>participation fee of 100</strong>. This includes meals, local transportation and some entry fees. We have to warn you though, Munich is generally an expensive place during Oktoberfest. A liter of beer is<strong> 9.10 to 9.50</strong>! But as usual, everything except for drinks is included for our participants. No need to worry, we will not be spending the entire week at Oktoberfest itself, and you will have a lot of chances to get cheaper beer! <img class="wp-smiley" alt=":)" src="http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" />\r\n\r\n<strong>This is a once in a lifetime chance to experience Oktoberfest at such affordable prices!</strong>\r\n\r\nAgain, this is the opportunity of your life to enjoy the worlds biggest beer festival (and party) with your fellow EESTECers! We strongly encourage you to apply! <img class="wp-smiley" alt=":)" src="http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" />\r\n\r\nP.S. Loving beer is a must <img class="wp-smiley" alt=";)" src="http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" />\r\n\r\nSee you in Munich,', 'Oktoberfest Exchange 2012', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'oktoberfest-exchange-2012', '', '', '2013-03-01 22:46:01', '2013-03-01 21:46:01', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/oktoberfest-exchange-2012/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2244, 1, '2012-06-21 13:48:17', '2012-06-21 12:48:17', '\n<p>Dear EESTEC-ers,</p>\n<p>We can proudly invite you to our traditional event <span style="color: #ff0000;"><strong>JAZZ DO IT!</strong></span> . Since it was great all years before, we&#8217;re making it again! That&#8217;s why we are asking you to join us at the biggest jazz event in Southern and Eastern Europe <strong><a href="http://www.nisville.com/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.nisville.com'']);" target="_blank">&#8220;Niville jazz festival&#8221;</a></strong>. Together we will enjoy the good jazz sound accompanied with great atmosphere that only EESTEC exchange can provide. Organized in the medieval <a href="http://img704.imageshack.us/img704/1240/centar.jpg" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://img704.imageshack.us'']);" target="_blank">fortress</a> and visited by more than <strong>100.000 people</strong> only last year, Niville hosted some of the biggest stars of jazz music: Steve Hans and Candy Dulfer, Grace Kelly Band, Incognito, Solomon Burke, Benny Golson, De Phazz, Roy Hargrove, Sly&amp;Robbie, Mungo Jerry, Tom Harrell&#8230; This year there is no exception because Lollo Meier Quartet, Get The Blessing, Tacuma &amp; Joseph Bowie Defunkt Funk Expirience, Opus 5, Maria Joao, David Linx, Brussels Jazz Orchestra and 50 other bands on 5 different stages will jazz it up for us!</p>\n<p>Regular price for this festival is about 50 Euros, but as our guest you are getting it for <strong>free</strong> <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n<p>And you will also learn some things about acoustics and making music.</p>\n<p>But, thats not all. The City of Ni has great cultural and historical heritage. Serbia is birthplace of 17 Roman emperors, and one of the most important persons in European history, emperor <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Constantine_the_Great" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://en.wikipedia.org'']);" target="_blank">Constantine the Great</a>, was born in Ni (roman name <strong>NAISSUS</strong>) in 272AD.</p>\n<p>You will also visit a <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ni_Fortress" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://en.wikipedia.org'']);" target="_blank">Fortress of Ni</a>, where Niville jazz festival takes place. The fortress exists at this place for more than 2000 years, and has layers from different historical periods. Thats because Ni is on the road that connects Europe with Middle East (in roman times this road was called VIA MILITARIS), so many civilizations passed here and they left some trace in the fortress. Its in this condition since XVII century, and now its one of the best preserved fortifications of Ottoman style in Europe.</p>\n<p>In Ni exists one unique monument in the world, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Skull_Tower" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://en.wikipedia.org'']);" target="_blank">Skull Tower</a>, which was built from skulls of the warriors who died in the egar battle in the 1809. You will also visit a <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_of_egar" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://en.wikipedia.org'']);" target="_blank">egar monument</a> where this battle took place.</p>\n<p>Well show you one relaxing place, <a href="http://www.nistourism.org.rs/health-oasis.html" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.nistourism.org.rs'']);" target="_blank">Nika Banja</a> spa which has radioactive healing water and well go swimming there with a lot of EESTEC spirit!</p>\n<p>And if you think that we only have history, youre wrong, because Ni is known as town where you can have a lot of fun. We have centuries old hedonist legacy! Are you brave enough to try our traditional drink <strong>rakija</strong>? And the best BBQ in the world including pljeskavica will help your body to work well with all that alcohol. There wont be a single moment that youll be hungry, because Serbians like good food in big quantities. All that you will be able to taste in a traditional ambient at the special night in <strong>kafana</strong>. If you dont know what <strong>merak</strong> is (that word has no translation to other languages), you will learn here!</p>\n<p>So the crazy summer cocktail with&#8230; traditional Serbian drinks and food plenty of great music nice town a lot of EESTEC spirit Mix all that in a summer temperature and share it with good orgaNICEers.</p>\n<p>What are you waiting for?</p>\n<p><strong><span style="color: #ff0000;">JAZZ DO IT!</span></strong></p>\n', 'Jazz do it! 2012', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'jazz-do-it-2012', '', '', '2012-06-21 13:48:17', '2012-06-21 12:48:17', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/jazz-do-it-2012/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2245, 1, '2012-06-19 16:15:57', '2012-06-19 15:15:57', 'We promise to offer you the best Summer School ever, if you are brave enough to risk spending a week in summer LEARNING! EESTECers will have the opportunity to attend a high quality academic event combined with the awesome EESTEC Spirit. You will have the chance to get in touch with top expertise speakers and participants.\r\n\r\nThe School will have two main topics: <strong>Graphic Design and Web development</strong>, each with its own classes schedule. In addition there will also be a common schedule, to let participants work in <strong>teams</strong> and be involved in innovative and constructive challenges.\r\n\r\nWe are also planning a competition between teams of 5, picked randomly from both designers and developers. The winning team <strong>will of course be awarded</strong> <img class="wp-smiley" alt=";-)" src="http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" />\r\n\r\nOn Saturday you will all attend a very special photography class No more details  it is a surprise!\r\n\r\nWe will work hard, but we will have fun too! No worries about thisyou will be in Italy, DONT FORGET IT!\r\n\r\nFor more details visit our website <a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://ts.eestec.it'']);" href="http://ts.eestec.it/ess/" target="_blank">http://ts.eestec.it/ess/</a>\r\n\r\nPresentation event: <a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://ts.eestec.it'']);" href="http://ts.eestec.it/ess/eestec-summer-school-presentation/" target="_blank">http://ts.eestec.it/ess/eestec-summer-school-presentation/</a>\r\n\r\nSummer School program: <a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://ts.eestec.it'']);" href="http://ts.eestec.it/ess/ess-program/" target="_blank">http://ts.eestec.it/ess/ess-program/</a>\r\n\r\nWe hope to see you all in Trieste! <img class="wp-smiley" alt=":)" src="http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" />\r\n\r\nGreetings from LC Trieste!', '1st EESTEC Summer School 2012 Graphic Design & Web Development', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', '1st-eestec-summer-school-2012-graphic-design-web-development', '', '', '2013-03-01 22:51:21', '2013-03-01 21:51:21', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/1st-eestec-summer-school-2012-graphic-design-web-development/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2246, 1, '2012-06-13 16:17:45', '2012-06-13 15:17:45', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>Last summer, we moved some boundaries of EESTEC events and we made one epic event. But this summer be prepared for more&#8230;.double the action, triple the excitement&#8230; and more of the excitement&#8230;be prepared to <strong>Cross the Line</strong> with LC Podgorica.</p>\n<p>We offer you 7 days of unforgettable atmosphere, 7 days of EESTEC spirit, 7 days and seven nights of our parties and memories for a lifetime.</p>\n<p>We will spend 7 days in Kotor, one of the most beautiful cities on Montenegrin coast (UNESCO protected) . You will be able to experience Mediterranean spirit, see one of the most beautiful bays in Europe during the cruise that we will organize around Boka bay. But the most important thing is the Kotor Carnival, one of the biggest and craziest carnivals in Europe. We plan to appear as a group mask, and the theme of our mask is secret for now <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif'' alt='';)'' class=''wp-smiley'' />  .</p>\n<p>This event will also have an educational part. Considering that you are probably tired of engineering, we decided to make a workshop on photography, journalism and filmmaking. You will be able to choose one of those three and show your creativity. Beside of this we will organize workshop where we will design our performance for carnival.</p>\n<p>Priority will be given to those who write a motivation letter, or those who make a motivational video and show us EESTEC spirit, good energy and creativity. Also if you have some special talents or motivation your are more than welcome to express them and you will get bonus points for that.</p>\n<p><strong>Important notice</strong></p>\n<p>If you want an ordinary summer or you consider yourself as non creative or boring person, <strong>DO NOT APPLY</strong> for this event <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n', 'Cross the line', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'cross-the-line', '', '', '2012-06-13 16:17:45', '2012-06-13 15:17:45', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/cross-the-line/', 0, 'events', '', 0);
