(2247, 1, '2012-06-08 11:44:50', '2012-06-08 10:44:50', '\n<p>Let me ask you this, you want to go on a vacation this summer but youre still wondering where? Let me tell you this, it is not late, it is the best time for wondering.</p>\n<p>An idea pops out in your head, having an EESTEC vacation?!?<br />\nYou are scratching your head saying naah, where would you find that kind of thing? Those guys rock and those ladies jazz. That would be awesome, but is there something like EESTEC vacation?!?</p>\n<p>Well guess what, there is!<br />\nBring on your spirit and become a fellow EESTECer with that wild crew from LC Skopje. Have the summer of your life, while round trippin their country.<br />\nAnd you know what you are already accepted; because this is not exchange, it&#8217;s a vacation, everybody is accepted. We provide all the logistics and planning of this awesome vacation, but we can not provide the accommodation and the food.</p>\n<p>Our plan is to show you our country, every day different dish, every day different club, every day different kafana, every day different breathtaking sights. We will visit 5 cities that will show you why do we love to live here, and reminding you that when the day ends the games may begin!</p>\n<p>The trip goes like this &#8211; 2 days in Skopje, 2 days on Tikves Lake (with one stop on the way in the town called Veles to eat tasty pastrmajlija (the grandma of the Italian pizza)), 1 day in Bitola and 5 days in Ohrid. During this holiday will be touring you showing off with our nature, being proud of our history, architecture and culture all in all days to remember, and nights even more or not. We will be visiting (the schedule is in the link below):</p>\n<p>Skopje:</p>\n<p>The Old Bazar, this is something, time-travel to the middle ages in our Charshija:<br />\n<a href="http://tinyurl.com/6cfmyy6" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://tinyurl.com'']);" target="_blank">http://tinyurl.com/6cfmyy6</a></p>\n<p>The Biggest Cross in the world on the top of mount Vodno. Have a cup of coffee on the top of the mountain with a view of the whole Skopje area. Also the biggest statue of Alexander the Great in the world and its fountain below:<br />\n<a href="http://tinyurl.com/cyj3brd" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://tinyurl.com'']);" target="_blank">http://tinyurl.com/cyj3brd</a><br />\n<a href="http://tinyurl.com/d3k9fdd" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://tinyurl.com'']);" target="_blank">http://tinyurl.com/d3k9fdd</a><br />\n<a href="http://tinyurl.com/c2zgx9t" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://tinyurl.com'']);" target="_blank">http://tinyurl.com/c2zgx9t</a><br />\n<a href="http://tinyurl.com/cq4toh6" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://tinyurl.com'']);" target="_blank">http://tinyurl.com/cq4toh6</a></p>\n<p>Bitola (also known as the city of the consuls):<br />\n<a href="http://tinyurl.com/d87ywkt" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://tinyurl.com'']);" target="_blank">http://tinyurl.com/d87ywkt</a></p>\n<p>Heraklea (antient Roman city):<br />\n<a href="http://tinyurl.com/cxv9lw5" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://tinyurl.com'']);" target="_blank">http://tinyurl.com/cxv9lw5</a></p>\n<p>Tikves Lake where we will be spending 2 days in the famous wine region and enjoy the beautiful nature(motivational weekend of the holiday) :<br />\n<a href="http://tinyurl.com/cfovnzr" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://tinyurl.com'']);" target="_blank">http://tinyurl.com/cfovnzr</a></p>\n<p>Ohrid &#8211; the pearl of the Balkan (the pictures are enough to show you the beauty of the town):<br />\n<a href="http://tinyurl.com/bm87nuh" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://tinyurl.com'']);" target="_blank">http://tinyurl.com/bm87nuh</a><br />\n<a href="http://tinyurl.com/c8f6fm8" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://tinyurl.com'']);" target="_blank">http://tinyurl.com/c8f6fm8</a><br />\n<a href="http://tinyurl.com/d3xj7eu" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://tinyurl.com'']);" target="_blank">http://tinyurl.com/d3xj7eu</a><br />\n<a href="http://tinyurl.com/cwh96uc" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://tinyurl.com'']);" target="_blank">http://tinyurl.com/cwh96uc</a><br />\n<a href="http://tinyurl.com/buvxfvx" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://tinyurl.com'']);" target="_blank">http://tinyurl.com/buvxfvx</a> (pictures from Feel the Energy 2, when we spend 3 days in Ohrid)</p>\n<p>Because this is a holiday, we can alternate the plan, but be fast, apply and tell us your suggestion. The maximum amount of money that we estimate that you will need to bring with you and enjoy to the max, from the moment you enter our country, to the moment you exit is 350 euros (here we calculated the food, accommodation, traveling expenses, alcohol). But that is maximum, that is why we provided the price list for the common expenses (in the link bellow).</p>\n<p>You can find the schedule and the price list on the following link:<br />\n<a href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheet/ccc?key=0AvbT_55U9pUedFZEemNTLUJvQm9zVkFCVnZQY0g4b2c&amp;pli=1#gid=0" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://docs.google.com'']);" target="_blank">https://docs.google.com/spreadsheet/ccc?key=0AvbT_55U9pUedFZEemNTLUJvQm9zVkFCVnZQY0g4b2c&amp;pli=1#gid=0</a></p>\n<p>Put your application on the following link:<br />\n<a href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheet/viewform?formkey=dFMtUGYzUVI2YjlXSnlFSlRxWE1hZGc6MQ" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://docs.google.com'']);" target="_blank">https://docs.google.com/spreadsheet/viewform?formkey=dFMtUGYzUVI2YjlXSnlFSlRxWE1hZGc6MQ</a></p>\n<p>You can see the other participants in real time (wow real-time?!?) here:<br />\n<a href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheet/ccc?key=0AvbT_55U9pUedFMtUGYzUVI2YjlXSnlFSlRxWE1hZGc" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://docs.google.com'']);" target="_blank">https://docs.google.com/spreadsheet/ccc?key=0AvbT_55U9pUedFMtUGYzUVI2YjlXSnlFSlRxWE1hZGc</a></p>\n<p>Facebook Group:<br />\n<a href="http://www.facebook.com/groups/383347785033668/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.facebook.com'']);" target="_blank">http://www.facebook.com/groups/383347785033668/</a></p>\n<p>Facebook Event:<br />\n<a href="http://www.facebook.com/events/294062514017607/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.facebook.com'']);" target="_blank">http://www.facebook.com/events/294062514017607/</a></p>\n<p>You can send us as many questions you have, you can spam us, and bore us to death with suggestions on this mail:<br />\n<a href="mailto:contact@eestec-sk.org.mk" target="_blank">contact@eestec-sk.org.mk</a></p>\n<p>You are still here? Go to that Google doc and put your name in the list of the lovely people!</p>\n', 'EESTECers gone wild', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'eestecers-gone-wild', '', '', '2012-06-08 11:44:50', '2012-06-08 10:44:50', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/eestecers-gone-wild/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2248, 1, '2012-05-27 12:01:54', '2012-05-27 11:01:54', '\n<p>The most exciting summer exchange for 2012 is finally here!</p>\n<p>LC Athens is taking you to the second largest city in Greece, Thessaloniki, also known as the queen of the North! Who hasn&#8217;t heard of one of the best party cities worldwide, that combines the ancient with the new! The White Tower, the roman forum, the famous delicious pastries (it is impossible to leave the city without visiting its bakeries!) , the relaxed way of living of its people, even a walk down the seaside promenade are only some of the city&#8217;s treasures&#8230;</p>\n<p>Also, we have planned a day trip to the site of Vergina, the burial site of the kings of Macedon including Philip II, and also to Edessa, a town that&#8217;s famous for the waterfalls and the amazing scenery it provides.</p>\n<p>But that doesn&#8217;t stop there! Our participants will get the chance to attend our International Motivational Weekend (yes, you read correctly!) with no charge, taking place during the last 3 days of our exchange in Chalkidiki!<br />\nGet ready for camping, endless sun, parties&#8230; Get ready to GREECE U UP!!</p>\n', 'Greece Me Up', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'greece-me-up', '', '', '2012-05-27 12:01:54', '2012-05-27 11:01:54', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/greece-me-up/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2249, 1, '2012-05-12 20:12:43', '2012-05-12 19:12:43', '\n<p><strong>Dear EESTECers</strong></p>\n<p>Ever interested in what <strong>Plone</strong> has to offer? Ever wanted to learn more about a technology that could mean well paid work and tons of contacts? Here&#8217;s your opportunity! Moreover, there will be experienced members of the International EESTEC IT Team that can teach you how to get involved in the team to put all this new knowledge into action, with the best mentors to guide you. Are you a professional coder? Have you never touched a programming language before? Everyone interested in contributing is welcome! All you need is a laptop and a UTP cable since this is an advanced skills workshop.</p>\n<p>Interested in helping out the EESTEC IT team? You want to improve <a href="http://eestec.net/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://eestec.net'']);" target="_blank">eestec.net</a> but you just don&#8217;t know how to? This is your chance! JLC Antwerp organizes an ITT event as its first event in cooperation with Plone, the powerful and flexible system powering <a href="http://eestec.net/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://eestec.net'']);" target="_blank">eestec.net</a>. During this event, you will have the opportunity to learn about the system from professional developers and contribute both to EESTEC IT projects and even to the plone system itself. You can also work on other EESTEC IT projects such as Lykeion, we provide the infrastructure for a week of IT activity.</p>\n<p>Of course we will also provide the relaxation after the coding, and show you the beautiful city of Antwerp! The largest city of Belgium, featuring nice places such as the &#8220;Groenplaats&#8221;, the &#8220;Meir&#8221;, the &#8220;Keyserlei&#8221;, and a cathedral. Additionally we have a harbor, French fries (lots), traffic, a river, the tallest building in Belgium, waffles, chocolate, and much more. You will also see the University of Antwerp and it&#8217;s happy students. Additionally, we will also introduce you to Belgian beer and &#8220;cantus&#8221; which is a traditional student singing night.<br />\n<strong>Extra requirements</strong>: basic programming experience, preferably in object-oriented programming. The aim of the workshop is to introduce participants to Plone, so no previous Plone/Zope knowledge is required. However, it is necessary to have basic programming notions to fully understand all the sessions during this workshop, which include parts with code examples.<br />\nTo check those requirements are fulfilled, all applicants must fill the following form after applying through the website: <a href="http://eestec.net/workspaces/board/it-workshop/view" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://eestec.net'']);" target="_blank">http://eestec.net/workspaces/board/it-workshop/view</a>. This form will serve as a standardized CV to measure your skills.<br />\nIn addition to the CV, a motivational letter is also required and can be written in the application form in <a href="http://eestec.net" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://eestec.net'']);" target="_blank">eestec.net</a>.</p>\n<p>As for the extra requirements: <strong>dont worry, we are not looking for professional programmers!</strong> We just want to ensure the quality of the event by setting a minimum level of IT knowledge. All sessions will be easy to understand, and will be adapted to the level of the final participants.</p>\n<p><strong>Dont let this requirement keep you from applying!</strong> Even if you think you dont have enough experience, give it a try. In the end we will judge whether thats true or not. The most important thing is being motivated and wanting to learn.</p>\n<p>EESTECers can apply through the system, if you are a Plone professional, contact Joni Orponen.</p>\n', 'IT Workshop', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'it-workshop', '', '', '2012-05-12 20:12:43', '2012-05-12 19:12:43', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/it-workshop/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2250, 1, '2012-05-01 17:14:03', '2012-05-01 16:14:03', '\n<p>It&#8217;s time for the <strong>second Grant Team Operational Conference (GToc)</strong>, which is an operational event for educating the new EESTEC Grant Team members!<br />\nSince the Congress in 2011, when GT became an official EESTEC Body, through months of hard work, the results have been very successful. In order to expand, the GT needs motivated people from various LCs that want to get involved in the rather difficult, yet very promising area of grants.</p>\n<p>During this event, participants will get familiar with the grants that EESTEC can benefit from, be introduced to the concept of grants and the technical details around them, and they will also be given the opportunity to join Grant Team as junior members, since GToc is the only way one can become official member of the GT.</p>\n<p>But let&#8217;s not forget about the place where GToc will be held! The beautiful city of Athens awaits you!<br />\nLC Athens will host the event and show everyone how Athens is great during the day and night! Sightseeing in our beautiful historical centre, the Acropolis and its brand new museum, places where you can taste traditional greek dishes and enjoy greek hospitality, and of course night parties (because Athens nightlife is something worth finding out <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif'' alt='';)'' class=''wp-smiley'' />  ). During the weekend, we will have the chance to visit a beautiful island called Aigina, in order for the participants to regain their strength.</p>\n<p>So, if you&#8217;re interested in getting involved with the Grant Team, make sure you apply <strong><span style="color: #ff0000;">before May 20th</span></strong>, along with a <strong>motivational letter</strong> with any past experience you have with grants and the reasons for your interest in the GT.<br />\nThe selection of the participants will be made by both the Int. Board and the Grant Team, in order to ensure the proper continuation of the GT.</p>\n<p>Last but really not least, we&#8217;re really pleased that our application for the <strong>&#8221;Youth in Action&#8221;</strong> programme was accepted, so about <strong>70% of the travelling expenses will be refunded!!</strong> So, this goes for the following LCs that sent us a Part3 document: Ankara, Banja Luka, Belgrade, Bucharest, Budapest, Delft, Eskisehir, Krakow, Ljubljana, Lille, Madrid, Nis, Novi Sad, Podgorica, Trieste, Zagreb, Zurich.</p>\n<p>See you in sunny Athens! <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n', '2nd Grant Team Operational Conference', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', '2nd-grant-team-operational-conference', '', '', '2012-05-01 17:14:03', '2012-05-01 16:14:03', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/2nd-grant-team-operational-conference/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2251, 1, '2012-04-26 09:11:49', '2012-04-26 08:11:49', '\n<p><strong>Dear EESTECers,</strong><br />\nLet us invite you to the Advanced Skills Workshop (a new terminology in EESTEC since this years Congress) organized by LC Budapest this summer, called TANDEM.</p>\n<p><strong>Technology and Design in Motion</strong> (TANDEM) is an 8 days long workshop held in Hungary between the 19th and 27th of June that <strong>brings together students with different backgrounds</strong> to discover the use of <strong>Kinect</strong> and brainstorm on projects using <strong>Natural User Interfaces</strong> (NUI), with an emphasis on <strong>bringing new ideas to life</strong>. The participants will include 20 motivated EESTECers from all over Europe and 10 Design and Arts students from a number of high-profile universities in Hungary. You will have to work together in teams during the whole week, which not only gives you a unique chance to experience completely different work styles, but also creates an inspiring environment and fosters you to think outside of the box.</p>\n<p>During the workshop we will introduce you the necessary technical knowledge to use the Kinect, give introductory lectures to the Designers about programming in general and also invite experts to give inspirational talks. After this youll form mixed teams, choose a problem that youd like to work on, and yes, youll actually implement a working prototype of your solution as well!</p>\n<p>But did you really think working is all that we care about? 30 youngsters in a city with a <strong>unique atmosphere and unmatched nightlife</strong> under the supervision of our superb LC guarantees those sleepless nights youre dreaming of. We believe Budapest is also <strong>one of the most beautiful capitals in Europe</strong> and well do our best to show you as many faces of it as we can. Well also take you to our beloved <strong>Lake Balaton</strong> to get tanned and include a few adventure and sports programs to energize you even more. Not trusting us would probably be the biggest mistake you could make, so we really hope to see you in Budapest <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n<p>So, who should apply? Were looking for people with <strong>some experience in programming</strong> (preferably Java or C#, but this is not a strict requirement) and <strong>enough motivation to do some real work</strong> during the day instead of just sleeping at the lectures. This does not mean however that we miss any of the traditional EESTEC values &#8211; <strong>awesome parties, cool people, laying on the beach, a city rally, a few free rounds and some surprises</strong> are all important aspects of the event <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n<p>In order to apply please use the <a href="http://eestec.net/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://eestec.net'']);" target="_blank">eestec.net</a> site as you always do <strong>AND</strong> fill in <a href="http://eestec.net/lc/budapest/test/tandem" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://eestec.net'']);" target="_blank">THIS INTERNAL FORM</a> as well! Its a little bit longer, but not as long as it looks at first sight, and not difficult at all, so go ahead, give it 20 minutes so that we can host you on this one-of-a-kind event <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n<p>Looking forward to seeing you here,</p>\n<p><strong>The Extremely Enthusiastic OC</strong></p>\n', 'Technology and Design in Motion ASWS', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'technology-and-design-in-motion-asws', '', '', '2012-04-26 09:11:49', '2012-04-26 08:11:49', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/technology-and-design-in-motion-asws/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2252, 1, '2012-04-06 20:08:23', '2012-04-06 19:08:23', '\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>LC Sarajevo is organizing an exchange from 30th April to 6th May &#8220;High5 for LC Sarajevo!&#8221; and during it we invite all of you who are not participants of our exchange to join us on our birthday weekend (4th and 5th May). Our LC is celebrating 5 years of its existence, and we are doing our best to make this week more memorable than any event that you have ever participated before and with your appearance we are sure we will succeed! This is an awesome opportunity to explore Bosnia and Herzegovina and its rich cultural background, especially the city of Sarajevo, to make new acquaintances, share EESTEC spirit and have an unforgettable time! We invite you to participate in our birthday ceremony which we proudly make for our honorable guests, EESTECers, professors and students!</strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">As you could see before, LC Sarajevo is organizing an exchange from 30th April to 6th May and it goes by the name &#8220;High5 for LC Sarajevo&#8221;! Our LC is celebrating 5 years of its existence, and you should consider it to be a great reason for a big FIESTA <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif'' alt='';)'' class=''wp-smiley'' />  We are doing our best to make this week more memorable than any event that you have ever participated before and with your appearance we are sure we will succeed! This is an awesome opportunity to explore Bosnia and Herzegovina and its rich cultural background, especially the city of Sarajevo, to make new acquaintances, share EESTEC spirit and have an unforgettable time! Oh, who am I kidding&#8230;We are going to make the best parties and we will offer you fascinating experiences!!! <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Here are some videos which can show you even more <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif'' alt='';)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yLk7jgZUxX0" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.youtube.com'']);" target="_blank">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yLk7jgZUxX0</a></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Z9Imf56AJn0" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.youtube.com'']);" target="_blank">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Z9Imf56AJn0</a></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">As for the informal part, you can expect lots of different parties at various locations, interesting activities during the day and hopefully, you can get the picture of our way of living and tradition. All of you should feel like home during the visit because Bosnian people proved to be extremely friendly and helpful. Besides all of this one thing is certain, you will not get enough sleep <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Also, on behalf of the LC Sarajevo, we invite you to participate in our formal ceremony which we proudly make for our honorable guests,EESTECers, professors and students!</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">For participation fee of only <strong>20 </strong> you will have next things included:</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"> accommodation for two nights, 4th and 5th of May</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"> breakfast included for two days</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"> birthday dinner party (dinner &amp; one drink)</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"> free drinks on farewell party <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">For those who want to come to Sarajevo earlier it&#8217;s additional 10  per night (breakfast included).</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">We invite you all to be our guests and make our birthday celebration more special with your presence <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Deadline for application is <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>April 10th</strong></span>, so don&#8217;t hesitate. We want you! <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">For any questions feel free to contact:</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><a href="mailto:elmica.bh@gmail.com" target="_blank">elmica.bh@gmail.com</a></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">See you all soon <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n', 'LC Sarajevo&#8217;s 5th Birthday', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'lc-sarajevos-5th-birthday', '', '', '2012-04-06 20:08:23', '2012-04-06 19:08:23', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/lc-sarajevos-5th-birthday/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2253, 1, '2012-04-06 20:00:59', '2012-04-06 19:00:59', '\n<p><img class="alignleft" title="Manage your Project" src="https://fbcdn-sphotos-a.akamaihd.net/hphotos-ak-prn1/532483_342471049141109_339478169440397_821007_1848878874_n.jpg" alt="" width="206" height="170" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">LC COSENZA is proud to announce you our next Workshop, Manage your Project, Manage your Future. It will be held from 7th to 14th May, 18 participants.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">You can have good knowledge in your engineer field, but do you know how to work in a team? How to behave in project work? How to coordinate the work of more people? How to respect deadline? How to spend less money and time?</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">This year we will focus on Project Management. It is the science and art to implement successfully projects. It is a science because it is based on techniques and methodologies to follow, and is considered an art because it is necessary to have different skills and know how. It is important because it allows to address any project in an effective, structured and repeatable.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">In our workshop we will:</p>\n<ul style="text-align: justify;">\n<li>Explain the fundamentals of Project Management, a topic of great relevance for all those organizations who see the &#8220;project management&#8221; as an important tool for change and innovation;</li>\n<li>Provide information on basic skills that project managers and their team should have for the exercise of its functions;</li>\n<li>Identify the &#8220;soft skills&#8221; to manage a team and exercise their leadership;</li>\n<li>Provide information on the major certification programs exist</li>\n</ul>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Furthermore, you will be offered our warm Italian hospitality as well as funny times and parties.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Are you still waiting to apply? LC COSENZA is ready for you!!</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yr8L5CU_iXk&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;a" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.youtube.com'']);" target="_blank">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yr8L5CU_iXk&amp;feature=youtu.be&amp;a</a></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><a href="http://www.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fprezi.com%2Fcotp6dhgxrrw%2Fmanageyourproject%2F&amp;h=NAQEXp90R" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.facebook.com'']);" target="_blank">http://prezi.com/cotp6dhgxrrw/manageyourproject/</a></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Apply via eestec.net with your motivational letter before the deadline!!</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><a href="http://www.asiunical.org/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.asiunical.org'']);" target="_blank">More information about this event</a></p>\n', 'Manage your Project, Manage your Future', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'manage-your-project-manage-your-future', '', '', '2012-04-06 20:00:59', '2012-04-06 19:00:59', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/manage-your-project-manage-your-future/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2254, 1, '2012-04-06 19:52:11', '2012-04-06 18:52:11', '\n<p><strong>Study tour which is dedicated to students, who want to learn about modern solutions in the field of energy, automation and electrical science.</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>LC Krakow is organizing a workshop entitled &#8220;Smart energy for a better world&#8217; in cooperation with ABB Corporate Research Centre which will be held in Krakow from 8th till 15th of July 2012. This study tour is dedicated to students, who want to learn about modern solutions in the field of energy, automation and electrical science. The event will be a unique opportunity to visit one of the most advanced ABB Research Centers in the world and to broaden your knowledge on:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Advanced numerical simulations</li>\n<li>Power electronics</li>\n<li>Transients phenomena</li>\n<li>Smart Protection</li>\n<li>Advanced diagnostics</li>\n<li>Ferroresonance phenomena</li>\n</ul>\n<p>All students from European Universities are invited to join us at the ABB Corporate Research Center situated in Krakow, one of Poland&#8217;s most renown cities. This event will be a great occasion to meet experts on energy, electrical sciences and to visit Poland&#8217;s well-known tourist attractions.</p>\n<p>We are waiting for applications from students who have:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>electrical engineering profile</li>\n<li>good academic results</li>\n<li>good command of English</li>\n<li>completed at least 3 years of university education</li>\n</ul>\n<p>More information about the lectures and lab excercises can be found on the website of the event <a href="http://smart.eestec.pl/workshops.php" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://smart.eestec.pl'']);" target="_blank">here</a>.</p>\n<p>Apart from educational part of the event, you will have also a chance to see Krakow, the center of cultural and artistic life and one of the biggest cities in Poland. To be more specific you will visit:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>the Wawel Royal Castle &#8211; located at the Vistula River the residence of Polish kings and queens;</li>\n<li>the Underground of the Citys Main Market Square  unusual place created by modern technology with the exhibition of the monuments from the Middle Ages.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>There are also a laser tags competition, football game, barbecue, unforgettable parties every night planned and many others activities to keep you busy for the whole week, but we do not want to reveal all of the attractions now. You have to come to Krakow and see for yourself <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif'' alt='';)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n<p>How to apply:<br />\n1. EESTEC members: via eestec.net, where you should write down your motivational letter and send to me your CV (my email address: <a href="mailto:skoczylas.ewelina@gmail.com" target="_blank">skoczylas.ewelina@gmail.com</a>)<br />\n2. Non-EESTECers: via website: <a href="http://smart.eestec.pl/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://smart.eestec.pl'']);" target="_blank">smart.eestec.pl</a></p>\n<p>If you have any question, please do not hesitate to ask me: <a href="mailto:skoczylas.ewelina@gmail.com" target="_blank">skoczylas.ewelina@gmail.com</a>.<br />\nThe website of the event: <a href="http://smart.eestec.pl" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://smart.eestec.pl'']);" target="_blank">http://smart.eestec.pl</a></p>\n<p>Hope to see you in Krakow! <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif'' alt='';)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n<p><a href="http://smart.eestec.pl" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://smart.eestec.pl'']);" target="_blank">More information about this event</a></p>\n', 'Smart energy for a better world', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'smart-energy-for-a-better-world', '', '', '2012-04-06 19:52:11', '2012-04-06 18:52:11', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/smart-energy-for-a-better-world/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2255, 1, '2012-03-25 01:32:17', '2012-03-25 00:32:17', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>If you have never been to Zagreb, shame on you! You must have heard that our events are just awesome and here is another one to prove that is true! <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif'' alt='';)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n<p>The opportunity to apply for our event and come to Zagreb is finally here. Just in case you need more convincing to come (even though I doubt it), read the rest of our invitation!</p>\n<p><strong>Special Note!! No motivational letters needed, but advantage goes to people who send motivational pictures! <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif'' alt='';)'' class=''wp-smiley'' />  We want to SEE why you want to come to our workshop so be creative! <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif'' alt='';)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </strong></p>\n<p>This year&#8217;s theme will be <strong>&#8220;Risky business&#8221;</strong> and as you can guess from the name, the event is based on learning about risk management. You will have several very interesting classes held by professors from our faculty and visiting lecturers. But that is not all! If you apply now, you will get a set of knives free of charge! What?? No, you wont. You will get classes consisted of case studies and the opportunity to apply the acquired knowledge on practical examples. Thats more useful than a set of knives! <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n<p><em>What else we&#8217;ve got you&#8217;re wondering?</em><br />\nOK, if you haven&#8217;t heard about wonderful Croatian nature you are really missing a lot! Google it and look at the pictures&#8230;[5 minutes later] You must be interested now! <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif'' alt='';)'' class=''wp-smiley'' />  We will show you some beautiful sights and that is not all, &#8217;cause you also get to experience the Croatian culture and not to mention our awesome food and drinks!</p>\n<p>Let me repeat that again  experience the culture and our awesome food and drinks! Get it? <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif'' alt='':D'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n<p>You will definitely not leave hungry or thirsty (except if you eat or drink really really really lot), but you will be eager to come back to taste Croatia again <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n<p><em>You&#8217;re asking yourselves what about the real memorable having fun part which everyone forgets because of too muchhmmm .too much what? <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif'' alt='':D'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </em><br />\nNow that&#8217;s our strongest card, so don&#8217;t come tired or wanting to rest, we are not going to allow that! <strong>You ARE going to party every day and it IS going to be legen&#8230;&#8230;..dary! <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif'' alt='';)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </strong></p>\n<p>In the end, it doesn&#8217;t matter where we take you because we will make your time here unforgettable.</p>\n<p>Need more convincing? You really are hard to get! Just contact us on <a href="mailto:cp@eestec-zg.hr" target="_blank">cp@eestec-zg.hr</a> for any other information!</p>\n<p>So come and meet us! We prepared a great week for you, guaranteed!</p>\n<p>And remember, wine is fine but whiskey is quicker!</p>\n<p>LC Zagreb <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n', 'Risky Business', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'risky-business', '', '', '2012-03-25 01:32:17', '2012-03-25 00:32:17', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/risky-business/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2256, 1, '2012-03-12 10:43:30', '2012-03-12 09:43:30', 'Dear EESTECers,\r\n\r\nZurich is back with a new event. ARE YOU READY?\r\n\r\nDo you like fun and parties in a great international city? The experience of constructing a mighty weapon? Smashing birds against walls to subdue the filthy pigs? Taking defencelesse creatures under your patronage? Yes, of course youre right, we will play Angry Birds!\r\n\r\nIn small groups you will design and program your self-made catapult. At the end, there will be a challenge in which you will proof your skills in the topic aim and shoot. Constructed with simple materials and programmed in LabView (will be provided during the week) your war machine is ready to show the little green pigs their master. Whos laughing now?! To participate, no extensive informatics knowledge is required.. Dont forget to mention your programming experience in your motivational letter though, so we can plan the groups in advance.\r\n\r\nDespite of the new subject, many of our famous activities will take place! Live La Vida Loca on our tram party, experience Zurich on our city rally and enjoy yourself on our Swiss night!\r\n\r\nBesides destroying castles, we will also show you the beauty of Switzerland and its mountains. And have we mentioned yet? Like every year, there will be many legendary parties!\r\n\r\nUnlike the last years, this LC Zurich event takes place in May, so we will be able to have more outside activities. As soon as all the filthy pigs are dead, we will go on a weekend trip to the countryside. We swear, no academical part there! So we will have more time to party! Buckle up and apply!\r\n\r\nOf course we will announce the participants list before the Congress!\r\n\r\nBest regards and see you in Zurich!!', 'Angry Engineers', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'angry-engineers', '', '', '2013-03-01 22:53:53', '2013-03-01 21:53:53', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/angry-engineers/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2257, 1, '2012-03-12 09:08:54', '2012-03-12 08:08:54', '\n<p>Hello there, dear and amazing EESTECers!</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">Now, cutting to the chase, because April is the new March when it comes to EESTEC events, I would like to proudly announce you the first LC Bucharest Workshop in quite some time:</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>&#8220;Embedded Design Conference&#8221;</strong></p>\n<p>We hear so much about <strong>telemedicine</strong>, about integrated systems, about how cool it is to be a bio-medical engineer and how hype embedded systems are. But how about this: how about you do this for a change?</p>\n<p>What will you do during this week in Bucharest more precisely?</p>\n<p>You will assist lectures on the exact equipment that you will be bringing to use;<br />\nYou will get the chance to use up those programming skills that you thought to be gone, or maybe gain some;<br />\nYou will code on micro-controller devices so that you bring the concepts of telemedicine to life.</p>\n<p>And of course, let&#8217;s not forget about the fun part. Yes, the academics involved are quite heavy and interesting. But still, here we&#8217;re talking about an event powered by yours truly LC Bucharest. And you may be too young to remember our last legendary workshop, but you&#8217;re surely not too young to have met us so far or to have heard stories about how we rock the house everywhere we go <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif'' alt='';)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n<p>You will get to enjoy the city in one of the most entertaining days, through a lively program, you will have the chance to taste our amazing traditional dishes and also to party amazingly. And if you don&#8217;t trust me, ask your Congress members from last year about how we took care of them in Bucharest <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif'' alt='';)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n<p>You can bet this event is the one you&#8217;ve been waiting for! So don&#8217;t hesitate, bug your CPs and apply now <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif'' alt='';)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n', 'Embedded Design Conference', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'embedded-design-conference', '', '', '2012-03-12 09:08:54', '2012-03-12 08:08:54', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/embedded-design-conference/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2258, 1, '2012-03-04 23:11:06', '2012-03-04 22:11:06', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers !</p>\n<p>LC Krakow would like to announce you that the 4th edition of our workshop KrakYourNet is coming once again this spring! But surprise, surprise <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif'' alt='':D'' class=''wp-smiley'' />  We have decided it is a time for changes and KrakYourNet4 is going to be only for our domestic students. For you we have a pleasure to present an exchange, organised in parallel with KYN4, named All day, all night, what a Krakow which will take place from 14th to 21th of April in the heart of Poland.</p>\n<p>For the ones who has never been in Krakow it will be an opportunity to see everything the best what our city can offer. And if you have already visited Krakow before, now you will have the chance to explore it even more and truly fall in love with this center of academic, cultural, artistic life and one of the oldest and largest cities in Poland.</p>\n<p>To be more specific you will visit:</p>\n<p>Cyfronet Academic Computer Centre &#8211; one of the largest Polish supercomputing and networking centres;<br />\nThe Wawel Royal Castle  located at the Vistula River the residence of Polish kings and queens;<br />\nThe Underground od the Citys Main Market Square  unusual place created by modern technology with the exhibition of the monuments from the Middle Ages;<br />\nKociuszko Mound  from the top of the mound you can admire the beautiful view of the whole city;<br />\nThe memorial and museum AuschwitzBirkenau  the concentration camp from the Second World War and one of the symbols of the Holocaust.</p>\n<p>Still want more? Well, there are a laser tags competition, football game, bowling, unforgettable parties every night planned and many others activities to keep you busy for the whole week, but we do not want to reveal all of the attractions now. You have to come to Krakow and see for yourself <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif'' alt='';)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n<p>We promise you the time of your life, full of sightseeing and having fun! Dont wait, apply right now. We are waiting for you!</p>\n<p><strong>Apply via <a href="http://eestec.net" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://eestec.net'']);" target="_blank">eestec.net</a>. The deadline for applications is 18th of March. The participation fee is 50 euro. The number of participants may be increased.</strong></p>\n<p>If you have any questions, dont hesitate to contact me: <a href="mailto:skoczylas.ewelina@gmail.com" target="_blank">skoczylas.ewelina@gmail.com</a>. See you soon!</p>\n<p>Greetings,</p>\n', 'All day, all night, what a Krakow!', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'all-day-all-night-what-a-krakow', '', '', '2012-03-04 23:11:06', '2012-03-04 22:11:06', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/all-day-all-night-what-a-krakow/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2259, 1, '2012-02-16 21:50:12', '2012-02-16 20:50:12', '<strong>RIS Workshop will be focused in the impact of robotics and High technologies in our Life. Hopefully youll enjoy it</strong>\r\n\r\nDear EESTECers,\r\n\r\nFor the first time in France, JLC Lille is proud to announce you its EESTEC workshop: R.I.S !\r\n\r\nThe environmental awareness and the need of more efficiency led to develop more advanced technologies. Mandatory in all sectors of industry, intelligent autonomous systems are the key to growth of all technology focused companies. This has not only an effect on our environment, but also on our attitude. Whether in transportation, work tools or communication, theyve became part of our every day life.\r\n\r\nThrough this event, well try to gather students around the theme of technical and technological innovation, and its social and environmental impacts. Participants will attend theoretical presentations from scientists working in the field. They will also be visiting firms and laboratories in different sectors of intelligent systems.\r\n\r\nWe will likewise organize two contests : The Software tournament, and the Robotics tournament in which each participant will be teaming up with a French student.\r\n\r\nRIS will bring a greater effectiveness to the knowledge and the training of the participants, giving them the chance to be in direct contact with the Department of Research in Robotics field.\r\n\r\nAt last, but not the least, well make sure you have a great time in Lille! Youll have the opportunity to explore the best spots of the city during the City Rally, discover its charming atmosphere during day and night and try tasty French food and drinks!\r\n\r\nDont think, dont wait. Just APPLY! Well be waiting for you motivation letters!\r\n\r\nOfficial website is coming soon, but you can find informations and news about the school and the city on\r\n\r\n<a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.youtube.com'']);" href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iRC1znun9J8" target="_blank">PolytechLille Video</a>\r\n<a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.youtube.com'']);" href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jD6k2xmcPsU&amp;feature=related" target="_blank">Nao in polytechLille</a>\r\n<a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.polytech-lille.com'']);" href="http://www.polytech-lille.com/english/polytech-lille-ecole-polytechnique-france-art46.html" target="_blank">http://www.polytech-lille.com/english/polytech-lille-ecole-polytechnique-france-art46.html</a>\r\n<a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.destination-lille-metropole.eu'']);" href="http://www.destination-lille-metropole.eu/index.php?lang=en" target="_blank">Lille Metropole</a>\r\n\r\nSee you soon in Lille!', 'Robotics and Intelligent Systems (RIS) event', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'robotics-and-intelligent-systems-ris-event', '', '', '2013-03-01 22:52:41', '2013-03-01 21:52:41', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/robotics-and-intelligent-systems-ris-event/', 0, 'events', '', 0);
