(2260, 1, '2012-02-16 21:37:11', '2012-02-16 20:37:11', '\n<p><img class="alignnone" title="Tie before you die" src="http://eestec.net/lc/delft/tie-before-you-die/themalogocolor.png/image_thumb" alt="Tie before you die" width="128" height="128" /></p>\n<p>DEAR EESTECERS,</p>\n<p>CAPSLOCK IS CRUISE CONTROL FOR COOL and a tie is cruise control for Delft. All (active) members of eestec LC Delft know that, as has been showed during ECMs and Congresses. We all love that feeling of wearing a tie, you know. Ever wanted to know that feeling, to wear a tie from Delft? We offer you the solution, because you have to <strong>Tie before you Die</strong>!</p>\n<p>After two years of silence LC Delft is back with a wonderful workshop full of educational, cultural and cool activities. We will show you how pleasant Delft is, how great our university is and how flat our country is.</p>\n<p>On the program we have among others:<br />\n- An excursion to the Dutch deltaworks. During a personal tour with some rental vans we will take you to see the stormvloedkering, the haringvlietdam and part of the Rotterdam harbour.<br />\n- A (day)trip to Amsterdam. That is something that can not be missing. When you think of The Netherlands, you think of Amsterdam with the great bars and wonderful sightseeing.<br />\n- A case study of the innovation department of an international company: Omron.<br />\n- Some awesome parties and so called borrels. According to eestec spirit the parties in the night will be awesome ofcourse, but to Delft standards we will also have some nice so called borrels.<br />\n- Informational lectures about our university and what they have to offer.<br />\n- LC Delft members as homestay. Hotels are good, but homestays are better according to us. It will provide a personal touch with our members.</p>\n<p>All activities can be participated while enjoying the sweet touch around your neck of a cool traditional LC Delft tie.</p>\n<p>Concluding I would like to tell you that this will be an awesome event and you should participate, because Delft is waiting for you!</p>\n<p>See you in Delft!</p>\n<p>Paul Marcelis<br />\nEESTEC LC Delft<br />\nContact Person<br />\n<a href="mailto:delft@eestec.net" target="_blank">delft@eestec.net</a></p>\n', 'Tie before you Die', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'tie-before-you-die', '', '', '2012-02-16 21:37:11', '2012-02-16 20:37:11', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/tie-before-you-die/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2261, 1, '2012-02-16 21:31:44', '2012-02-16 20:31:44', '\n<p><strong>An interactive workshop about the interaction between nano technology and power engineering.</strong></p>\n<p>After our announcement of &#8220;Speak Up!&#8221; two weeks ago, we are happy to present you our second event <strong>&#8220;From Nano to GigaWatts&#8221;</strong> (<strong>28.4.</strong> to<strong> 6.5.12</strong>).</p>\n<p>This workshop will cover many interesting points about the interaction between nano technology and power engineering. Do you know about the existance of solar cells based on nano technology? How these work? How all these futur solar cells influence the power grid? How we can power our homes in the future although there is no sun at night?</p>\n<p>There will be lectures about these topics as well as a hands-on lab on the development of a solar cell on organic basis where you&#8217;ll learn how to build your own functional solar cell. We&#8217;ll be cooperating with two departments in our university, so the lectures will be held by our professors.</p>\n<p>Apart from the lectures, we will introduce you to the lovely Bavarian capital, Munich. We look forward to showing you our Bavarian culture, Munich nightlife and our charming hospitality. The workshop will take place during the weeks of spring festival which is the &#8220;little sister&#8221; of our Oktoberfest and, of course, we don&#8217;t want you to miss this event either!</p>\n<p>As usual, the workshop will conclude with the International Motivational Weekend. This event will be held at a house in the alps. There you&#8217;ll participate in soft-skill training and, not to overlook, some unforgettable parties. (The IMW is free for participants!)</p>\n<p>Do not hestitate and apply now! LC Awesome is waiting for you!</p>\n', 'From Nano to GigaWatts', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'from-nano-to-gigawatts', '', '', '2012-02-16 21:31:44', '2012-02-16 20:31:44', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/from-nano-to-gigawatts/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2262, 1, '2012-02-16 21:25:27', '2012-02-16 20:25:27', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>LC Munich would like to invite you to the IMW 2012, Mhlbach am Hochknig.</p>\n<p>For everyone, who doesn&#8217;t know what an IMW is:</p>\n<p>An International Motivational Weekend is held to motivate new members (or future members) from all LCs in order to experience EESTEC and get an impression of the EESTEC Spirit. Therefore on Saturday EESTEC Trainers will have Softskill-Trainings with relaxing tournaments and baubleries prepared for all participants. As Friday and Saturday night, please enjoy two awesome theme parties.</p>\n<p>As an conclusion for our events Speak Up! and Nano feat. Power, we will be taking along all of our 30 participants and new members from LC Munich.</p>\n<p>Regarding the location, the house is located in the beautiful alps, next to the spa area Mhlbach am Hochknig. During your freetime you can go hiking, play volleyball/soccer, explore the area with your friends, or simply relax while watching the hilarious landscape. <a href="http://www.hochkeilhaus.at/englisch/e_index.htm" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.hochkeilhaus.at'']);" target="_blank">http://www.hochkeilhaus.at/englisch/e_index.htm</a></p>\n<p>The participation fee is 55 , which includes accomodation and full board together with all kind of drinks for the parties on Friday and Saturday. Due to limited flexibility and possibilities, we will have to ask you to come by your own car. Nevertheless, we will try to offer pick-up service for people coming by train, but we can&#8217;t guarantee it. The pick up price will also vary on the location of pick-up (Make requests at eestec.ws@fs.ei.tum.de).</p>\n<p>The easiest way to participate in this event is simply apply for one of our awesome events (Deadlines are March, 15th for Speak Up and Nano feat. Power).</p>\n<p>We are looking forward to meeting you!</p>\n', 'IMW 2012 in Mhlbach am Hochknig (LC Mnich)', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'imw-2012-in-muhlbach-am-hochkonig-lc-munich', '', '', '2012-02-16 21:25:27', '2012-02-16 20:25:27', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/imw-2012-in-muhlbach-am-hochkonig-lc-munich/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2263, 1, '2012-02-05 12:06:22', '2012-02-05 11:06:22', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>LC Munich is honored to present you the sequel of our Women in Engineering <strong>&#8220;Speak Up!&#8221;</strong> workshop from <strong>April 28th</strong> until <strong>May 6th</strong>. As always, the event goes hand in hand with our second event which will be announced in the next couple of weeks.</p>\n<p>Our department for Gender Studies will give an interactive four day seminar. Female students will learn how to use their voice, express themselves and prove themselves in a working environment. It is a fact that women earn less money, are treated worse and hold less important positions in a company. Often, these facts lead to prejudice against women and they don&#8217;t even try to stand up for themselves, seeing that &#8220;it is just as it is&#8221;. So all you girls, use your voice and Speak Up! Our seminar will show you how to grasp opportunities and broaden your prospects for your future working life. Besides, together with all the participants you should work out your personal road to success.</p>\n<p>Furthermore, there will be a womens&#8217; contact forum during where you&#8217;ll have the opportunity to interact and exchange experiences with other women working in engineering jobs.</p>\n<p>Apart from the lectures, we will introduce you to the lovely Bavarian capital, Munich. We look forward to showing you our Bavarian culture, Munich nightlife and our charming hospitality. The workshop will take place during the weeks of spring festival which is the &#8220;little sister&#8221; of our Oktoberfest and, of course, we don&#8217;t want you to miss this event either!</p>\n<p>As usual, the workshop will conclude with the International Motivational Weekend. This event will be held at a house in the alps. There you&#8217;ll participate in soft-skill training and, not to overlook, some unforgettable parties. (The IMW is free for participants!)</p>\n<p>Do not hestitate and apply now! LC Awesome is waiting for you</p>\n', 'WiE: Speak Up!', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'wie-speak-up', '', '', '2012-02-05 12:06:22', '2012-02-05 11:06:22', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/wie-speak-up/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2264, 1, '2012-02-05 12:00:23', '2012-02-05 11:00:23', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>If you survive EESTEC March events and take a little break in April, we think that in May you will have enough energy for full adventure in Sarajevo.</p>\n<p>We are inviting you to visit our city, <strong>from 30th April till 6th May</strong>, city that had the first full-time (dawn to dusk) tram line in Europe, city with many drinking fountains that share the legend: if you drink water from them, you will come back to Sarajevo for sure (we still think that evapi are to blame for that, but drink some water, just in case <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> ), city in which the 14th Winter Olympic Games took place, that organizes one of the greatest film festivals in region every year &#8211; Sarajevo Film Festival, city that was in 2009. chosen as one of the 10 cities in the world you should visit.</p>\n<p>If those facts are not enough, then you are surely going to be intrigued by what EESTEC LC Sarajevo has prepared for you.</p>\n<p>Unforgettable sightseeing, where in the center of the city you are able to see Ghazi Husrev-beg mosque, which is one of the most significant Islamic monuments on Balkan, Ashkenazi Synagogue, third largest synagogue in Europe, Cathedral of Heart of Jesus which is, due to interesting combination of Gothic and Romanic elements different from all others and Orthodox Church which is one of the biggest orthodox temples in Balkans, and all that very close to each other.</p>\n<p>Still not interested? Then, we expect you to change your mind when we say that we have prepared two celebrations for you. First one is the celebration of 1st May, Labor Day, which is traditionally celebrated as a day off in Sarajevo.</p>\n<p>The second one is the celebration we are especially proud of. Two days of event are planned for <strong>celebrating LC Sarajevos 5th birthday</strong>. You will have a chance to see all our accomplishments during those 5 years, meet our alumni members and many more EESTECers from all over Europe that are going to be guests of our celebration. Its, of course, applied that special occasions require special celebration in form of crazy all-night partying in city that never sleeps. We simply have to mention some delicious food that you will have opportunity to try in Sarajevo, such as evapi, burek and other pies, baklava and many more &#8211; you can be sure that you are going to enjoy our food very much <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> .</p>\n<p>If you are still second guessing whether to apply or not, there is one <strong>surprise trip</strong> planned&#8230; But, since it is surprise, you have to apply and see for yourself&#8230;</p>\n<p>Sooo? Are we going to meet in a beautiful city surrounded by mountains, beautiful nature and astonishing sights, the home of warm and friendly people and EESTECers waiting to host you and make this one week the most amazing week of your life <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> .</p>\n<p>Deadline for applying is <strong>25.03.2012</strong>.</p>\n<p>More about our previous event, our city and country :<br />\n<a title="Bosnia and Herzegovina promo video" href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Z9Imf56AJn0" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.youtube.com'']);" target="_blank">Bosnia and Herzegovina promo video</a><br />\n<a title="Video clip from last event 1" href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yLk7jgZUxX0" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.youtube.com'']);" target="_blank">Video clip from last event 1</a><br />\n<a title="Short video clip from last event 2" href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Crjp55vxaRM" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.youtube.com'']);" target="_blank">Short video clip from last event 2</a><br />\n<a title="http://www.visitsarajevo.ba" href="http://www.visitsarajevo.ba/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.visitsarajevo.ba'']);" target="_blank">http://www.visitsarajevo.ba</a></p>\n<p><a title="http://www.visitsarajevo.ba" href="http://www.visitsarajevo.ba/" target="_blank"><br />\n</a></p>\n<p>We will send you special invitation for celebrating LC Sarajevos 5th birthday, this one is only for the exchange <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif'' alt='';)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n<p>If you have any questions, feel free to contact me on <a href="mailto:elmica.bh@gmail.com" target="_blank">elmica.bh@gmail.com</a>. I&#8217;ll be pleased to answer.</p>\n<p>So, don&#8217;t hesitate and apply now for the greatest fun you&#8217;ll have this Spring!</p>\n<p>Can&#8217;t wait to see you all soon in the capital of The Heart-shaped Land!</p>\n<p><strong>Enjoy NATURE. Enjoy FRIENDSHIP. Enjoy CRAZY. Enjoy LAZY. Enjoy EAST. Enjoy WEST. Enjoy LIFE. Enjoy BOSNIA AND HERZEGOVINA.</strong></p>\n', 'High 5 for LC Sarajevo', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'high-5-for-lc-sarajevo', '', '', '2012-02-05 12:00:23', '2012-02-05 11:00:23', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/high-5-for-lc-sarajevo/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2265, 1, '2012-01-22 02:38:43', '2012-01-22 01:38:43', '\n<p>Hello dear EESTEC-ers, after 2 years LC East Sarajevo is back! We are proud to present you &#8220;Jahorina Spring Break&#8221;, unforgettable event that will take place from 20th to 27th of March 2012.</p>\n<p>Academic part will be held on Jahorina (our Olympic mountain), where International Scientific Symposium &#8211; Infoteh 2012 will take place. You will have opportunity to listen lectures from the experts, scientists, engineers, researchers and students that deal with information technologies. We provided <a href="http://www.motel-topalovic.com/hotele.html" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.motel-topalovic.com'']);" target="_blank">hotel accommodation</a> for our participants, transport to Infoteh and back.</p>\n<p>Non academic part will be quite hedonistic and relaxed, but full of various activities, such as swimming, bowlingor just lazy sitting in pub and drinking beer/coffee/juice/rakija/whatever</p>\n<p>We will also visit Orlovaca cave and beautiful well of Bosna river. Sightseeing and visiting city landmarks are also part of the program. During these 7 days you will taste our traditional food and drinks. We will organize traditional Serbian night with our live music, and people dressed in traditional Serbian clothes.</p>\n<p>And at the end, thing that you are waiting the most.YES! Parties will be every night on various places!</p>\n<p>As you could see, this is a life time opportunity. Many people would kill for it, so dont hesitate to apply! <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n<p>See you in East Sarajevo!</p>\n', 'Jahorina Spring Break', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'jahorina-spring-break', '', '', '2012-01-22 02:38:43', '2012-01-22 01:38:43', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/jahorina-spring-break/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2266, 1, '2012-01-22 02:33:57', '2012-01-22 01:33:57', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>Have you ever wanted to turn lead into gold? Ever wondered how to convince a company of the importance of willingly giving money and stuff to EESTEC? Ever wondered how to get money out of thin air? FRAME IS YOUR EVENT!</p>\n<p>In EESTEC International we&#8217;re looking for people with EESTEC Spirit and the nuts to fight to make international events possible, to bring more and more quality to everything we do. Motivation is the cement that keeps us together, that makes us strong to make greatness happen. But the same way we can&#8217;t build a palace without bricks, we can&#8217;t deploy projects and organize events without money.</p>\n<p>Enter FR, the team that will bring stability and a stable economical source to sustain our international infrastructure and make congresses, ECMs, T4T, etc. not only possible but pleasant, not having to worry about tight budgets and loans <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n<p>But this is not only for International. Think about the experience you might acquire and the boost your local LC FR might get. So lets work together in a great team for all EESTEC.</p>\n<p>And this awesome event is going to take place in a beautiful <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ni" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://en.wikipedia.org'']);" target="_blank">City of Ni</a>. It has been gate between East and West. It has great cultural and historical heritage. One of the most important persons in European history, Emperor <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Constantine_the_Great" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://en.wikipedia.org'']);" target="_blank">Constantine the Great</a>, was born in Ni (roman name <strong>NAISSUS</strong>) in 272AD. Because of that, Ni is also known as The Emperor&#8217;s city.</p>\n<p>You will visit <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ni_Fortress" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://en.wikipedia.org'']);" target="_blank">Fortress of Ni</a> that exists at this place for more than 2000 years, and has layers from different historical periods. Thats because Ni has been gate between East and West, so many civilizations passed here and they left some trace in the fortress. Its in this condition since XVII century, and now its one of the best preserved fortifications of Ottoman style in Europe.</p>\n<p>We have rich historical legacy, but we have even richer offer of national foods and drinks. You won&#8217;t be hungry at any moment and you will be able to enjoy in our best meals. Don&#8217;t forget our traditional drink- rakija!</p>\n<p>Serbia is famous of its very live nightlife. So you will have a lot of fun in both traditional places called kafana and in night clubs.</p>\n<p>We&#8217;re preparing you unforgettable EESTEC event!</p>\n<p>Applying is via <a href="http://eestec.net/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://eestec.net'']);" target="_blank">eestec.net</a> site. Motivational letter is required.</p>\n<p>For any additional question, contact <a href="mailto:treasurer@eestec.net" target="_blank">treasurer@eestec.net</a>.</p>\n<p>Greetings from Ni!</p>\n', 'FRAME 2012', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'frame-2012', '', '', '2012-01-22 02:33:57', '2012-01-22 01:33:57', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/frame-2012/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2267, 1, '2012-01-21 19:22:19', '2012-01-21 18:22:19', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>One more time, LC Madrid is proud to announce you our last workshop! <strong>Network Society 2.0</strong></p>\n<p>Due to its success last year, we have decided to continue with the topic. It will make you aware of the importance that networking each other has. A networked society allows us to save time, money and energy when trying to communicate each other and it can make things easier in case of necessity. In our workshop we will analyse and treat the presence of networks and communications in every aspect of our lives. Nowadays people is more connected than ever, and a big part of our communication takes part in the so-called &#8220;social networks&#8221;. Most of us have smartphones in our pockets, and couldn&#8217;t think of living without being permanently connected. Furthermore, networks are also present in every other aspect of society, such as health-care, commerce and learning. We can truly speak of a &#8220;Society of the networks&#8221;, the &#8220;Network society&#8221;. For that reason, we have prepared several lectures carried out by different companies just to show you their cutting-edge projects and visits to laboratories and research centres to see exactly how they work.</p>\n<p>It will be held from <strong>22nd to 29th April</strong>, so you have enough time to renew your energy after Congress <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif'' alt='';)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n<p>But that&#8217;s not all!! We have also prepared for you non-academical activities. You will have the opportunity to explore every secret place of Madrid during the City Rally, to taste Spanish food and drinks (I know all of you like Sangra) and feel its atmosphere during day, but specially during night!</p>\n<p>At the end, during the weekend, organizers and participants will stay in the countryside. What we will do there is&#8230;a surprise! <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif'' alt='';)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n<p>Still thinking to apply?! Seriously?!</p>\n<p>Apply now! You have until <strong>15th of March</strong>! Long time to make up your minds.</p>\n<p>Finally, as we always say&#8230;</p>\n<p>We are so sorry to have to say this, but as we don&#8217;t apply for EU grant, every year we have to make great efforts to find sponsors for our events, and although last year was faultless <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif'' alt='';)'' class=''wp-smiley'' />  , we expect an exemplary attitude from all of you and we friendly ask you for cooperation and comprehension. Irresponsible attitudes won&#8217;t be tolerated and in case it happens, participants will be warned and eventually expelled from the event if warnings are disregarded.<br />\nWhen it is time to party, we have party (and trust me, we will do! ;D), but when it&#8217;s time to work, we must work (and later we have party! ^^).</p>\n<p><strong>Follow us</strong>: <a href="http://www.eestec.es/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.eestec.es'']);" target="_blank">Website</a>, <a href="http://www.facebook.com/#!/pages/Eestec-Eurielec/115934218476771" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.facebook.com'']);" target="_blank">Facebook</a> and <a href="http://twitter.com/eurielec" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://twitter.com'']);" target="_blank">Twitter</a></p>\n<p>We hope to see you all in Madrid! =)</p>\n<p>Greetings from LC Madrid</p>\n', 'Network Society 2.0', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'network-society-2-0', '', '', '2012-01-21 19:22:19', '2012-01-21 18:22:19', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/network-society-2-0/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2268, 1, '2012-01-13 17:32:57', '2012-01-13 16:32:57', 'Dear EESTECers,\r\n\r\nWe are very glad to officially announce Congress 2012 registration period. From now and till 29 January all LCs, JLCs and Observers have a chance to register their representative for Congress which will take place from 29th of March till 6th of April in Tallinn and Riga, Estonia and Latvia respectively (First 4 days will be in Tallinn and rest 4 days in Riga).\r\n\r\nEach LC, JLC and Observer have a right for at least one place on Congress. If you do not register your representative till the deadline, Int. Board will assign place for your LC to BAs, Trainers, IT members and other international teams.\r\n\r\nPlease do not miss the <strong>deadline 29 January</strong> for your registration!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>What kind of participants are expected at the Congress?</strong>\r\n\r\nIts totally up to the LC/JLC/Observer to decide who you want to send on Congress as your official representatives. Int. Board will not interfere in your decision.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>What do we expect from participants during Congress?</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>We expect that every LC has at least one representative during every General Assembly (GA) sessions. It is inexcusable to miss any GA since we are going to have discussion on very important topics for EESTEC such as:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li> EESTEC projects</li>\r\n	<li> Board and Bodies report</li>\r\n	<li> Promotion and degradation of LCs and JLCs</li>\r\n	<li> RoP changing</li>\r\n	<li> Election of the new International Board</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThis year we will also have Open Day as part of Congress 2012. Open Day can be counted as a fair where there are booths for participating companies, universities, EESTEC local committees and international Board, and every representative are free to visit each others booths for information exchange about any idea or opportunity.\r\n\r\nWhat do you need to bring for Open Day?\r\n\r\nEvery LC representative should bring on Congress:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li> Informational materials of your University-Faculty (this is most important)</li>\r\n	<li> Informational materials of your LC (also very important)</li>\r\n	<li> Promo materials of your LC activities (posters, flyers, bookmarks)</li>\r\n	<li> LC flag (only if you have one, dont need to make if you dont have)</li>\r\n	<li> Prepare nformational (at least 1 page) documents or presentation/slides which includes:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li> Your recruitment Strategy (how you get new members every year)</li>\r\n	<li> What makes your LC successful? (your successful projects, activities)</li>\r\n	<li> How you keep motivations of your members? (motivation strategies, tips and tricks)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>To sum up and again the most important, dont miss deadline for registration, 29 January, since after that deadline, International Board will give your places to Bodies.</strong>\r\n\r\nAlso, you find additional information in the site <a onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://eestec.net'']);" href="http://eestec.net/news-and-offers/congress-2012-in-general" target="_blank">here</a>\r\n\r\nWaiting for your registration,\r\nEESTEC International board', '26th Annual Congress', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', '26th-annual-congress', '', '', '2013-03-13 23:31:25', '2013-03-13 22:31:25', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/26th-annual-congress/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2269, 1, '2012-01-09 23:56:24', '2012-01-09 22:56:24', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers;</p>\n<p>What about using just a thin LCD except for a 3 kg laptop or a desktop? What if there werent any harddisks in your computers? We are proud to announce our upcoming workshop <strong>CLOCODILE</strong> (<strong>CLO</strong>ud <strong>CO</strong>mputing and <strong>D</strong>elightful <strong>I</strong>stanbul <strong>L</strong>ife is <strong>E</strong>nclosed) which will be held on 4 &#8211; 11 March 2012, in Istanbul, Turkey.</p>\n<p>Imagine a world that your data would never been lost or a harddisk that does not fit in your pockets. The days that you can reach your data with just one password are not far away. Cloud Computing is going to shape future computers. It is the new trend in IT World which will change all human habits. In this workshop following topics are going to be discussed;</p>\n<p>-What is Cloud Computing?</p>\n<p>-Advantages and disadvantages of Cloud Computing</p>\n<p>-Services of Cloud Computing</p>\n<p>-Attitude of companies</p>\n<p>-Distincts between classical methods and Cloud Computing</p>\n<p>Our goal is to teach what exactly Cloud Computing is and to create ideas for future on this topic which may change the IT World.</p>\n<p>Wait, we havent forgotten the craziest part of our event. Youll forget about any other cities or time youve spent anywhere, and you will never forget your most delightful time in your life, of course in Istanbul. You should know that one week is not enough to see all beauties of Istanbul which is a metropolitan with 17 million population; however, you ll have an unforgettable 7 days without doubt. As one of the biggest cities, Istanbul is full of beauties, cultural activities, historical places and delightful nightlife of course. Istanbul has become the capital of 3 biggest empires of the history; <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Roman_Empire" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://en.wikipedia.org'']);" target="_blank">Roman</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Byzantine_Empire" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://en.wikipedia.org'']);" target="_blank">Byzantine</a> and <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ottoman_Empire" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://en.wikipedia.org'']);" target="_blank">Ottoman Empire</a>. So just guess how old the city is and how much diversity and historical richness it includes. We are going to take you to <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Topkapi_Palace_Museum" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://en.wikipedia.org'']);" target="_blank">Topkap</a> and <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dolmabahe_Palace" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://en.wikipedia.org'']);" target="_blank">Dolmabahe Palaces</a> where the Ottoman Sultans resided, the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hagia_Sophia" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://en.wikipedia.org'']);" target="_blank">Hagia Sophia Museum</a> from the 6th century, the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sultan_Ahmed_Mosque" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://en.wikipedia.org'']);" target="_blank">Blue Mosque</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Basilica_Cistern" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://en.wikipedia.org'']);" target="_blank">Basilica Cistern</a> and some more surprise beautiful places. Participants will also have the chance to watch both Asian and European Part from the middle of the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bosphorus" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://en.wikipedia.org'']);" target="_blank">Bosphorus</a> when we are making Bosphorus Tour as a tradition. You will taste <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Turkish_Cuisine" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://en.wikipedia.org'']);" target="_blank">Turkish Cuisine</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nargile" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://en.wikipedia.org'']);" target="_blank">Nargile</a> and <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rak" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://en.wikipedia.org'']);" target="_blank">Rak</a> with Turkish hospitality. Can you imagine a street where about 1 million peopele walks on just in one day? That streets name is Istiklal and parties will be held in <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/stiklal_Avenue" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://en.wikipedia.org'']);" target="_blank">Istiklal Avenue</a> which is the most crowded and crazy street you can ever see. Please do not forget to bring extra SD Cards for your camera, because your card will be full at the end of the first day!</p>\n<p>Are you still waiting to apply ? ? LC ISTANBUL is ready for you ! ! Apply via <a href="http://eestec.net/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://eestec.net'']);" target="_blank">eestec.net</a> with your motivational letter before 2nd of February.</p>\n<p>For more information do not hestitate to contact us via <a href="mailto:emrecoskun1036@gmail.com" target="_blank">emrecoskun1036@gmail.com</a></p>\n<p>Our website: <a href="http://www.eestec.itu.edu.tr" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.eestec.itu.edu.tr'']);" target="_blank">www.eestec.itu.edu.tr</a></p>\n<p>In addition; to help you to know at least a little about;</p>\n<p>Istanbul, <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=m-lh6zH74nQ" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.youtube.com'']);" target="_blank">Istanbul &#8211; 2010 European Capital of Culture</a> , <a href="ht