(2287, 1, '2011-05-31 19:34:18', '2011-05-31 18:34:18', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers!</p>\n<p>After great success in organizing Trainers Meeting in October 2010, LC Banja Luka is honored to present our next workshop called <strong>Let the penguin in</strong>!, that will be held from 23.07  29.07.2011.</p>\n<p>Topic of our workshop is <strong>virtualization</strong>. You will learn about major problems and development of this framework, implementation, purpose &#8211; server consolidation, load balancing, security, types of virtualization and concepts used alongside. Academic part will include interesting lectures from experienced teachers from the field and hands-on labs on GNU/Linux distribution  Debian.</p>\n<p>This week will be incredibly exciting because of three things:</p>\n<p>1. International Debian Conference  this year <strong>DebCon11</strong> will be held in Banja Luka. We will use this opportunity to introduce you to Debian distribution and go to Debian Day. There you will listen to experts from this field. You can find more about this conference on <a href="http://www.debconf.org/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.debconf.org'']);" target="_blank">http://www.debconf.org/</a></p>\n<p>2. This will be the most exciting week in Banja Luka because 4th <strong>Demofest</strong> festival is going to be held at the same time! Demofest is festival and competition of young demo bands from all over the Balkan. This year 438 bands applied and only 30 will get the chance to compete. Also, you will listen to Trickys, Kelis and Skindreads concerts (type of music: rock, metal, punk, reggae).</p>\n<p>Read more about Demofest on <a href="http://www.demofest.org/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.demofest.org'']);" target="_blank">http://www.demofest.org/</a></p>\n<p>3. Our workshop J As always we promise you a lot of <strong>great food</strong> and <strong>crazy parties</strong>. We wont miss the chance to take you to <strong>best RAFTING in the world</strong>, on one of the worlds best rivers for this kind of sport (there were European Championship 2005, Euro Cup 2007, World Championship 2009 in Banja Luka).</p>\n<p>There will be many more interesting things that you feel only when you are part of this event. Come and feel the beauty of summer in the city on Vrbas!</p>\n<p>We are waiting for you applications and hope to see you in Banja Luka!!</p>\n<p>If you have any questions, contact our CP Marija Racic at: <a href="mailto:elmaars@gmail.com" target="_blank">marija.racicc@gmail.com</a></p>\n', 'Let the penguin IN', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'let-the-penguin-in', '', '', '2011-05-31 19:34:18', '2011-05-31 18:34:18', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/let-the-penguin-in/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2288, 1, '2011-05-27 21:15:01', '2011-05-27 20:15:01', '\n<p>Hello my dear EESTECers!</p>\n<p>LC Rijeka is again organizing the traditional summer exchange RiSEx 2011 in period 19.7-25.7.2011. Just like every year, we guarantee you a lot of fun, sun and the beach. Among all things, we have organized you an attractive trip, cruise with the tourist boat in the Kvarner bay, parties on the beach, crazy city relly, visit to Opatija, one of the most beautiful cities at the nothern Adriatic Sea, and many, many more.</p>\n<p>It is very easy to find us. You can travel to here by train, over Zagreb or Ljubljana, by car, bus (driving on new and high quality highways), or by plane via one of the nearby airports (Zagreb, Ljubljana, Venezia). Do not hesistate one single moment, but start slowly with packing the sunscreen in your bag and we are waiting for your applications. This year we are accepting 20 participants. See you in Rijeka. We are looking forward to your arrival.</p>\n<p>P.S. For all of you who need a little more persuation to sign up, we decided to post this video clip, &#8217;cause all you know a picture is worth thousand words <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif'' alt='';)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n<p><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QIiYY9jRnCw" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.youtube.com'']);" target="_blank">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QIiYY9jRnCw</a></p>\n', 'Rijeka Summer Exchange 2011', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'rijeka-summer-exchange-2011', '', '', '2011-05-27 21:15:01', '2011-05-27 20:15:01', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/rijeka-summer-exchange-2011/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2289, 1, '2011-05-24 09:14:40', '2011-05-24 08:14:40', '\n<p><strong>LC Sarajevo is proud to announce that eMovie Academy is becoming a tradition, and it&#8217;s your chance to make your dreams come true <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' />  7 days of glamour on one of the biggest European movie festivals, 7 days of an unforgettable atmosphere which one awesome LC will provide for you, 7 days of pure EESTEC spirit, 7 nights of crazy fun and a lot more! Deadline for applying is 15.06.2011. Don&#8217;t miss it!</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>How many times have you watched movie stars on the red carpet and wished to be one of them? You watch reports about film festivals on TV and you think you&#8217;ll never be able to be part of that world? Ever wanted to try to be an actor, screenwriter, producer or editor of a movie?</p>\n<p>LC Sarajevo is proud to announce that <strong>eMovie Academy</strong> is becoming a tradition, and it&#8217;s your chance to make your dreams come true <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> . 7 days of glamour on one of the biggest European movie festivals, 7 days of an unforgettable atmosphere which one awesome LC will provide for you, 7 days of pure EESTEC spirit, 7 nights of crazy fun and a lot more!</p>\n<p>The academical part of the event will consist of lectures about movies, editing, and filming. You will learn about editing a movie in professional software tools. Lectures are going to be held by experienced people in the movie domain, meaning that after them you&#8217;ll be able to (and you will) make your own movie <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif'' alt='';)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> .</p>\n<p>In the period from 22.07. until 29.07. Sarajevo becomes overflowed with people, visited by famous actors and movie lovers from many countries. This is the period of one of the most respected movie festivals in Europe &#8211; the Sarajevo Film Festival (<a href="http://www.sff.ba/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.sff.ba'']);" target="_blank">www.sff.ba</a>). During these days Sarajevo lives 24/7, and we will make sure that you feel it from first hand experience through unforgettable nights, parties, people, and also by arranging accommodation at the center of the city.</p>\n<p>We will also present you cultural beauties of Sarajevo, the place where West and East meet, the diversity of our delicious food (like evapi, burek, baklava&#8230;), our natural wealth and our cultural and historical heritage&#8230;</p>\n<p>Deadline for applying is <strong>15.06.2011</strong>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The official website of eMovie Academy is already online: <a href="http://www.ema.eestec-sa.ba/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.ema.eestec-sa.ba'']);" target="_blank">www.ema.eestec-sa.ba</a>.</p>\n<p>You can find more information about Sarajevo on:</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.sarajevo.ba/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.sarajevo.ba'']);" target="_blank">www.sarajevo.ba</a><br />\n<a href="http://www.sarajevo-tourism.com/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.sarajevo-tourism.com'']);" target="_blank">www.sarajevo-tourism.com</a></p>\n<p>If you have any questions, feel free to contact me on <a href="mailto:elmica.bh@gmail.com" target="_blank">elmica.bh@gmail.com</a>. I&#8217;ll be pleased to answer.</p>\n<p>So, don&#8217;t hesitate and apply now for the greatest fun you&#8217;ll have this summer!</p>\n<p>Can&#8217;t wait to see you all soon in the capital of The Heart-shaped Land!</p>\n<p><strong>Enjoy NATURE. Enjoy FRIENDSHIP. Enjoy CRAZY. Enjoy LAZY. Enjoy EAST. Enjoy WEST. Enjoy LIFE. Enjoy BOSNIA AND HERZEGOVINA.</strong></p>\n', 'eMovie Academy', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'emovie-academy', '', '', '2011-05-24 09:14:40', '2011-05-24 08:14:40', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/emovie-academy/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2290, 1, '2011-05-05 19:13:32', '2011-05-05 18:13:32', '\n<p>Dear EESTECER&#8217;s ;</p>\n<p>We proud to announce that our first Workshop,&#8221; Don&#8217;t hate it, Just do it!!&#8221; will be held</p>\n<p>on 5th-11th September 2011. Excellent city will have legendary Workshop!!</p>\n<p>In Turkey, electromagnetism and microwave topics are the most hated subjects . We</p>\n<p>thought that topics are not a big deal, we can handle them and we decide to do it &#8221; Don&#8217;t hate it, Just</p>\n<p>do it!!&#8221;. During Workshop we will learn what dipole antenna is and how we can build it. We will</p>\n<p>participate sessions about microwave and electromagnetism.</p>\n<p>I can hear that you are asking about social activities. We have great activities for you!</p>\n<p>We will have a boat trip for a day, beautiful bays, islands, sun and fun! Another day we will visit</p>\n<p>ancient Ephesus city and an old village which is irince, the village of vines!! and there is one more</p>\n<p>activity which is a big suprise for you!! Don&#8217;t forget to bring your swimming stuff</p>\n<p>Don&#8217;t worry about parties because you will learn that what party really is.</p>\n<p>Don&#8217;t wait, let&#8217;s do it! Just Apply!!</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Big Hugs from JLC zmir!!</p>\n', 'Don&#8217;t Hate it, Just Do it!!', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'dont-hate-it-just-do-it', '', '', '2011-05-05 19:13:32', '2011-05-05 18:13:32', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/dont-hate-it-just-do-it/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2291, 1, '2011-04-30 17:04:06', '2011-04-30 16:04:06', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>Do you know what a midsummer fest is? Do you know how it is celebrated in Latvia?</p>\n<p>The best way to find it out is to join real midsummer fest in Latvia. LC Riga is proud to present you our newest exchange When the night meets day. It will take place in Latvia from 22nd till 26th June.</p>\n<p>We want to show you how we Latvians celebrate our biggest fest all over the country.</p>\n<p>The first days and last we will spend discovering the beautiful city of Riga, located on the confluence of the river Daugava and at seaside. The participants will learn about the Latvian culture through sightseeing, enjoying the cuisine, seeing the nightlife and admiring city in the evening.</p>\n<p>And there are some reasons why you should come:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>to learn  from other students and share your knowledge, experiences, thoughts and ideas with the best EESTEC students.</li>\n<li>to take a look at the best technical university in Latvia- RTU, and see what student life is like here</li>\n<li>to see Latvia- small and beautiful country that just few years ago stepped into the EU</li>\n<li>to enjoy the capital of Latvia- Riga</li>\n<li>to practice and share your English skills and also learn some Latvian words and traditions</li>\n<li>to make unforgettable friends from different countries</li>\n<li>to have fun <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' />  -&gt; lots of fun!!! :)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>We can assure you that this will be unforgettable. So pack you summer clothing, cause Latvia is waiting for you!</p>\n<p>Yours sincerely,</p>\n<p><strong>LC Riga <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </strong></p>\n', 'When night meets day', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'when-night-meets-day', '', '', '2011-04-30 17:04:06', '2011-04-30 16:04:06', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/when-night-meets-day/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2292, 1, '2011-04-07 20:39:05', '2011-04-07 19:39:05', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,<br />\nas you all must already know, we make awesome events (if you haven&#8217;t heard, just ask anybody who&#8217;s been to Zagreb!), and we know you have been waiting to apply to our next one <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif'' alt='';)'' class=''wp-smiley'' />  Well, the opportunity to come to Zagreb is finally here, and if you haven&#8217;t yet decided are you coming, read the rest of our invitation!</p>\n<p>This year&#8217;s theme will be <strong>&#8220;Modern Telecomunications: Linking people everywhere!&#8221;</strong> or as we like to call it <strong>&#8220;Kinky Linky&#8221;</strong> <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_razz.gif'' alt='':P'' class=''wp-smiley'' />  You will have several very interesting classes held by young professors from our telecommunications department, and some insight on how it looks like in reality, from a real company, so even the academic part will be fun!</p>\n<p><em><span style="text-decoration: underline;">What else we&#8217;ve got you&#8217;re wondering? </span></em>OK, if you haven&#8217;t heard about wonderful Croatian nature you are really missing a lot! Google it and look at the pictures&#8230;[5 minutes later]You must be interested now <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif'' alt='';)'' class=''wp-smiley'' />  We will show you some beautiful sights on our field trips and that is not all, &#8217;cause you also get to experience the Croatian culture and not to mention our awesome food and drinks!<br />\nYou will definitely not leave hungry or thirsty, but you will be eager to come back to taste Croatia again <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n<p><em><span style="text-decoration: underline;">You&#8217;re asking yourselves what about the real memorable having fun part which everyone forgets because of too much alcohol?</span></em><br />\nNow that&#8217;s our strongest card, so don&#8217;t come tired or wanting to rest, we are not going to allow that,<br />\n<strong>you ARE going to party every day and it IS going to be  legen&#8230;dary <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif'' alt='';)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </strong> Word.</p>\n<p>It doesn&#8217;t matter where we take you, we will make your time here unforgettable, so come and meet us,<br />\nit will be a great spring week for you, we guarantee it!!<br />\nStart packing, we are waiting for you, and remember, wine is fine but whiskey is quicker!</p>\n<p>LC Zagreb <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n', 'Modern Telecomunications: Linking people everywhere!', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'modern-telecomunications-linking-people-everywhere', '', '', '2011-04-07 20:39:05', '2011-04-07 19:39:05', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/modern-telecomunications-linking-people-everywhere/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2293, 1, '2011-04-01 17:39:53', '2011-04-01 16:39:53', '\n<p>Dear EESTEC-ers,</p>\n<p>We LC Skopje are delighted to announce you that we are organizing something special  the workshop &#8220;Feel the Energy 2&#8243;. We invite you to explore the possibilities of the renewable energy sources and the wittiness of the self sustainable philosophy. Besides the energy we intend to create some unforgettable memories while round tripping our small but beautiful country from 1st till 8th May.</p>\n<p>We have arranged a mix of experts  finest selection of professors, experts from the industry and members of the Macedonian Academy of Science and Arts.<br />\nPrepare your diving suits because we are going to dive in the world of renewables. From our starting point the Global trends, we will dive in the &#8211; How to create energetic strategy lecture to get to the cliff called Investments in renewables and Energetic world trends . Lots of corrals and pearls by the coast are guaranteed like visiting: solar farm, Biogas factory and hydro plant with high end automation.</p>\n<p>We intend to light up the Skopje nightlife with our glossy parties, so we have prepared some fuel for your alcohol driven generators. But read carefully, you will need to do the wiring, and we dont have user manuals. And hey, did somebody mention clubbing, wine tasting and enjoying different meals and drinks during the international night?<br />\nShhhh, that supposed to be a secret. But its not a secret that you will feel the undying vibe of Macedonian tradition while visiting a traditional restaurant where archaic Macedonian songs and dances are performed by musical masters.</p>\n<p>And that is not all! At the end of the 4 day knowledge-gaining marathon you may feel that your batteries are quite low&#8230; But dont worry!  ! You&#8217;ll surely recharge the energy during the amazing weekend. How? LC Skopje is organizing a tour to the most gorgeous and peaceful city in Macedonia  Ohrid. OK it would not be that peaceful once we arrive. You can walk by the shores of the Balkan pearl  the lake of Ohrid holding hands with your new friend. You will visit the breathtaking old part of the city and take a boat trip to the St. Naums Monastery and its wonderful area. The beautiful sunset by the two romantic little isles make this location attractive spot for the tourists and renewables experts too J. And for the party animals dont forget the clubs that we will visit during the endless nights to suck that little crumb of energy you have left over <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n<p>So what are you waiting for, come to Macedonia and feel the timeless energy that flows in this wonderful land&#8230;</p>\n<p>Apply now! <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif'' alt='';)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n<p>In addition to help you to know at least a little about Ohrid and Macedonia<br />\n<a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=meeKffWE_Uc" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.youtube.com'']);" target="_blank">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=meeKffWE_Uc</a><br />\n<a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=t_sOTaG3FP8" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.youtube.com'']);" target="_blank">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=t_sOTaG3FP8</a></p>\n<p>Kind Regards and see you in Skopje,<br />\nFor more information feel free and ask me whenever you want. <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n', 'Feel the Energy 2', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'feel-the-energy-2', '', '', '2011-04-01 17:39:53', '2011-04-01 16:39:53', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/feel-the-energy-2/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2294, 1, '2011-04-01 17:07:55', '2011-04-01 16:07:55', '\n<p><strong>EESTEC GOT THE POWER!</strong></p>\n<p>LC Famagusta proudly presents Power Island where the participants will be able to fullfill the power of eeStec to every part of their bodies.</p>\n<p>The workshop will contain, sessions about the Industrial Usage of High Voltage as well as technical trips to Thermic Plants all around the island. During the workshop, participants will be able to discover the latest technology in our Technopark such as 3D laser printers, robotix and other new developments of our university labs and realize the island technology.</p>\n<p>Do we need to mention about Parties ? We will bring our participants to our spring fest where they will enjoy the 2003 Eurovision Song Contest Winner and 2009 MTV European Music Award Winner. We are inviting you over to share the great fun in our tropical campus with more than 15000 students including people from 68 different countries. Yacht Party, City Rally, Windsurfing, Karaoke Parties, Discos, Sea, Sun, Beach Parties, Beaches and Beaches&#8230; what else do you need?</p>\n<p>You will miss a lot if you miss this event, that&#8217;s for sure but you are already aware of that, aren&#8217;t you? <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n<p>Any hesitation would be greatly not accepted! We will be more than glad to answer your questions about anything.</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VRJtyYVMeUg" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.youtube.com'']);" target="_blank">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VRJtyYVMeUg</a></p>\n', 'Power Island', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'power-island', '', '', '2011-04-01 17:07:55', '2011-04-01 16:07:55', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/power-island/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2295, 1, '2011-03-24 13:46:46', '2011-03-24 12:46:46', '\n<p>Dear fellow EESTECers,</p>\n<p>EESTEC LC Budapest (MAVE) in cooperation with Siemens Healthcare and the Budapest University of Technology and Economics proudly presents a week-long professional event in Budapest, a place where future is present!</p>\n<p>If you want to participate in the most medtech workshop in the history of EESTEC, get prepared now! Submit your scientific abstract following the guidelines in the form and send it with your application!</p>\n<p>Participants will have to present their field of research or studies relevant to CIS. Applications must include a fully filled Application form, including the 2-page abstract supporting the proposed presentation sent to <a href="mailto: cis2011@eestec.hu" target="_blank">cis2011@eestec.hu</a> by 22th May. Selection will be made based on scientific merit and geographic variety.</p>\n<p>What kind of presentation are we awaiting from you? Topics include (but are not limited to) medical robot systems, mechatronics and control, medical imaging, image processing and registration, treatment planning, image-guided surgery, patient, rehabilitation and assistive robotics, surgery and diagnosis.</p>\n<p>The academic program will take 5 days, including tutorials from professors visiting from all over the world; your presentation, university and Siemens labs tours. Hands-on minimally-invasive surgical training session will also be included.</p>\n<p>After the hardworking days, we will take a train to our beloved lake Velence, and have time to rest and enjoy the beautiful Hungarian summer on the beach.</p>\n<p>During this week, you will spend time not only with people from EESTEC but will get a chance to meet other student organizations: learn with IEEE plus EMSA, party with AEGEE and train with ESTIEM.</p>\n<p>We are eagerly waiting for your application!</p>\n<p>On behalf of all the organizers,<br />\n<strong>Adam Kovacs-Veres</strong><br />\nVice-chairman, LC Budapest</p>\n', 'Computer Integrated Surgery', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'computer-integrated-surgery', '', '', '2011-03-24 13:46:46', '2011-03-24 12:46:46', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/computer-integrated-surgery/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2296, 1, '2011-03-19 19:15:47', '2011-03-19 18:15:47', '\n<p>Dear Eestecers <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n<p>We are happy to inform you that LC Athens organises a workshop during 21st &#8211; 29th May called &#8221;Dreamers Become Winners&#8221; !!!!</p>\n<p>The subject of this workshop will be entrepreunership &#8211; a concept which gets more and more important for youth in these crazy days of crisis.</p>\n<p>Best professors of our faculty will  hold lectures designed to catch your full attention<br />\nand through interactive learning you will finally run your own business and maybe become rich and famous?! one day..</p>\n<p>Moreover,we will have some trainings so that you will be able to obtain the appropriate so-called soft skills and also get acquaired with green energy and innovations which are the latest trend. You will also have the chance to practice those soft skills through real activities.</p>\n<p>Last but not least you will have the opportunity to see our facilities, laboratories and come in contact with students and professors of National Technical University of Athens.</p>\n<p>Is that all???? NOOOO?? What about the entertainment part!?</p>\n<p>You  will have the chance to..</p>\n<p>- spend a memorable week in lively Athens that you ll never ever forget..</p>\n<p>- visit some of the most interesting historical sights and museums  of Athens, including the brand new Acropolis Museum</p>\n<p>- participate in some really crazy and wild parties</p>\n<p>- visit an exotic greek island (Agkistri) for a day ,swim ,get tanned, have a great beach party and make your friends green with envy</p>\n<p>- strengthen your eestec spirit and make amazing new friends all over Europe</p>\n<p>What are you waiting for?!!</p>\n<p>Just apply <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n<p>Athens will be all yours!!</p>\n<p>PS. As you may already know this workshop will be funded by the Youth in Action programme. So don&#8217;t forget that we will refund 70% of participants&#8217; travel cost! (for those who have sent us Part 3 document:</p>\n<p>Ankara, Banja Luka, Belgrade, Budapest, East Sarajevo, Istanbul, Krakow, Ljubljana, Madrid, Maribor, Munich, Novi Sad,Podgorica,Riga,Trieste &amp; Zurich !! )</p>\n', 'Dreamers Become Winners', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'dreamers-become-winners', '', '', '2011-03-19 19:15:47', '2011-03-19 18:15:47', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/dreamers-become-winners/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2297, 1, '2011-02-19 17:07:07', '2011-02-19 16:07:07', '\n<p>Fellow EESTECers!</p>\n<p>LC Krakw is more than just happy to announce third edition of workshop on IT Security &#8211; KrakYourNet3. This year our flag event will be held between 10th and 16th of April 2011, in Krakw, the jewel of polish cities and Zakopane, magnificent gate to Tatra Mountains and Tatra National Park. We have put our effort on educational part of the event. Our aim is to provide best lecturers and lectures to be as much consolidated as they can be. Of course to leave more time for our dear participants to party and see our beautiful country!</p>\n<p>If you are interested in IT and always aware of your safety in the net this event is for you! You will get the tools to stay safe and you will see how your on-line security is threatened in so many various ways&#8230; On the other hand if you do not have a clue about Internet security this event will open your eyes and give you a candle in the darkness of nowadays chambers of IT!</p>\n<p>Last but not least we have prepared awesome activities to keep you busy with parties, sightseeing and simply having fun all the time you are not at the lectures. I do not count sleeping time, cause there will be none! You will have opportunity to see Krakw, medieval city of polish kings and Zakopane, village in Tatra Mountains where we will go for excursion. To sum up: hiking, grilling, sightseeing, partying, no sleeping and more.</p>\n<p>Everyones invited! Apply, come, meet us, learn something about IT, see Krakw and party wildly with us!!!</p>\n', 'KrakYourNet3', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'krakyournet3', '', '', '2011-02-19 17:07:07', '2011-02-19 16:07:07', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/krakyournet3/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2298, 1, '2011-02-19 15:42:33', '2011-02-19 14:42:33', '\n<p>Search engines are the main instruments used for seeking information on the web. They have been subject to deep changes, such as the web, and for this reason LC Cosenza is pleased to announce that a workshop, whose title is &#8220;Search Engines: Indexing, Optimization And Marketing from Web 2.0 to Social Networks&#8221;, is taking place from May 16 to May 23. Deadline: April 16, 2011.</p>\n<p>The topics, which will be discussed, concern with the indexing techniques used to find out new e-contents, and SEO experts will be helping us to deepen optimization techniques to be adopted to improve web sites, blogs and extra resources presentations.</p>\n<p>Moreover, some marketing instruments provided from search engines will be introduced and compared to unconventional marketing techniques, taking into account the importance of social networks.</p>\n<p>Furthermore, you will be offered our warm Italian hospitality as well as funny times and parties.</p>\n<p>SEO, SEF, SEM, #HashTag and other keywords are waiting for you!!!</p>\n', 'Search Engines: Indexing, Optimization And Marketing from Web 2.0 to Social Networks', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'search-engines-indexing-optimization-and-marketing-from-web-2-0-to-social-networks', '', '', '2011-02-19 15:42:33', '2011-02-19 14:42:33', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/search-engines-indexing-optimization-and-marketing-from-web-2-0-to-social-networks/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2299, 1, '2011-01-29 07:39:47', '2011-01-29 06:39:47', '\n<p>Hello my dear EESTECers!</p>\n<p>This year again we are organizing &#8220;Rijeka Carnival Exchange 2011&#8243;. Rijeka&#8217;s Carnival has imposed to our city, region and Croatia like the fifth season &#8211; time of craziness and relaxation, and its rich entertainment, sports and cultural programs had satisfied all ages and tastes. Defiant to space and time, Carnival in a warm host to every person of good will who search escape from the gloomy everyday in the game, laughter, fun and vine <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' />  . LC Rijeka is again participating in main Carnival event as TNT dynamites (<a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wn7ZGZn_sFw" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.youtube.com'']);" target="_blank">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wn7ZGZn_sFw</a>). The application form is in upper link.</p>\n<p>See you in Rijeka. Bye!</p>\n', 'Rijeka Carnival Exchange 2011', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'rijeka-carnival-exchange-2011', '', '', '2011-01-29 07:39:47', '2011-01-29 06:39:47', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/rijeka-carnival-exchange-2011/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2300, 1, '2011-01-26 10:30:12', '2011-01-26 09:30:12', '\n<p>The event is organized in form of workshop with set of lectures followed by labs. The main focus is on developing Android applications. The entertainment part of the event is based on Rabadan Carnival in Bellinzona  (<a href="http://www.rabadan.ch/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.rabadan.ch'']);" target="_blank">http://www.rabadan.ch</a>), this is the most famous and the craziest event in Switzerland. We would kindly ask all the participants to bring carnival masks in order not to feel stupid there <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif'' alt='';)'' class=''wp-smiley'' />  Guided tours around beautiful Lugano lake are foreseen as well. Optionally skiing and chocolate museum visit are offered.</p>\n<p>We hope you will go back home with an unforgeable experience and a fancy (hopefully commercially exploitive) Android application that will change your lives and the world <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif'' alt='';)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> )</p>\n<p>Location: <a href="http://maps.google.com/maps?f=q&amp;source=s_q&amp;hl=en&amp;geocode=&amp;q=Lugano,+Switzerland&amp;aq=0&amp;sll=37.0625,-95.677068&amp;sspn=55.411532,79.013672&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;hq=&amp;hnear=Lugano,+Ticino,+Switzerland&amp;t=h&amp;z=13&amp;iwloc=A" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://maps.google.com'']);" target="_blank">Lugano, Switzerland</a></p>\n<p>More information on Lugano you may find at <a href="http://www.lugano-tourism.ch/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.lugano-tourism.ch'']);" target="_blank">http://www.lugano-tourism.ch</a></p>\n<p>We are eagerly waiting your applications!</p>\n<p>EESTEC LC Lugano</p>\n', 'Lugano goes mobile!', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'lugano-goes-mobile', '', '', '2011-01-26 10:30:12', '2011-01-26 09:30:12', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/lugano-goes-mobile/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2301, 1, '2011-01-24 20:02:30', '2011-01-24 19:02:30', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers;</p>\n<p>LC Istanbul is happy and proud to announce our upcoming workshop <strong>MANAGINATION11</strong>  (Management and Imagination ) which will be held on 6 &#8211; 13 March 2011, in Istanbul, Turkey. We have prepared you a fantastic event with the main subject project management and innovation.</p>\n<p>Have you ever wanted to be a leader? You have to organize some projects but there are lots of problems around you to solve? You take responsibilities but there is less time than you need?  Then, this event is for you because we prepared to give the secrets of these problems during seminars, presentations and trainings.  The aim of our event is improve your hidden talents and help you to have a good business career. On the other hand, we also want to show you how is important the creativity for an engineer.  The way of getting out the steps easily will be shared with our lucky participants by experienced trainers of world-famous companies.</p>\n<p>Do you think that weve forgotten the best part of our event? We have to confess; making extraordinary parties, knocking around and make people crazy is more and more easy for us when you compare with the academic part : )) You should know that one week is not enough to see all beauties of Istanbul which is a metropolitan with 17 million population ; however,  you ll have an unforgettable 7 days without doubt. Istanbul is full of beauties, cultural activities, historical places and nightlife of course <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':-)'' class=''wp-smiley'' />  This city has become the capital of 3 biggest empires of the history (Roman, Byzantium and Ottoman). So just guess how old the city is and how much diversity and richness it includes. We are going to take you to Topkapi and Dolmabahce Palaces where the Ottoman Sultans resided, the Hagia Sophia Museum from the 6th century, the Blue Mosque, Basilica Cistern and some more surprise places. Participants will also have the chance to watch both Asian and European Part from the middle of the Marmara sea when we are making Bosphorus Tour as usual. And the parties will be held in Istiklal Avenue which is the most crowded and crazy street you can ever see.</p>\n<p>Are you still waiting to apply ?  ? LC ISTANBUL is ready for you ! ! =)</p>\n<p>For more information feel free and ask me whenever you want. Our website (<a href="http://www.eestec.itu.edu.tr/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.eestec.itu.edu.tr'']);" target="_blank">www.eestec.itu.edu.tr</a>) will be update soon.</p>\n<p>In addition; to help you to know at least a little about Istanbul <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=m-lh6zH74nQ&amp;feature=related" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.youtube.com'']);" target="_blank">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=m-lh6zH74nQ&amp;feature=related</a> and Turkey <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7CBllQ3Uchk" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.youtube.com'']);" target="_blank">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7CBllQ3Uchk</a></p>\n<p>Kind Regards and see you in Istanbul,</p>\n<p>Melih Krat DEMRDREK</p>\n<p>Contact Person of LC ISTANBUL</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.eestec.itu.edu.tr/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.eestec.itu.edu.tr'']);" target="_blank">More information about this event</a></p>\n', 'Managination&#8217;11', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'managination11', '', '', '2011-01-24 20:02:30', '2011-01-24 19:02:30', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/managination11/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2302, 1, '2011-01-24 19:53:23', '2011-01-24 18:53:23', '\n<p>Please note that our EU grant application is still pending, so all EESTECers from LCs that have not sent us part3 documents are also encouraged to apply.<br />\nThe event will take place, <strong>regardless</strong> of the outcome of the EU grant.<br />\nAs for our applicants, we take your <strong>priority lists</strong> and <strong>motivational letters</strong><br />\ninto account when selecting participants.</p>\n<p>After the great success last year&#8217;s WiE, we are proud to announce that we and<br />\nour Gender Studies department (Gender Zentrum) are working together to make it<br />\nhappen again this year.</p>\n<p>The academic part of the workshop will cover the same topics as last year<br />\n(difficulties and barriers for women in engineering jobs, women&#8217;s networks as<br />\nwell as job- and life-planning), but these topics will be approached from a<br />\ndifferent angle this year, so, even if you participated last year, it might be<br />\nworth it to apply again.</p>\n<p>Furthermore, there will be a women&#8217;s contact forum during which you&#8217;ll have<br />\nthe opportunity to interact and exchange experiences with other women working<br />\nin engineering jobs.</p>\n<p>Apart from the lectures, we&#8217;ll of course be showing you the city of Munich,<br />\nit&#8217;s nightlife and cultural aspects.</p>\n<p>The workshop will conclude with the International Motivation Weekend. This<br />\nevent will be held at a house in Austria (near Salzburg) with a great view.<br />\nHere you&#8217;ll be participating in soft-skill training and, of course, some<br />\nunforgettable parties.</p>\n<p>We&#8217;re looking forward to your application</p>\n<p>Important: <strong>Only women may apply!</strong></p>\n<p>Hope to see you in May!</p>\n', 'WiE &#8211; Women in Engineering', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'wie-women-in-engineering', '', '', '2011-01-24 19:53:23', '2011-01-24 18:53:23', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/wie-women-in-engineering/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2303, 1, '2011-01-24 19:46:58', '2011-01-24 18:46:58', '\n<p><strong>Please note</strong> that our EU grant application is still pending, so all EESTECers from LCs that<br />\nhave not sent us part3 documents are also encouraged to apply.<br />\nThe event will take place, <strong>regardless</strong> of the outcome of the EU grant.<br />\nAs for our applicants, we take your <strong>priority lists</strong> and <strong>motivational letters</strong><br />\ninto account when selecting participants.</p>\n<p>We are happy to announce our Dr. med. Nano workshop.</p>\n<p>This workshop will cover some interesting points about the interaction between<br />\nnano technology and medical engineering. There will be lectures, about both<br />\ntopics as well as a hands-on lab on the development of nanosensors on a<br />\nbimolecular basis during which you&#8217;ll learn how to build your own sensor.</p>\n<p>We&#8217;ll be cooperating with two departments in our university, so the lectures<br />\nwill be held by our professors.</p>\n<p>Of course you will also see the great city of Munich, experience the Bavarian<br />\nway of life and Bavarian hospitality. Also be prepared for Munich&#8217;s nightlife<br />\nand some unforgettable parties.</p>\n<p>The workshop will conclude with the International Motivation Weekend. This<br />\nevent will be held at a house in Austria (near Salzburg) with a great view.<br />\nHere you&#8217;ll be participating in soft-skill training and, of course, more<br />\npartying.</p>\n<p>It&#8217;ll be a great week&#8230; so don&#8217;t hesitate to apply!</p>\n<p>DEADLINE: 2011/04/08 18:00:00 GMT+2</p>\n', 'Dr. med. Nano', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'dr-med-nano', '', '', '2011-01-24 19:46:58', '2011-01-24 18:46:58', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/dr-med-nano/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2304, 1, '2011-01-24 19:35:47', '2011-01-24 18:35:47', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>LC Madrid is proud to present our new and first event for the 2011!<br />\nDue to the generational change at our local committee and the great change which our society is living, this year we decided to change our minds and focus on something that is closer to us: the SOCIETY. But nowadays everything is global, we all are interconnected with everything, so our society lives and works in NETWORKs.<br />\nFor all these reasons, we have created NETWORK SOCIETY, a new kind of event for us during which, through conferences, seminars and visits to laboratories and research centers, we will try to offer you a wide overview of what is being done in this fields and how our global society is growing up through the network.</p>\n<p>This amazing project will be held in Madrid from  3th April 2011 to 10th April 2011.</p>\n<p>Okay, okay, that all sounds very nice and interesting, but what about the party? WE WANT PARTY!</p>\n<p>Don&#8217;t worry, as we always say: Madrid NEVER sleeps.<br />\nSo, during the whole week you&#8217;ll have a lot of chances to feel Madrid&#8217;s party and lifestyle, visit some of the landmarks of our city and participate in the traditional CityRally. And if that were not enough, during the weekend you will have the opportunity to enjoy some time out the city, practicing some sports and having crazy parties in the countryside!</p>\n<p>Besides, this year we have talked to a psychic who has confirmed that no other Eyjafjallajkull will wake up during our event. Now, what are you waiting for? Apply for the event ASAP, the deadline is 6th February 2011! =&#8217;D</p>\n<p>By the way, there&#8217;s another important point&#8230;<br />\nWe&#8217;re so sorry to have to say this, but as we don&#8217;t apply for EU grant, every year we have to make great efforts to find sponsors for our events, and although we are delighted with the result obtained in this area the last year, in previous events some years back, we had problems with some people showing a total lack of consideration for our work, sleeping during conferences with the sponsors and university professors, which made us lose all our credibility among them&#8230;</p>\n<p>Therefore, this time we expect a similar attitude to the last year and we won&#8217;t tolerate an irresponsible one. And in case of it happens, participants will be warned and eventually expelled from the event if warnings are disregarded.</p>\n<p>When there is time to party, we party (and trust me, there will be! ;D), but when it&#8217;s time to work, we work (and later we have party! ^^).</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.eestec.es/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.eestec.es'']);" target="_blank">More information about this event</a></p>\n<p>We hope to see you all in Madrid!</p>\n<p>Greetings from LC Madrid&#8230;</p>\n', 'Network Society', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'network-society', '', '', '2011-01-24 19:35:47', '2011-01-24 18:35:47', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/network-society/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2305, 1, '2011-01-23 12:11:53', '2011-01-23 11:11:53', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>Let&#8217;s all prepare for magnificent and breathtaking mountain of Durmitor and enjoy an unexpected beautiful and picturesque winter wonderland!</p>\n<p>LC Podgorica is happy to invite eight of you to join 3 days long snowy party in tourist center of National Park Durmitor and winter sports of Montenegro &#8211; the town of abljak,  which is situated in the north-west of Montenegro, 1450 meters above sea level.</p>\n<p>Beside extremely good parties, visitation of National Park and other interesting activities, LC Podgorica will hold training on the topic of Team Building and Project Management. Accordingly, you will have a chance to meet a lot of your colleagues from Electrical Engineering Faculty Podgorica.</p>\n<p>If you have any questions, feel free to ask me <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n<p>Deadline for applying is <strong>7. February 2011</strong>.</p>\n<p>More information about abljak you can discover on: <a href="http://www.durmitorcg.com/opstina_eng.php" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.durmitorcg.com'']);" target="_blank">http://www.durmitorcg.com/opstina_eng.php</a></p>\n<p><strong>It is no wonder that visiting Montenegro during the winter can be full of pleasant surprises.</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Come to discover, experience and enjoy &#8221;Wild Beauty&#8221;!</strong> <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n', 'Durmitor Motivational Weekend', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'durmitor-motivational-weekend', '', '', '2011-01-23 12:11:53', '2011-01-23 11:11:53', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/durmitor-motivational-weekend/', 0, 'events', '', 0);
