(2306, 1, '2011-01-18 20:38:17', '2011-01-18 19:38:17', '\n<p>Dear CPs,</p>\n<p>We&#8217;re happy to announce that LC Belgrade won EU grant and therefore is making preparations for a workshop called &#8221;<strong>Lead the way!</strong>&#8221;.<br />\nThe prime aim of this event is to prepare young people (meaning participants <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> ) with necessary skills and knowledge in order to improve themselves (more), to create successful business plans and start up their own businesses, find financing opportunities and become future leaders in their communities.<br />\nAll of these skills you&#8217;ll get by taking part in different activities, such as: lectures, presentations, working sessions, funny games&#8230;</p>\n<p>Apart from this academic activities, we&#8217;ll do our best to present you the beauties of <a href="http://www.tob.rs/en/index.php" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.tob.rs'']);" target="_blank">our capital</a> (is there anyone who haven&#8217;t heard about Kalish Challenge?!) and its world wide famous nightlife. You&#8217;ll have enough time to enjoy delights of Serbian cuisine and to find out why people fall in love with rakija with the first sip. <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /><br />\nOh, and&#8230;Prepare yourselves for a lot of winter magic, since we&#8217;re taking you to weekend trip to Kopaonik, one of our most attractive mountains.</p>\n<p>We&#8217;d like to thank to all LCs who signed part3 form and made this event possible by giving us their support.<br />\nPlease note that only LCs listed below can send their members to this event, paying respect to referred gender distribution.</p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;" rowspan="2"><strong>LC<br />\n</strong></td>\n<td style="text-align: center;" rowspan="2"><strong>Number of participants<br />\n</strong></td>\n<td style="text-align: center;" colspan="2"><strong>Distribution by gender<br />\n</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><strong>M</strong></td>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><strong>F</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: left;">Ankara</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: left;">Munich</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: left;">Ljubljana</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: left;">Maribor</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: left;">Zagreb</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: left;">Sarajevo</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: left;">East Sarajevo</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: left;">Belgrade</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: left;">Madrid</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: left;">Bucharest</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: left;">Tallinn</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: left;">Athens</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: left;">Podgorica</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: left;">Skopje</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>0</td>\n<td>2</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: left;">Budapest</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>0</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: left;">Delft</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td style="text-align: left;">1</td>\n<td>0</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n', 'Lead the way!', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'lead-the-way', '', '', '2011-01-18 20:38:17', '2011-01-18 19:38:17', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/lead-the-way/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2307, 1, '2011-01-03 22:47:58', '2011-01-03 21:47:58', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>After our third edition of Conquer the markets LC Zrich is proud to announce our new workshop Zrich interactive!</p>\n<p>Despite of the new subject many of the well-tried parts like our famous tram-party and the city rally will take place. In small groups you will design or program games and light animations on our self-made interactive dance floor, which detects movements on it and can be enlightened in all possible colors. Groups will be made according to your preferences and knowledge, so if you do not like to program, you can think about the next party game hit! And it will be played on a 4&#215;2.5m &#8220;Touchscreen&#8221;!</p>\n<p>Check out this video of Snake being played on a smaller version of the dance-floor: <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=um1bMXSOXw8" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.youtube.com'']);" target="_blank">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=um1bMXSOXw8</a></p>\n<p>Besides playing with the dance floor we will visit a <strong>chocolate factory</strong> and go one <strong>whole day skiing</strong>! Like every year there will be <strong>many parties</strong> with much free alcohol <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif'' alt='';-)'' class=''wp-smiley'' />  We are proud to announce that we got the Youth in Action-grant, which means a big part of the travel costs will be paid back to you. Additionally it enables us to organize some special activities you will not forget, ever!</p>\n<p>A temporary schedule can be found here: <a href="http://eestec.net/lc/zurich/zurich-interactive" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://eestec.net'']);" target="_blank">http://eestec.net/lc/zurich/zurich-interactive</a></p>\n<p>If you don&#8217;t have skiing equipment and want to go on the ski-slopes it&#8217;s possible to rent everything. For us it is important that everybody who wants to ski gets the possibility- for this we will pay a part of the renting and ticket costs! And for those not wanting to try skiing, a beautiful day in the snow-covered alps with some sledging and some Glhwein is waiting!</p>\n<p>Best regards and see you in Zrich!!</p>\n<p>Your LC Zrich</p>\n', 'Zrich interactive', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'zurich-interactive', '', '', '2011-01-03 22:47:58', '2011-01-03 21:47:58', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/zurich-interactive/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2308, 1, '2011-01-03 22:40:19', '2011-01-03 21:40:19', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>Dig out your earmuffs, gloves and other winter clothes and get ready for some mind-blowing fun in the snow!</p>\n<p>LC Sarajevo is proud to announce that our EESTEC Winter Olympic Games Sarajevo are becoming a tradition! We are now even more focused on and excited about offering you more fun and entertainment!!</p>\n<p>Everyone knows that when it comes to EESTEC having fun is obligatory so let us prove once again that the EESTEC spirit is alive and kicking!</p>\n<p>It is time to hang up your thinking caps and get ready to party EESTEC STYLE! The parties are going to be crazier, the games more intense than anything you have EVER experienced. This is truly an exchange you will not want to miss out on! (I should also mention that there is no academical part <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> )</p>\n<p>Every night from 22.02.2011 to 27.02.2011 you will be able to experience the Great Spirit of Sarajevo. We will present you cultural beauties of Sarajevo, the place where West and East meet.</p>\n<p>Not only will you experience a cultural mix unlike anywhere in the world and have a chance to meet the friendliest people, but you will also enjoy a weekend on one of our beautiful mountains.</p>\n<p>A true winter wonderland.</p>\n<p>If you have any questions, feel free to contact CP of event Dana Kujan on dzana.kujan@gmail.com.</p>\n<p>Deadline for applying is 25th January 2011.</p>\n<p>More information about Sarajevo and last years EWOGS you can find on:</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.ewogs.com.ba" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.ewogs.com.ba'']);" target="_blank">http://www.ewogs.com.ba</a></p>\n<p><a href="http://www.sarajevo.ba" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.sarajevo.ba'']);" target="_blank">http://www.sarajevo.ba</a></p>\n<p><a href="http://www.sarajevo-tourism.com" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.sarajevo-tourism.com'']);" target="_blank">http://www.sarajevo-tourism.com</a></p>\n<p><strong>Enjoy NATURE. Enjoy FRIENDSHIP. Enjoy CRAZY. Enjoy LAZY. Enjoy EAST. Enjoy WEST. Enjoy LIFE. Enjoy BOSNIA AND HERZEGOVINA.</strong></p>\n', 'Winter Olympic Games Sarajevo', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'winter-olympic-games-sarajevo', '', '', '2011-01-03 22:40:19', '2011-01-03 21:40:19', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/winter-olympic-games-sarajevo/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2309, 1, '2010-12-24 16:14:27', '2010-12-24 15:14:27', '\n<p>Did you ever want to stop the moment? Sometimes the words do not have any meaning,in at that moment an image becomes physical with photographing. If you are one of that people who wants to stop the moment, if your fever is not balanced and if you want to photograph intersection of European and Asian culter together. Then we will give a chance to you to fell more energetic and refreshing yourself with humanistic photosynthesis.</p>\n<p>The main topic of the event is &#8216;photograph&#8217; and &#8216;photoshop&#8217;. Event will be 2 parts; first part will be theoretical, we will give some sessions about how to produce a professional photograph, usage of a professional  camera, details of taking pictures and using photoshop professionally. Sessions will not be only informative but also funny. Second part will be practice, we will go to the area of Anadolu University, to the beautiful nature and historical places of Eskisehir and into the city, to take some good pictures together.</p>\n<p>Sessions will be really funny but also crazy nights of the Eskiehir will be waiting for you. Also we will give you a chance to see the best Turkish Bath in the Turkey, traditional Turkish drink Rak, delicious Turkish foods, Turkish Nargile,and so on&#8230;We will not forget traditional EESTEC nights for sure, multi culture night&#8230;</p>\n<p>LC ESKEHR will host 15 participants, if there will be more applications, we will try to accept best number of the applications which we can do. <strong>If you have your own camera, recommended to take it with you, but if you do not have any camera we will give you one until the end of the event.</strong></p>\n<p>So <strong>we are waiting for you</strong> ,and <strong>what are you waiting for</strong>?</p>\n<p>If you have any question do not hesitate to ask us.</p>\n<p>SEE YOU!</p>\n', 'PhotosynthESis', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'photosynthesis', '', '', '2010-12-24 16:14:27', '2010-12-24 15:14:27', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/photosynthesis/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2310, 1, '2010-12-16 08:48:54', '2010-12-16 07:48:54', '\n<p>Are you interested in space? Do you like Star Wars movies? Would you like to experience Finland&#8217;s beautiful winter? Eestec LC Helsinki proudly presents the first workshop of the year 2011: StarWorks! We have prepared you an awesome workshop about space technology and provided an opportunity to learn cool stuff from famous and crazy scientist guys like Esko Valtaoja!</p>\n<p>We will have super interesting lectures about space, remote sensing, northern lights and satellites. We will also have some fun sessions where you will learn how to study earth from space. Our Department of Radio Science and Engineering will provide you one ECTS (European Credit Transfer and Accumulation System) if you return a diary of the stuff you have learned during the week.</p>\n<p>And no.. we have not forgotten to spoil you with some parties as we are going to throw you to sauna, show you some naked people and teach you how to drink &amp; sing in Finnish academic student party called sitsit. And furthermore, you&#8217;ll experience parties in Helsinki center, movie making with local TV-channel and weekend at a countryside where you can do ice swimming!</p>\n<p>So grab your lightsaber and make sure that you&#8217;ll be in Helsinki at 23rd of January 2011!</p>\n', 'StarWorks', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'starworks', '', '', '2010-12-16 08:48:54', '2010-12-16 07:48:54', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/starworks/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2311, 1, '2010-11-14 14:53:17', '2010-11-14 13:53:17', '\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Hello dear EESTECers,</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">LC Aachen is happy to invite you to this year&#8217;s edition of our traditional Niko-Event.</span> <span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">It takes place from 5.12. (arrival) to 11.12. (departure) 2010. The deadline to apply is the 19.11.2010.</span><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">We have to apologize for announcing the event so late and for the short deadline!</span> <span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">However, we will try to present you some nice days: Instead of workshop-atmosphere with lots of learning and company-visiting, we promise you a small nice meeting in a Christmas fair atmosphere with lots of hot mulled wine, gingerbread and EESTEC-spirit! Furthermore we will have a trip to Cologne and tours around our nice little town.</span> <span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">And of course there is the main event: the Unicup, the annual icehockey-tournament at our University. Your job will be to cheer our teams to victory!</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Should you have any questions, feel free to contact us at any time!</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Hopefully see you soon!</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Andreea Siller (CP Aachen)</span></p>\n', 'Niko-Meeting', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'niko-meeting', '', '', '2010-11-14 14:53:17', '2010-11-14 13:53:17', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/niko-meeting/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2312, 1, '2010-10-22 23:23:41', '2010-10-22 22:23:41', '\n<p>Dear lovely EESTECers;</p>\n<p>Were sure that all of you wonder how to fly a plane? How can a pilot keep all of the aeronautical units in the cockpit under control? As we EESTECers, planes are very important for us and you have a chance to know everything about them thanks to our great(will be) workshop <strong>Above us only sky!</strong> which will take place in Ankara between <strong>4.12.2010 </strong>and <strong>12.12.2010</strong>.</p>\n<p>The main topic of workshop is &#8220;Avionics&#8221; which is a combination of the words &#8220;aviation&#8221; and &#8220;electronics&#8221;. As you may know, especially with the development of unmanned aerial vehicle, avionics has become a very popular topic nowadays.<br />\nDuring the workshop, you&#8217;ll have comprehensive knowledge about avionics by taking lectures regarding subtopics which are navigation, unmanned aerial vehicle, control, avionics history and development, and every other detail you need to know. Trainings will be given by professors and their assistants in Aerospace Engineering Department of Middle East Technical University which is one of the best technical university in Turkey and trainers of TAI(Turkish Aerospace Industries) which is the biggest company in Turkey in aerospace industry. You&#8217;ll not only have lectures, but also visit production line in the factory of TAI, laboratories of Aerospace Engineering Department of Middle East Technical University, and aeronautic museums. In addition, you&#8217;ll have an opportunity to see a simulation of how unmanned aerial vehicle works.</p>\n<p>Now lets move on to the fun part! We guarantee the enjoying part will be awesome as much as the academic part. You will have a great chance to get know &#8220;T<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kebab" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://en.wikipedia.org'']);">urkish Kebab</a>&#8220;, &#8220;<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nargile" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://en.wikipedia.org'']);">Turkish Nargile</a>&#8220;, &#8220;<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Belly_dance" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://en.wikipedia.org'']);">Turkish Belly Dance</a>&#8220;, &#8220;<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rak" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://en.wikipedia.org'']);">Turkish Raki</a>&#8221; and the most important one Turkish Hospitality. Accommodation will be in the guest house of Turkish Aeronautics Association; that is, you&#8217;re gonna stay with quite many planes. Every night well enjoy with the non-stop and crazy parties with different themes such as masquerade party, aeronautics party where guys can be pilot and girls can be hostess for one night! But it&#8217;s for sure; we&#8217;ll not forget to have some EESTEC event traditions like sightseeing, international night as well.</p>\n<p>LC Ankara will host <strong>15 participants</strong>; however, we&#8217;ll do our best to accept more participants. <strong>Deadline to apply is the 1st of November</strong>.</p>\n<p>As you see, such a wonderful event in different continent, Asia is ready for you. So what you are supposed to do now is just to enter <a href="http://eestec.net" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://eestec.net'']);">eestec.net</a> and submit your application form!!</p>\n<p>If you have any question, feel free to ask via <strong>mervebilgic90@gmail.com</strong>.</p>\n<p>Looking forward to seeing you here!!</p>\n<p>Greetings from Turkey!</p>\n', 'Above us only Sky!', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'above-us-only-sky', '', '', '2010-10-22 23:23:41', '2010-10-22 22:23:41', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/above-us-only-sky/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2313, 1, '2010-10-22 23:10:55', '2010-10-22 22:10:55', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>Have you ever wondered what it would be like to build some robots? Or maybe you are curious about how amazing Riga and its nightlife is? JLC Riga has prepared for you our very first workshop Plop, Plop, Fizz, Fizz, Oh, What a Robot it is? and it will take place in Latvia, Riga from 5th till 12th December .</p>\n<p>With the help of experienced trainers you will be able to gain practical skills to operate electronical components and learn basic programming that will let the Robot you build become a real fighter! All the built robots will take part Baltic states robot contest Robotika.</p>\n<p>Besides that, we are planning to show you our best places in Riga and not only. You should know that Riga is famous with its architecture and skyline of 3 Church steeples, which has become a true visiting card. Well, of course when the sun goes down, the nightlife can begin and Old Riga is full of places to have fun  plenty of pubs and clubs. But you will have to see it all for yourselves.</p>\n<p>For the weekend we have prepared to you little trip to Sigulda (also called The Switzerland of Latvia) which is famous for its Castles and adorable landscapes.</p>\n<p>Well, we cannot tell you all the details, but we can assure you that you will love it here. Don&#8217;t miss this <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EO_9_Zd8pqk" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://www.youtube.com'']);">beautiful city</a> !</p>\n<p>See you in Riga! <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /> </p>\n', 'Plop, Plop, Fizz, Fizz, Oh, What a Robot it is?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'plop-plop-fizz-fizz-oh-what-a-robot-it-is', '', '', '2010-10-22 23:10:55', '2010-10-22 22:10:55', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/plop-plop-fizz-fizz-oh-what-a-robot-it-is/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2314, 1, '2010-10-22 23:04:22', '2010-10-22 22:04:22', '\n<p>Dear EESTECers,</p>\n<p>LC Munich is proud to announce that we will organize an event never done<br />\nbefore: The soon-to-be-legendary Oktoberfest Exchange!<br />\nIt will take place between Wednesday the 29th September and Tuesday the<br />\n4th October.</p>\n<p>A few words regarding the concept of this exchange: There will be no<br />\nlectures, however, entertainment during your stay in Munich will be cared<br />\nfor. We will accommodate you privately, since there is no way to get a<br />\nhotel spot in Munich during Oktoberfest without paying ridiculous prices.<br />\nUnfortunately we have to ask a participation fee of 90. This includes<br />\nbeer and food at the Oktoberfest worth 27. Be advised, however, that you<br />\nwill very likely spend a lot more money on beer &#8212; one beer is 8.50.<br />\nMunich is generally an expensive place during the Oktoberfest, but as<br />\nusual, everything except for drinks is included for our participants.<br />\nThe exchange will include two visits to the famous &#8220;Wiesn&#8221; along with<br />\nsightseeing to famous places such as Neuschwanstein, a nearby castle built<br />\nby Bavarian King Ludwig II.</p>\n<p>For various organisational reasons we unfortunately cannot accept more<br />\nthan 10-12 participants, the exact number is yet to be announced. We<br />\nencourage you very much to apply, after all this is a once in a lifetime<br />\nopportunity (unless we do it again next year) to visit the famous<br />\nOkotberfest with few fellow EESTECers!! Don&#8217;t miss out and send your<br />\napplication today <img src=''http://eestec-lj.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':-)'' class=''wp-smiley'' /><br />\nDeadline to apply is Saturday, August 14th, 12 PM (noon).</p>\n<p><strong>Disclaimer:</strong> Due to the nature of the event and the extraordinary<br />\ncircumstances, we reserve the right not to respect your priority list. We<br />\nencourage you, however, to send one anyway and apologize for the<br />\ninconvenience. We&#8217;ll try to fulfill your request as good as possible.</p>\n', 'Oktoberfest Exchange', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'oktoberfest-exchange', '', '', '2010-10-22 23:04:22', '2010-10-22 22:04:22', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/oktoberfest-exchange/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2315, 1, '2010-07-24 18:30:52', '2010-07-24 17:30:52', '\n<p><strong><br />\n</strong></p>\n<h2>Green Week in Novi Sad  Act Now &#8211; Change the Future</h2>\n<p>eYouwins &#8211; The European Youth Week in Novi Sad is the one of the first and the largest youth festival with a thematic focus in Serbia. eYouwins is dedicated to youth in Serbia, Europe and worldwide, and its mission is to promote the spirit of cooperation, to link cultures, ideas and, above all, people. Festival has started in 2006 and in short time has gained popularity among young people all over Europe. During the last four years more than 5000 young people were involved in the Festival events and almost 400 guests from 25 countries visited Novi Sad and Serbia.</p>\n<p>In 2010 eYouwins celebrates 5th birthday and invites 150 participants to come to Novi Sad, between 17th and 24th August; to focus on green ways of life and sustainable development of our society. Therefore, this year eYouwins is greenWins.<br />\nProgram of the greenWins is structured as a combination of three elements: education, action and fun.<br />\nEducational part of greenWins will be composed of lectures and workshops. The main part of the thematic work of greenWins will be the group work on different topics organized in six different workshops which highlight the Festival theme from various aspects. The second segment of greenWins is Action. In this segment, participants will be directly involved in actions related to Festival topic, practicing ecological habits and raising awareness in Novi Sad and its surrounding. Finally, third segment of the Festival, Fun, covers activities relating to art, music and sport. Traditional Youth Carnival during Festival weekend will bring interesting concerts and dance performances organized for participants, citizens and other visitors of Novi Sad.</p>\n<p>Planned workshops<br />\nWS1  reCycle it! (what, how &amp; where to recycle)<br />\nWS2  Art of Waste (creative reuse of waste)<br />\nWS3  Blue Gold (Water Scarcity )<br />\nWS4  Ecology Hotspots (mapping ecology problems)<br />\nWS5Energy (R)evolution (managing energy resources)<br />\nWS6  Changing Clime (climate change)</p>\n<p>Participation fee for greenWins is 60 EURO for international participants and 3000 Dinars for the participants from Serbia.<br />\nThe participation fee covers accommodation, and meals during the Festival (light breakfast, lunch and dinner per day), organised excursions, sightseeing, entrance fees, and free participation in trips, conference programme, cultural and sport events of the Festival.<br />\nIn participants fee is not included travel costs and personal expenses!!!<br />\nAccepted participants will pay the participants fee on arrival, at the registration. If you want to take a part in the Festival fill the registration form as earlier as you can!!!</p>\n<p>Application deadline is 15th July 20010!!</p>\n<p>For more information on the festival please visit our website at: <a href="http://eyouwins.com/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push([''_trackEvent'',''outbound-article'',''http://eyouwins.com'']);">http://eyouwins.com</a></p>\n<p>Should you have any questions, please do not hesitate to contact me at any time!</p>\n<p>We hope to see you in Novi Sad!!!</p>\n', 'greenWins 2010', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'greenwins-2010', '', '', '2010-07-24 18:30:52', '2010-07-24 17:30:52', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/workshops-exchanges/greenwins-2010/', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2488, 1, '2013-03-06 00:36:20', '2013-03-05 23:36:20', 'Greetings from The North.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nEverything today is driven by computers, bigger or smaller ones. Almost everything that has any kind of electronics includes a computing unit also. So what are these, why they make so complex things work? We try to find this answer for you as we open the world of digital technology for you.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAND SO! We proudly announce our new workshop"Workshop of 41:73:73:65:6d:62:6c:79". Our fellows at computer techlab are more than welcoming to take you for a tour in the world of computing with ones and zeros.<b></b>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nFor one week our LC is happy to host you to enjoy our beautiful city of Tampere, the northernmost LC in eestec. If you think this is going to be one of those easier workshops where you can sleep between lectures then youre gravely mistaken. We indeed take our education seriously but we take our parties even more seriously. In one week we will introduce you to the whole new world of sauna, singing, Finnish culture, city life of small town and the right Finnish way of doing things wrong.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSo, everyone who has any interest in digital designs, embedded systems, computers or just generally is trying to find something interesting to study, we openly welcome you.\r\n\r\nWed really appreciate those applications that have some information about what you generally study and what you know about digital designs and computer technologies as our professor may want people to have some degree of knowledge about the area.', 'Workshop of 41:73:73:65:6d:62:6c:79', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'workshop-of-417373656d626c79', '', '', '2013-03-06 00:36:20', '2013-03-05 23:36:20', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/?post_type=workshops_exchanges&#038;p=2488', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2562, 1, '2013-03-12 02:30:11', '2013-03-12 01:30:11', 'Prepare every single cell in your body, cause you are going to become time traveller in Belgrade, and we will give our best to be great companions in this journey. We''re happy to announce that this May you could be the part of "World Beyond Tomorrow".\r\n\r\nGuiding you through a regular family day, twenty years from now, lecturers will introduce you with new necessary technologies. Familiar with all the details and needed knowledge about 4G, hologram, must-have robots, and all innovations that strive to become a part of our everyday life, the future will seem like the present to you. In cooperation with ESTIEM, the organisation for European Students of Industrial Engineering and Management, we will show you admirable landscapes of our country and the way we define word<a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=--c03roM4nI" target="_blank">party</a>. So, you will also have the opportunity to meet with members of their event which would be held side-by-side with our workshop.\r\n\r\nAfter a long time, we decided to show you the<a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_Zu_tkk9be0" target="_blank">White city</a>in the period when you can see it in all of its beautiful colors, through the joy of spring. Ada Ciganlija, oasis of nature in the busy city life, is waiting for you, as well as Kalemegdan, Skadarlija, Nikola Tesla Museum, Knez Mihailova street... You will have the chance to enjoy traditional<a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wIwNwZwNXuA" target="_blank">Serbian cuisine</a>, gibanica, ajvar, pljeskavica and of course rakija.\r\n\r\n\r\nApply now, and enjoy in knowledge and party time warp! :)\r\n\r\n\r\nSee you in Serbia,\r\nAnita Jovi.', 'World Beyond Tomorrow', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'world-beyond-tomorrow', '', '', '2013-03-27 17:07:10', '2013-03-27 16:07:10', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/?post_type=workshops_exchanges&#038;p=2562', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2650, 1, '2013-03-16 14:01:52', '2013-03-16 13:01:52', '<div>Dear EESTECers,</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>All of you probably remember one of the most known Latin phrases: "Historia est Magistra Vitae" :) We sure do and we are proud to announce our workshop which pretty much bases on this phrase. If you apply for Back in Time we can promise you wont regret it.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>Have you ever wondered how stuff worked before almost everything went digital and computer controlled? All those interesting and smart solutions everyone has forgotten about? In Zagreb you will have a chance to get familiar with them. Old principles of automatics, programming, power engineering and wireless technology can always come in handy to todays modern engineers. We will make comparisons between old and new, and make conclusions with pros and cons for each individual technology/solution/approach.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>Now lets get to the more interesting part of the workshop  our beautiful city of Zagreb. You will get in touch with every part of Croatian culture and have an opportunity to taste our delicious cousin and our inspiring drinks. Also, you will get a chance to enjoy our beautiful Adriatic coast and our crystal clear sea ;)</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>Our museums are going to give you a very good insight into our culture and you will spend time exploring Zagreb in a really interesting way. We will make sure you have enough time to enjoy the city and relax.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>And the most important part  youll attend the most awesome parties in Zagreb and we can assure you that you will remember them for your life.</div>\r\n<div>So, dont hesitate to apply to our super duper workshop! We promise you good time :)</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>If you have any questions or need more convincing just contact us.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>With love from LC Zagreb &lt;3</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div><span style="color: #222222; font-family: arial,sans-serif;"><span style="color: #888888;"><span style="color: #888888;"><br clear="all" /> </span></span></span></div>\r\n<iframe src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/Xsz49mzCVg0" height="315" width="560" allowfullscreen="" frameborder="0"></iframe>', 'Back in Time', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'back-in-time', '', '', '2013-04-04 12:59:46', '2013-04-04 11:59:46', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/?post_type=workshops_exchanges&#038;p=2650', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2652, 1, '2013-03-16 14:08:48', '2013-03-16 13:08:48', '<div id="parent-fieldname-text">\r\n\r\nDear EESTECers,\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWe are proud to announce our next workshop. After a long tradition of successful workshops, we are still trying to do better and improve our offer! This time we will amuse you with a workshop related to Green and Eco Friendly Technologies.\r\nFuture Technologies are coming to be more and more green. Our lectures will deal with Green Computing technologies, having a deep practical insight: we will have the honor to host some successful StartUp in this field, that will explain how it works in real life.\r\n\r\nGreen Economy is the new challenge, and we are ready to catch it!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nMoreover this year there will be an exclusive news! Our workshop will be held in collaboration with ESTIEM Association (European Students of Industrial Engineering and Management). Green supply chain will be the other topic that you will have the opportunity do deal with.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nIt means a double opportunity to meet and melt with Students from all Europe!!!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAcademics activity will be just a short (but heaped) bracket in your experience here in Cosenza.\r\nCosenza is the biggest Campus in the South of Italy. A neighborhood made up exclusively of 2000 Students and 200 Erasmus Students, offers one of the most brave and challenging night life! <strong>Get ready for it!!!</strong>\r\n\r\nYou will have also the opportunity to visit the most stunning and breathtaking landscapes of our land! The land of the sun, the sea and the good food! All this delved in a rich cultural background ( don''t forget that Pitagora was born in Calabria ;) ).\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nCalabria is waiting for you, see you there!!! :D\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nPS: We will provide you a detailed programme as soon as possible.\r\n\r\n</div>', 'GECO (Green Engineering COmputing)', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'geco-green-engineering-computing', '', '', '2013-03-16 14:08:48', '2013-03-16 13:08:48', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/?post_type=workshops_exchanges&#038;p=2652', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2664, 1, '2013-03-27 20:32:39', '2013-03-27 19:32:39', '<div>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><b><i>Hello dear friends, students and other members of NGOs!</i></b></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><b><i>LeadershipSummer School is coming!</i></b></span>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><b><i>Do you want to inspire people? Do you have plans to lead a project in your NGO? Do you think that the word leader describes you?</i></b></span>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><b><i>Interested? </i></b></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><b><i>Apply to LSS`13.</i></b></span>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<b><i><span style="color: #000000;">Our project will help you discover your potential!</span></i></b>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><b><i>Together we can change the world!</i></b></span>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<span style="color: #000000;">==============================<wbr />==========================\r\n</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><b>==What is LSS?===</b></span>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;">The Leadership Summer Schoolis an intensive learning event and a networking platform, aimingat increasing skills and readiness of youth NGO leaders, sharing best practices and improving leadership skills among prominent members of each participating organisation.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"></span>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><b>===What are we looking for?===</b></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;">We are looking for<b>70 highly motivated and active students and youth</b>who will participate to a challenging learning event.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><b>===When and Where?===</b></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;">Sofia (Bulgaria)<i>f</i></span>rom<b>21st till 30th of July 2013</b>\r\n\r\n<img alt="Inline images 2" src="https://mail.google.com/mail/u/0/?ui=2&amp;ik=6c33839bd5&amp;view=att&amp;th=13dad4cf0ee7a16d&amp;attid=0.1&amp;disp=emb&amp;realattid=ii_13dad39a8865b14e&amp;zw&amp;atsh=1" width="420" height="310" />\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><b>===What about the fee?===</b></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;">The fee will be<b>190 EUR</b>whichincludes:\r\n</span>- accommodation;\r\n- food (3 meals per day + coffee breaks);\r\n- transport for LSS activities;\r\n- and some social activities.\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;">If selected to participate in the event, it will be requested from you to pay 50% of the fee (95 EUR) as participation confirmation: this amount is<i><b>not refundable</b></i>. The rest can be paid anticipatively or at the event itself. More details will be communicated at that moment.</span>\r\n\r\n<i><span style="color: #000000;">We are not able to provide scholarship or any form of discount.</span></i>\r\n\r\n<i><span style="color: #000000;"></span></i>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<b><span style="color: #000000;">===How to apply?===</span></b>\r\n\r\n<b><span style="color: #000000;"></span></b>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;">Fill the<a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1zqu6fpLsWGk9QtI5Ln72Pzlx2BWv9xWiEF6Ha19Qn2A/viewform" target="_blank">LSS 2013 Application form</a>.</span>\r\n<div><span style="color: #000000;"></span></div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div dir="ltr">\r\n<div><i><b>Deadline to apply: April 14th 23:59 CET</b></i></div>\r\n<b><span style="color: #000000;">===And now ===</span></b>\r\nWe are looking forward to reading your applications and if you have any questions or suggestions, feel free to contact us by mail:<a href="mailto:contact@leadershipsummerschool.org" target="_blank">contact@<wbr />leadershipsummerschool.org</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'Leadership Summer School 2013', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'leadership-summer-school-2013', '', '', '2013-03-27 20:36:33', '2013-03-27 19:36:33', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/?post_type=workshops_exchanges&#038;p=2664', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2670, 1, '2013-03-27 21:07:17', '2013-03-27 20:07:17', 'DearEESTECers,\r\n\r\nWe, LC Delft, are proud to announce our next workshop Tie Another Day  A challange from Mars,\r\n\r\nFirst of all, welcome to the<strong>Mars rover project</strong>! In this powerful workshop we give you a directive to design a complex system. We have taken a top-down approach. This way you can understand the operation of the increasingly larger parts within the whole system.\r\n\r\nIn the first part of the workshop you will design a mobile robot (the Mars Rover) in a group of students. This robot has to be able to search for a line and then track the line and take turns. Some<strong>additional intelligence</strong>has to be added as well. The design steps are not only useful for this workshop, but also for complex systems in general. First you focus at the problem as a whole, and then the problem is divided into even smaller parts which are then implemented. This is the so-called top-down approach.\r\n\r\nIn the design you have to deal with operation and readout of input signals (sensors), output actuators the motors) and a controller. The robot is programmed in VHDL. VHDL is a Hardware Description Language (HDL), a language which is used to help design digital circuits.\r\n\r\nIn order to test the Mars Rover,<strong>a complex maze</strong>is available. Your Mars Rover has to find the way out as fast as possible. As an added challenge, the maze contains instructions for the Mars Rover for making sharp turns that allows a faster traversal of the maze.\r\n\r\nThe second part of the workshop focuses on the<strong>power supply of the Mars Rover</strong>. In the first part of the workshop, the robot will use batteries as its power supply. If the batteries run out of power, you can easily replace them. However, on Mars this would pose a problem. In order to be able to use the Mars rover for an extended amount of time, an alternative energy source is needed. On Mars it is possible to use solar energy to power the Mars rover. In the second part of the workshop you will examine a solar cell and design additional circuits in order to use the solar energy as the power supply of the Mars rover.\r\n\r\nObvious this is not everything in the weekend and at every evening there will be time to explore other things like Delft and The Netherlands. So dont hesitate and apply before Friday the 19<sup>th</sup>of april.\r\n\r\nFor Questions dont hesitate to contact<a href="mailto:cp@etv.tudelft.nl">cp@etv.tudelft.nl</a> for further questions.', 'Tie Another Day - A Challenge from Mars', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'tie-another-day-a-challange-from-mars', '', '', '2013-03-27 21:36:26', '2013-03-27 20:36:26', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/?post_type=workshops_exchanges&#038;p=2670', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2673, 1, '2013-03-27 21:23:26', '2013-03-27 20:23:26', '<div id="parent-fieldname-text">\r\n\r\nDear EESTECers,\r\n\r\nWere proud to announce the second edition of a workshop entitled Smart Energy for a Better World, in cooperation with ABB Corporate Research Centre, which will be held in Krakow from 7th till 13th of July 2013.\r\n\r\nThis study tour is dedicated to students, who want to learn about modern solutions in the field of energy, automation and electrical science. The event will be a unique opportunity to visit one of the most advanced ABB Research Centers in the world and to broaden your knowledge on:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Advanced numerical simulations</li>\r\n	<li>Power electronics</li>\r\n	<li>Transients phenomena</li>\r\n	<li>Smart Protection</li>\r\n	<li>Advanced diagnostics</li>\r\n	<li>Ferroresonance phenomena</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nAll students from European Universities are invited to join us in Krakow, one of Poland''s most renown cities. This event will be a great occasion to meet experts on energy, electrical sciences and to visit Poland''s well-known tourist attractions.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWe are waiting for applications from students who have:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>electrical engineering profile</li>\r\n	<li>good academic results</li>\r\n	<li>good command of English</li>\r\n	<li>completed at least 3 years of university education</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nMore information about the lectures and lab excercises can be found on the website of the event<a href="http://smart.eestec.pl/" target="_blank">here</a>.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nFeel the EESTEC Spirit and join us in Krakw. See with your own eyes the beauty one of the biggest city in Poland with its historicial treasures and vivid nightlife. Youve got an unusual opportunity to visit i.a.:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>the Wawel Royal Castle - located at the Vistula River the residence of Polish kings and queens;</li>\r\n	<li>the Underground of the Citys Main Market Square  unusual place created by modern technology with the exhibition of the monuments from the Middle Ages;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nWe will go on a tour to Kryspinw lake, barbecue at the biggest student campus in Poland or have a bowling night. We wont reveal all of the spicy attractions weve prepared. We can say youll certainly experience the amazing nightlife and many other activities so you wont get chance to get bored. Apply now or regret through the lifetime.\r\n\r\nHow to apply:\r\n\r\n1. EESTEC members: via eestec.net, where you should write down your motivational letter and send your CV to<a href="mailto:krakow@eestec.net">krakow@eestec.net</a>\r\n\r\n2. Non-EESTECers: via website:<a href="http://smart.eestec.pl/" target="_blank">smart.eestec.pl</a>\r\n\r\nWere waiting for You in Krakow! ;)\r\n<div></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<a id="parent-fieldname-eventUrl" href="http://smart.eestec.pl/" target="_blank">More information about this event</a>', 'Smart Energy for a Better World 2', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'smart-energy-for-a-better-world-2', '', '', '2013-05-15 14:15:43', '2013-05-15 13:15:43', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/?post_type=workshops_exchanges&#038;p=2673', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(2910, 1, '2013-04-08 20:19:59', '2013-04-08 19:19:59', '<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Dear EESTECers,\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">LC Belgrade is proud to announce its first <a href="http://tinyurl.com/cd2zv47" target="_blank">International Motivational Weekend</a>, which will be held from 17th to 19th May! We are bringing the participants of our workshop <strong>World Beyond Tomorrow",</strong> as a conclusion to a great event! The best way to participate at the IMW is to apply for our workshop!</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Prepare yourself to enjoy in the youth camp erdap, located in the tourist region Karata, just in the period in all of its beautiful colors, through the joy of spring! You will have the chance to enjoy in our beautiful countryside, visit Hydroelectric Power Station erdap 1" - the largest and first producer of hydroelectricity in Southeast Europe, take part in many fun activities like the games without limits, indoor soccer tournaments, beach volleyball, beer pong in the evening, have great fun at the parties and a lot of other funny things!</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">The participation fee is <strong>55</strong>, which includes return journey from Belgrade to Karata, accommodation, 3 meals a day, drinks and free theme parties. At the IMW we will be accompanied by members of association <i>ESTIEM LG Belgrade</i>, so we definitely need all of you to join us and show them our EESTEC spirit! Also, you can ask us to book a room for you at the hostel in Belgrade, if you want to stay few more days.</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Our bus will leave Belgrade at 09:00 am on Friday and back from the location on a Sunday afternoon.</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">We promise you won''t regret it! <a href="http://eestec.net/lc/belgrade/imw-belgrade-2013" target="_blank">See you in Serbia</a>!</span></p>', 'IMW Belgrade 2013', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'imw-belgrade-2013', '', '', '2013-04-08 20:19:59', '2013-04-08 19:19:59', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/?post_type=workshops_exchanges&#038;p=2910', 0, 'events', '', 0);
