(3171, 18, '2013-09-23 11:58:25', '2013-09-23 10:58:25', 'Dear EESTECers,\r\n\r\nThe 6thT4Tis in front of us and as you had the chance to see it will be organized by amazing LC Skopje between<b>20th</b>and<b>30th October</b>, who decided to take the organization and contribute to our EESTEC family!\r\n\r\nBelow you can find more information about EESTEC''s Training Team, the event itself, the purpose of organizing it and the benefits of becoming an EESTEC Trainer. Have fun! :)\r\n\r\n<b>What is the EESTEC Training Team? What are Trainings?</b>\r\n\r\n<b></b>EESTEC Training Team is an official EESTEC body which is providing different services for EESTEC and through those services, based on trainings, constantly improving the work of EESTEC on international and local levels!\r\n\r\nMain goal of trainings is transfer of knowledge in an advanced way through different activities, techniques and methodologies.\r\n\r\nMore details and information about the Training Team, Training System and Trainings you can find in the Official Training Team Document<a href="http://eestec.net/workspaces/training-team/training-material/Training%20Team%20Official%20documents/1st%20Official%20Training%20Team%20Document.pdf/view?searchterm=training%20document" target="_blank">here</a>.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>What isT4T? Why isT4Tbeing organized?</b>\r\n\r\nT4T Training for Trainers is an international training event whose purpose is gaining new EESTEC trainers and it is the starting point for EESTECers to become a trainer.\r\n\r\nEESTECers which participate inT4Twill go through intensive trainings, working sessions and practical parts and learn how to transfer knowledge, which methodologies to use and, very important, how to deliver trainings!\r\n\r\nAs the transfer of knowledge is crucial for EESTEC,T4Tis an event which assures new generations to continue with developing and providing Training Team services to EESTEC members. It is a stage through all Training team members have to go in order to gain differentsoft skills like: leadership skills, presentation skills, communication skills and much more!\r\n\r\nUsing these skills for transferring knowledge in EESTEC provides greater quality of different activities which are being organized in International and local levels.\r\n\r\nDuringT4T,<b>10 days</b>of a lot of work is waiting for you so you will need to bring<b>a lot of positive energy</b>and<b>enthusiasm</b>in order to be effective all the time and to be able to endure theT4T.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Why become a Trainer? Why should you apply?</b>\r\n\r\nThere are definitely a lot of reasons to apply. Becoming a trainer gives you an opportunity to contribute to EESTEC International, to contribute to LCs and to contribute to yourselves!\r\n\r\nAs a trainer candidate (and optionally trainer) you will work in and create a positive atmosphere duringT4Tand after. If you become a trainer (for what you need to fulfill certain tasks) you will work on the transfer of knowledge to other EESTECers and you will have an opportunity to improve on personal level in different aspects. Besides the opportunities to deliver trainings afterwards, you will become member of the EESTEC Training Team where you will opportunities to work on different projects together with other teammates and to contribute to the further development of the Team!\r\n\r\nThe skills you gain while being a trainer are needed in all aspects of life today and so in EESTEC. Because of that, members who participate inT4Thave a big opportunity to develop themselves and to give a great contribution to the development of EESTEC!\r\n\r\n<b></b><b>Fun part :)</b>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;">If you had a chance to talk with somebody who is from Skopje or who was on an event in Skopje you probably heard all the best. LC Skopje will be in charge for the fun part during evenings and free time and according to the previous events which have been organized on a high level and we believe that LC Skopje will continue this tradition and contribute in making thisT4Textraordinary! Below you can find few words from our host LC:</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n"<i>LC Skopje is honored to be the organizing committee of such an important event for EESTEC as the 6-th Training for Trainers.</i>\r\n\r\n<i>As a Local Committee that is strongly devoted to the growth and development of the EESTEC network, we believe that answering the Call for this important operational event was not only our wish, but also an utmost duty.</i>\r\n\r\n<i>This year, for the first time,T4Twill be held in two cities: Skopje &amp; Ohrid (The balkan Jerusalem). After the success of 2 international events this calendar year, we are more than prepared to organize our third event, but don''t worry another one is coming up.</i>\r\n\r\n<i>IfT4Talone is not enough motivation to apply, we offer you great Macedonian cuisine, hospitality and parties!!!</i>\r\n\r\n<i>Cheers, LC Skopje.</i>"\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<i>If you are an experienced EESTECer, if you participated in trainings, if you want to become a trainer, if you want to develop yourself and EESTEC or if you think that you could become a trainer -<b>apply</b>!</i>\r\n\r\n<i></i>\r\n\r\n<i></i><i>All now is left is to fill the<a href="http://eestec.net/workspaces/training-team/training-material/Calls%20and%20Forms/T4T/6th-t4t-in-skopje/Application%20form%20for%20participants%20-%206th%20T4T%20in%20Skopje.docx/view" target="_blank"><b>application form</b></a>(<b>not apply over<a href="http://eestec.net/" target="_blank">eestec.net</a></b>) and to send it to<a href="mailto:trainings-coordinator@eestec.net" target="_blank">trainings-coordinator@eestec.<wbr />net</a>!</i>\r\n\r\n<i></i><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><b></b></span>\r\n\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><b>The deadline for applications is10th of September 2013.</b></span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nI will be glad to answer any questions and you feel free to ask anything you have on your mind (<i><a href="mailto:smajic.nermin@gmail.com" target="_blank">smajic.nermin@gmail.com</a></i>).\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWe hope to see a lot of applications! :)\r\n\r\nBest regards and enjoy!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nOn behalf of LC Skopje and Training Team,', 'The 6th Training for Trainers  T4T', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'the-6th-training-for-trainers-t4t-lc-skopje', '', '', '2013-09-23 12:52:59', '2013-09-23 11:52:59', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/?post_type=workshops_exchanges&#038;p=3171', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(3177, 18, '2013-09-23 12:46:50', '2013-09-23 11:46:50', 'Dear EESTECers,\r\n\r\nLC Munich/Awesome is proud to announce the<strong><i>OktoberfestExchange</i></strong>2013 from<strong>October 1st</strong>until<strong>October 6th</strong>.\r\nYou will have the honor of drinking the world''s finest beer in the world''s finest city with the most sophisticated soon-to-be engineers in Europe.\r\n\r\nBesides all these tempting facts we are also planning a cultural program, a City-Rally, sightseeing, and clubbing. There won''t be any lectures, however plenty of entertainment during your stay in Munich is guaranteed.\r\n\r\nSince hostel prices are ridiculous duringOktoberfest, we will be accommodating you privately. This year we wont ask you for a participation fee, but we need to ask you to pay everything yourself. This is not an official EESTEC event, its just a meeting among friends. We have to warn you though, Munich is generally an expensive place duringOktoberfest. A liter of beer (onOktoberfest) is<strong>9.40</strong>to<strong>9.85</strong>! No need to worry, we will not be spending the entire week atOktoberfestitself, and you will have a lot of chances to get cheaper beer! :)\r\n\r\n<strong>This is a once in a lifetime chance to experienceOktoberfest!</strong>\r\n\r\nAsk your EESTEC friends from Munich first, if they can host you. Then you can talk to them about how long to stay and some other activities. If some of you want to explore the vicinity of Munich, i.e. Castle Neuschwanstein or one of the lakes in the Alps, we can make such trips too! We plan to go toOktoberfeston Wednesday and Friday.\r\n\r\nAgain, this is the opportunity of your life to enjoy the world''s biggest beer festival (and party) with your fellow EESTECers! We strongly encourage you toapply! :) If you have any questions, feel free to ask me (<a href="mailto:Andreas.albrecht@fs.ei.tum.de" target="_blank">Andreas.albrecht@fs.ei.tum.de</a><wbr />) or any EESTECer from Munich you know.\r\n\r\nP.S. Loving beer is a must ;)\r\n\r\nSee you in Munich,\r\nAndreas Albrecht', 'Oktoberfest Exchange 2013', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'oktoberfest-exchange-2013', '', '', '2013-09-23 12:52:24', '2013-09-23 11:52:24', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/?post_type=workshops_exchanges&#038;p=3177', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(3183, 18, '2013-09-23 12:56:09', '2013-09-23 11:56:09', '<div><strong>Dear EESTECers</strong>,</div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>It''s true! Observer Xanthi is finally proud to announce its first workshop!! So behold and get ready to Rock-the-bit!!</div>\r\n<div>We have prepared for you a unique event, with lots of innovative ideas, that promises you a refreshing escape from university courses and studying obligations, right in the middle of November!!</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div><strong>What''s the topic?</strong></div>\r\n<div>The goal of this workshop is to familiarize attendees with the Arduino platform and teach them how to develop an Arduino-based code, in order to create several musical instruments and eventually form a rock-band!!! The practical sessions will consist of four main teams, each one responsible for a different instrument. Therefore, except from the academic part, you will also be able to improve your social and teamwork skills. In case you don''t have any prior knowledge of programming do not be alarmed! Alongside with the labs, there will be lectures focused on both the Arduino project and miscellaneous technological topics, like sound and music technology.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div><strong>Is that all?</strong></div>\r\n<div>Of course not!</div>\r\n<div>Xanthi is one of the most beautiful cities of northern Greece, best known for the quaint Old-Town. Through the City Rally you will explore every hidden treasure of every narrow street of the city with the 1000 colors. Get ready to experience the world''s famous greek hospitality, taste the local drinks and visit the landscape of outstanding natural beauty during the Motivational Weekend right at the end of our Workshop. You should definitely prepare yourself for more surprises to come..!!</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div>We invite you to join us from 17th to 24th of November 2013 and promise you an unforgettable week here in Xanthi, Greece.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div><strong>See you all in Xanthi!</strong></div>', 'Rock the bit', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'rock-the-bit', '', '', '2013-09-23 13:01:16', '2013-09-23 12:01:16', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/?post_type=workshops_exchanges&#038;p=3183', 0, 'events', '', 0),
(3190, 18, '2013-09-23 13:06:10', '2013-09-23 12:06:10', '<strong>Dear EESTECers !</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>LC zmir</strong> represents brand new workshop Braintrainer in cooperation with LG zmir. As a joint project of EESTEC and ESTIEM , Braintrainer will take place on the dates 1-7 December.\r\n\r\n<strong>During this workshop</strong> you''re going to improve your management skills and also as we always do you will have fun, meet new people and see fancy places.\r\n\r\nFirst 3 days of the workshop we''re going to be in a nice hotel which is out of city and we will relax a bit while we are away from the stress of the city life. On those days our lovely trainers from ESTIEM and EESTEC will give you training sessions and then nights will be ours !\r\n\r\n<strong>After enjoying</strong> those 3 days we will turn back to the city life, case will be open for us . Get ready business people ! Who solves the case first , wins the price! Do you wanna know who will be responsible for case studies here is just 2 examples : Schneider Electric , Bosch and there are even better companies ! May be if you are good enough you can get an internship offer too.\r\n\r\nWhen business is done , it''s time for pleasure we''ll have some visits to surroundings of the city. You need to know where ? Then here is a hint : One of them is irince where you can find unique kind of wines that''s why irince is called as a village of wines !\r\n\r\n<strong>Last but not least</strong> we guarantee you that you''re gonna have great parties over here. We''ll have our parties with our erasmus students in here and internationality level will grow up !', 'EESTEC & ESTIEM Joint Workshop BrainTrainer', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'eestec-estiem-joint-workshop-braintrainer', '', '', '2013-09-23 13:13:45', '2013-09-23 12:13:45', '', 0, 'http://eestec-lj.org/?post_type=workshops_exchanges&#038;p=3190', 0, 'events', '', 0),
